of Persian origin; Medatha, the father of Haman: Hammedatha (including the article).

or mah; or ma; or ma; also meh; a primitive particle; properly, interrogative what? (including how? why? when?); but also exclamation, what! (including how!), or indefinitely what (including whatever, and even relatively, that which); often used with prefixes in various adverbial or conjunctive senses: how (long, oft, (- soever)), (no-)thing, what (end, good, purpose, thing), whereby(-fore, -in, -to, -with), (for) why.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָה: how great (mighty), that which, what(-soever), why.
apparently a denominative from מָה; properly, to question or hesitate, i.e. (by implication) to be reluctant: delay, linger, stay selves, tarry.
from הוּם; confusion or uproar: destruction, discomfiture, trouble, tumult, vexation, vexed.
of Persian origin; Mehuman, a eunuch of Xerxes: Mehuman.
from יָטַב (augmented) and אֵל; bettered of God; Mehetabel, the name of an Edomitish man and woman: Mehetabeel, Mehetabel.
or mahir; from מָהַר; quick; hence, skilful: diligent, hasty, ready.
a primitive root; properly, to cut down or reduce, i.e. by implication, to adulterate: mixed.
from הָלַך; a walking (plural collectively), i.e. access: place to walk.
from הָלַך; a walk, i.e. a passage or a distance: journey, walk.
from הָלַל; fame: praise.
from מַהֲלָל and אֵל; praise of God; Mahalalel, the name of an antediluvian patriarch and of an Israelite: Mahalaleel.
from הָלַם; a blow: stripe, stroke.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; perhaps an abyss: deep pit.
from הָפַך; a destruction: when...overthrew, overthrow(-n).
from הָפַך; a wrench, i.e. the stocks: prison, stocks.

a primitive root; properly, to be liquid or flow easily, i.e. (by implication); to hurry (in a good or a bad sense); often used (with another verb) adverbially, promptly: be carried headlong, fearful, (cause to make, in, make) haste(-n, -ily), (be) hasty, (fetch, make ready) X quickly, rash, X shortly, (be so) X soon, make speed, X speedily, X straightway, X suddenly, swift.
a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as מָהַר through the idea of readiness in assent); to bargain (for a wife), i.e. to wed: endow, X surely.
from מָהַר; properly, hurrying; hence (adverbially) in a hurry: hasteth, hastily, at once, quickly, soon, speedily, suddenly.
from מָהַר; a price (for a wife): dowry.
feminine of מַהֵר; properly, a hurry; hence (adverbially) promptly: hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, make (with) speed(-ily), swiftly.
from מָהַר; hasty; Maharai, an Israelite: Maharai.

UNIQUE_WORD: מַהֵר שָׁלָל חָשׁ בַּז (mah-hare' shaw-lawl' khawsh baz)
DESCRIPTION: from מַהֵר and שָׁלָל and חוּשׁ and בָּז; hasting (is he (the enemy) to the) booty, swift (to the) prey; Maher-Shalal-Chash-Baz; the symbolical name of the son of Isaiah: Maher-sha-lal-bash-baz.
from הָתַל; a delusion: deceit.
from a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix m- and אָב; from (her (the mother's)) father; Moab, an incestuous son of Lot; also his territory and descendants: Moab.
feminine Mownabiyah; or Mowabiyth; patronymical from מוֹאָב; a Moabite or Moabitess, i.e. a descendant from Moab: (woman) of Moab, Moabite(-ish, -ss).
by transp. for מָבוֹא; an entrance: coming.
a primitive root; to melt, i.e. literally (to soften, flow down, disappear), or figuratively (to fear, faint): consume, dissolve, (be) faint(-hearted), melt (away), make soft.
a primitive root; to shake: measure.
or rather modao; from יָדַע; an acquaintance: kinswoman.
from יָדַע; acquaintance: kindred.
a primitive root; to waver; by implication, to slip, shake, fall: be carried, cast, be out of course, be fallen in decay, X exceedingly, fall(-ing down), be (re-)moved, be ready, shake, slide, slip.
from מוֹט; a wavering, i.e. fall; by implication, a pole (as shaking); hence, a yoke (as essentially a bent pole): bar, be moved, staff, yoke.
feminine of מוֹט; a pole; by implication, an ox-bow; hence, a yoke (either literal or figurative): bands, heavy, staves, yoke.
a primitive root; to become thin, i.e. (figuratively) be impoverished: be (waxen) poor(-er).

a primitive root; to cut short, i.e. curtail (specifically the prepuce, i.e. to circumcise); by implication, to blunt; figuratively, to destroy: circumcise(-ing), selves), cut down (in pieces), destroy, X must needs.

or mowl (Deuteronomy 1:1); or mowtl (Nehemiah 12:38); or mul (Numbers 22:5); from מוּל; properly, abrupt, i.e. a precipice; by implication, the front; used only adverbially (with prepositional prefix) opposite: (over) against, before, (fore-)front, from, (God-)ward, toward, with.
from יָלַד; birth; Moladah, a place in Palestine: Moladah.
from יָלַד; nativity (plural birth-place); by implication, lineage, native country; also offspring, family: begotten, born, issue, kindred, native(-ity).
from מוּל; circumcision: circumcision.
from יָלַד; genitor; Molid, an Israelite: Molid.
from סָבַב; a turn, i.e. circuit (of a building): winding about.
or mucabbah; feminine of מוּסַב; a reversal, i.e. the backside (of a gem), fold (of a double-leaved door), transmutation (of a name): being changed, inclosed, be set, turning.
from יָסַד; a foundation: foundation.
from יָסַד; a foundation: foundation.
feminine of מוּסָד; a foundation; figuratively, an appointment: foundation, grounded. Compare מֵיסְדוֹת.
or mocadah; feminine of מוֹסְדֵי; a foundation: foundation.
also (in plural) feminine mowcerah; or mocrah; from יָסַר; properly, chastisement, i.e. (by implication) a halter; figuratively, restraint: band, bond.

from יָסַר; properly, chastisement; figuratively, reproof, warning or instruction; also restraint: bond, chastening ((-eth)), chastisement, check, correction, discipline, doctrine, instruction, rebuke.
or (plural) Mocrowth feminine of מוֹסֵר; correction or corrections; Moserah or Moseroth, a place in the Desert: Mosera, Moseroth.

or moled; or (feminine) moweadah (2 Chronicles 8:13); from יָעַד; properly, an appointment, i.e. a fixed time or season; specifically, a festival; conventionally a year; by implication, an assembly (as convened for a definite purpose); technically the congregation; by extension, the place of meeting; also a signal (as appointed beforehand): appointed (sign, time), (place of, solemn) assembly, congregation, (set, solemn) feast, (appointed, due) season, solemn(-ity), synogogue, (set) time (appointed).
from יָעַד; properly, an assembly (as in מוֹעֵד); figuratively, a troop: appointed time.
from יָעַד; an appointed place, i.e. asylum: appointed.
from מוֹעָדִים and יָהּ; assembly of Jah; Moadjah, an Israelite: Moadiah. Compare מַעַדְיָה.
feminine passive participle of מָעַד; properly, made to slip, i.e. dislocated: out of joint.
from עוּף; properly, covered, i.e. dark; abstractly, obscurity, i.e. distress: dimness.
from יָעַץ; a purpose: counsel, device.
from עוּק; pressure, i.e. (figuratively) distress: affliction.
(Jer. 48:21) or meyphaath; or mephaath from יָפַע; illuminative; Mophaath or Mephaath, a place in Palestine: Mephaath.
or mopheth; from יָפָה in the sense of conspicuousness; a miracle; by implication, a token or omen: miracle, sign, wonder(-ed at).
a primitive root; to press, i.e. (figuratively) to oppress: extortioner.

or motsai; from יָצָא; a going forth, i.e. (the act) an egress, or (the place) an exit; hence, a source or product; specifically, dawn, the rising of the sun (the East), exportation, utterance, a gate, a fountain, a mine, a meadow (as producing grass): brought out, bud, that which came out, east, going forth, goings out, that which (thing that) is gone out, outgoing, proceeded out, spring, vein, (water-)course (springs).
the same as מוֹצָא; Motsa, the name of two Israelites: Moza.
feminine of מוֹצָא; a family descent; also a sewer (marg.; compare צֹאָה): draught house; going forth.
or muwtsaq; from יָצַק; narrowness; figuratively, distress: anguish, is straitened, straitness.
from עָגִיל; properly, fusion, i.e. literally, a casting (of metal); figuratively, a mass (of clay): casting, hardness.
or mutsaqah; from יָצַק; properly, something poured out, i.e. a casting (of metal); by implication, a tube (as cast): when it was cast, pipe.
a primitive root; to jeer, i.e. (intens.) blaspheme: be corrupt.
from יָקַד; a fire or fuel; abstractly, a conflagration: burning, hearth.
feminine of מוֹקֵד; fuel: burning.
or moqesh; from יָקֹשׁ; a noose (for catching animals) (literally or figuratively): by implication, a hook (for the nose): be ensnared, gin, (is) snare(-d), trap.
a primitive root; to alter; by implication, to barter, to dispose of: X at all, (ex-)change, remove.
or morat; or morah (Psa. 9:20); from יָרֵא; fear; by implication, a fearful thing or deed: dread, (that ought to be) fear(-ed), terribleness, terror.
or morag; from an unused root meaning to triturate; a threshing sledge: threshing instrument.
from יָרַד; a descent; as architecture, an ornamental appendage, perhaps a festoon: going down, steep place, thin work.
from יָרָה; an archer; also teacher or teaching; also the early rain (see יוֹרֶה): (early) rain.
or Moreh; the same as מוֹרֶה; Moreh, a Canaanite; also a hill (perhaps named from him): Moreh.
from מוּר in the sense of shearing; a razor: razor.
from יָרַט; obstinate, i.e. independent: peeled.
or Moriyah; from רָאָה and יָהּ; seen of Jah; Morijah, a hill in Palestine: Moriah.
from יָרַשׁ; a possession; figuratively, delightpossession, thought.
feminine of מוֹרָשֵׁי; a possession: heritage, inheritance, possession.
from יָרַשׁ and גַּת; possession of Gath; Moresheth-Gath, a place in Palestine: Moresheth-gath.
patrial from מוֹרֶ֫שֶׁת גַּת; a Morashtite or inhabitant of Moresheth-Gath: Morashthite.
a primitive root; to touch: feel, handle.

a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as מוּשׁ through the idea of receding by contact); to withdraw (both literally and figuratively, whether intransitive or transitive): cease, depart, go back, remove, take away.

or moshab; from יָשַׁב; a seat; figuratively, a site; abstractly, a session; by extension an abode (the place or the time); by implication, population: assembly, dwell in, dwelling(-place), wherein (that) dwelt (in), inhabited place, seat, sitting, situation, sojourning.
or Mushshiy; from מוּשׁ; sensitive; Mushi, a Levite: Mushi.
patronymical from מוּשִׁי; a Mushite (collectively) or descendants of Mushi: Mushites.
act participle feminine of מָשַׁך; something drawing, i.e. (figuratively) a cord: band.
from יָשַׁע; deliverance: salvation.

a primitive root: to die (literally or figuratively); causatively, to kill: X at all, X crying, (be) dead (body, man, one), (put to, worthy of) death, destroy(-er), (cause to, be like to, must) die, kill, necro(-mancer), X must needs, slay, X surely, X very suddenly, X in (no) wise.
(Psalm 48 or Muwth lab-ben; from מוּת and בֵּן with the preposition and article interposed; "To die for the son", probably the title of a popular song: death, Muthlabben.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָ֫וֶת; death: death.
from מוּת; death (natural or violent); concretely, the dead, their place or state (hades); figuratively, pestilence, ruin: (be) dead((-ly)), death, die(-d).
from יָתַר; literally, gain; figuratively, superiority: plenteousness, preeminence, profit.
from זָבַח; an altar: altar.
from an unused root meaning to mingle (water with wine); tempered wine: liquor.
from an unused root meaning to suck out; exhausted: burnt.
probably from an unused root meaning to faint with fear; terror; Mizzah, an Edomite: Mizzah.
probably from an unused root meaning to gather in; a granary: garner.
or mzuzah; from the same as זִיז; a door-post (as prominent): (door, side) post.
from זוּן; food: meat, victual.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָזוֹן: meat.
from זוּר in the sense of turning aside from truth; treachery, i.e. a plot: wound.
or mazor; from זוּר in the sense of binding up; a bandage, i.e. remedy; hence, a sore (as needing a compress): bound up, wound.
or mezach; from זָחַח; a belt (as movable): girdle, strength.
or (feminine) mizlagah; from an unused root meaning to draw up; a fork: fleshhook.
apparently from נָזַל in the sense of raining; a constellation, i.e. Zodiacal sign (perhaps as affecting the weather): planet. Compare מַזָּרוֹת.
from זָמַם; a plan, usually evil (machination), sometimes good (sagacity): (wicked) device, discretion, intent, witty invention, lewdness, mischievous (device), thought, wickedly.
from זָמַר; properly, instrumental music; by implication, a poem set to notes: psalm.
from זָמַר; a pruning-knife: pruning-hook.
from זָמַר; a tweezer (only in the plural): snuffers.
from the same as זְעֵיר; fewness; by implication, as superl. diminutiveness: few, X very.
from זָרָה; a winnowing shovel (as scattering the chaff): fan.
apparently from זָרָה; properly, a scatterer, i.e. the north wind (as dispersing clouds; only in plural): north.
apparently from נָזַר in the sense of distinction; some noted constellation (only in the plural), perhaps collectively, the zodiac: Mazzoroth. Compare מַזָּלוֹת.
from זָרַח; sunrise, i.e. the east: east (side, -ward), (sun-)rising (of the sun).
from זָרַע; a planted field: thing sown.
from זָרַק; a bowl (as if for sprinkling): bason, bowl.
from מָחָה in the sense of greasing; fat; figuratively, rich: fatling (one).
from the same as מֵחִים; fat, i.e. marrow: marrow.
a primitive root; to rub or strike the hands together (in exultation): clap.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָחָא; to strike in pieces; also to arrest; specifically to impale: hang, smite, stay.
or machaboo; from חָבָא; a refuge: hiding (lurking) place.
from חָבַר; a junction, i.e. seam or sewed piece: coupling.
from חָבַר; a joiner, i.e. brace or cramp: coupling, joining.
from the same as חֲבִתִּים; a pan for baking in: pan.
from חָגַר; a girdle: girding.

a primitive root; properly, to stroke or rub; by implication, to erase; also to smooth (as if with oil), i.e. grease or make fat; also to touch, i.e. reach to: abolish, blot out, destroy, full of marrow, put out, reach unto, X utterly, wipe (away, out).
from חוּג; an instrument for marking a circle, i.e. compasses: compass.
from an unused root meaning to enclose; a harbor (as shut in by the shore): haven.
or Mchiyyauel; from מָחָה and אֵל; smitten of God; Mechujael or Mechijael, an anxediluvian patriarch: Mehujael.
apparently a patrial, but from an unknown place (in the plural only for a singular); a Machavite or inhabitant of some place named Machaveh: Mahavite.
from חוּל; a (round) dance: dance(-cing).
the same as מָחוֹל; dancing; Machol, an Israelite: Mahol.
from חָזָה; a vision: vision.
from חָזָה; a window: light.
feminine plural from חָזָה; visions; Machazioth, an Israelite: Mahazioth.
from מָחָה; a stroke, i.e. battering-ram: engines.
from חוּד; junction; Mechida, one of the Nethinim: Mehida.
from חָיָה; preservation of life; hence, sustenance; also the live flesh, i.e. the quick: preserve life, quick, recover selves, reviving, sustenance, victuals.
from an unused root meaning to buy; price, payment, wages: gain, hire, price, sold, worth.
the same as מְחִיר; price; Mechir, an Israelite: Mehir.
from חָלָה; sickness; Machlah, the name apparently of two Israelitesses: Mahlah.
or (feminine) machalah; from חָלָה; sickness: disease, infirmity, sickness.
feminine of מַחֲשָׁבָה; a dance: company, dances(-cing).
from חָלַל; a cavern (as if excavated): cave.
from חָלָה; sick; Machlon, an Israelite: Mahlon.
from חָלָה; sick; Machli, the name of two Israelites: Mahli.
patronymical from מַחְלִי; a Machlite or (collectively) descendants of Machli: Mahlites.
from חָלָה; a disease: disease.
from חָלַף; a (sacrificial) knife (as gliding through the flesh): knife.
from חָלַף; a ringlet of hair (as gliding over each other): lock.
from חָלַץ; a mantle (as easily drawn off): changeable suit of apparel, change of raiment.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַחֲלֹ֫קֶת; a section (of the Levites): course.
from חָלַק; a section (of Levites, people or soldiers): company, course, division, portion. See also סֶ֫לַע הַמַּחְלְקוֹת.
from חָלָה; sickness; Machalath, probably the title (initial word) of a popular song: Mahalath.
the same as מָחֲלַת; sickness; Machalath, the name of an Ishmaelitess and of an Israelitess: Mahalath.
patrial from אָבֵל מְחוֹלָה; a Mecholathite or inhabitant of Abel-Mecholah: Mecholathite.
a denominative from חֶמְאָה; something buttery (i.e. unctuous and pleasant), as (figuratively) flattery: X than butter.
from חָמַד; delightful; hence, a delight, i.e. object of affection or desire: beloved, desire, goodly, lovely, pleasant (thing).
or machmuwd; from חָמַד; desired; hence, a valuable: pleasant thing.
from חָמַל; properly, sympathy; (by paronomasia with מַחְמַד) delight: pitieth.

from חָנָה; an encampment (of travellers or troops); hence, an army, whether literal (of soldiers) or figurative (of dancers, angels, cattle, locusts, stars; or even the sacred courts)army, band, battle, camp, company, drove, host, tents.
from מַחֲנֶה and דָּן; camp of Dan; Machaneh-Dan, a place in Palestine: Mahaneh-dan.
dual of מַחֲנֶה; double camp; Machanajim, a place in Palestine: Mahanaim.
from חָנַק: choking: strangling.
or machceh; from חָסָה; a shelter (literally or figuratively): hope, (place of) refuge, shelter, trust.
from חָסַם; a muzzle: bridle.
or machcor; from חָסֵר; deficiency; hence, impoverishment: lack, need, penury, poor, poverty, want.
from מַחֲסֶה and יָהּ; refuge of (i.e. in) Jah; Machsejah, an Israelite: Maaseiah.
a primitive root; to dash asunder; by implication, to crush, smash or violently plunge; figuratively, to subdue or destroy: dip, pierce (through), smite (through), strike through, wound.
from מָחַץ; a contusion: stroke.
from חָצַב; properly, a hewing; concretely, a quarry: hewed(-n).
from חָצָה; a halving: half.
from חָצָה; a halving or the middle: half (so much), mid(-day).
a primitive root; to crush: smite off.
from חָקַר; properly, scrutinized, i.e. (by implication) a recess: deep place.
probably from אָחַר; properly, deferred, i.e. the morrow; usually (adverbially) tomorrow; indefinitely, hereafter: time to come, tomorrow.
from the same as חַרְאֵי; a sink: draught house.
from חָרַשׁ; probably a pick-axe: mattock.
from חָרַשׁ; probably a hoe: share.
or mochoratham (1 Sam. 30:17); feminine from the same as מָחָר; the morrow or (adverbially) tomorrow: morrow, next day.

or machashebeth; from חָשַׁב; a contrivance, i.e. (concretely) a texture, machine, or (abstractly) intention, plan (whether bad, a plot; or good, advice): cunning (work), curious work, device(-sed), imagination, invented, means, purpose, thought.
from חָשַׁך; darkness; concretely, a dark place: dark(-ness, place).
from חָשַׂף; a peeling: made appear.
probably from מָחָה; erasure; Machath, the name of two Israelites: Mahath.
from חָתָה; properly, a dissolution; concretely, a ruin, or (abstractly) consternation: destruction, dismaying, ruin, terror.
the same as מְחִתָּה in the sense of removal; a pan for live coals: censer, firepan, snuffdish.
from חָתַר; a burglary; figuratively, unexpected examination: breaking up, secret search.
(Aramaic) or mtah (Aramaic); apparently corresponding to מָצָא in the intransitive sense of being found present; to arrive, extend or happen: come, reach.
apparently a denominative from טִיט; a broom (as removing dirt (compare Engl. "to dust", i.e. remove dust)): besom.
from טָבַח; slaughter: slaughter.

or (feminine) mattah; from נָטָה; a branch (as extending); figuratively, a tribe; also a rod, whether for chastising (figuratively, correction), ruling (a sceptre), throwing (a lance), or walking (a staff; figuratively, a support of life, e.g. bread): rod, staff, tribe.
from עָוַר with directive enclitic appended; downward, below or beneath; often adverbially with or without prefixesbeneath, down(-ward), less, very low, under(-neath).
from נָטָה; a bed (as extended) for sleeping or eating; by analogy, a sofa, litter or bier: bed((-chamber)), bier.
from נָטָה; a stretching, i.e. distortion (figuratively, iniquity): perverseness.
from נָטָה; expansion: stretching out.
from טָוָה; something spun: spun.
from טוּל in the sense of hammering out; an iron bar (as forged): bar.
or matmon; or matmun; from טָמַן; a secret storehouse; hence, a secreted valuable (buried); generally money: hidden riches, (hid) treasure(-s).
from נָטַע; something planted, i.e. the place (a garden or vineyard), or the thing (a plant, figuratively or men); by implication, the act, planting: plant(-ation, -ing).
or (feminine) matiammah; from טָעַם; a delicacy: dainty (meat), savoury meat.
from טָפַח; a wide cloak (for a woman): vail, wimple.
a primitive root; to rain: (cause to) rain (upon).
from מָטַר; rain: rain.
or mattarah; from נָטַר; a jail (as a guard-house); also an aim (as being closely watched): mark, prison.
from טָרַד; propulsive; Matred, an Edomitess: Matred.
from מָטַר; rainy; Matri, an Israelite: Matri.

an interrogative pronoun of persons, as מָה is of things, who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things); also (indefinitely) whoever; often used in oblique construction with prefix or suffix: any (man), X he, X him, + O that! what, which, who(-m, -se, -soever), + would to God.
from מָ֫יִם and דֹּ֫בֶא; water of quiet; Medeba, a place in Palestine: Medeba.
from יָדַד in the sense of loving; affectionate; Medad, an Israelite: Medad.
from מָ֫יִם and יֵרָקוֹן with the art. interposed; water of the yellowness; Me-haj-Jarkon, a place in Palestine: Me-jarkon.
from מָ֫יִם and זָהָב, water of gold; Me-Zahab, an Edomite: Mezahab.
from יָטַב; the best part: best.
a variation for מִיכָה; Mica, the name of two Israelites: Micha.
from מִי and (the prefix derivative from) כִּי and אֵל; who (is) like God?; Mikael, the name of an archangel and of nine Israelites: Michael.
an abbrev. of מִיכָיָה; Micah, the name of seven Israelites: Micah, Micaiah, Michah.
a contr. for מִיכָיְהוּ; Mikehu, an Israelite prophet: Micaiah (2 Chronicles 18:8).
from מִי and (the prefix derivative from) כִּי and יָהּ; who (is) like Jah?; Micajah, the name of two Israelites: Micah, Michaiah. Compare מִיכָה.
or Mikayhuw (Jeremiah 36:11); abbrev. for מִיכָיָ֫הוּ; Mikajah, the name of three Israelites: Micah, Micaiah, Michaiah.
for מִיכָיָה; Mikajah, the name of an Israelite and an Israelitess: Michaiah.
from יָכֹל; properly, a container, i.e. a streamlet: brook.
apparently the same as מִיכַל הַמָּ֫יִם; revulet; Mikal, Saul's daughter: Michal.
dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); water; figuratively, juice; by euphemism, urine, semen: + piss, wasting, water(-ing, (-course, -flood, -spring)).
a form for מִנְיָמִין; Mijamin, the name of three Israelites: Miamin, Mijamin.
from an unused root meaning to portion out; a sort, i.e. species: kind. Compare מִן.
properly, feminine passive participle of יָסַד; something founded, i.e. a foundation: foundation.
from סָכַך; a portico (as covered): covert.
from מִיץ; pressure: churning, forcing, wringing.
from מוּשׁ; departure; Mesha, a place in Arabia; also an Israelite: Mesha.
from מִי and אֵל with the abbrev. insep. relatively (see אֲשֶׁר) interposed; who (is) what God (is)?; Mishael, the name of three Israelites: Mishael.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִישָׁאֵל; Mishael, an Israelite: Mishael.

or miyshor; from יָשַׁר; a level, i.e. a plain (often used (with the article prefix) as a properly, name of certain districts); figuratively, concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) justice (sometimes adverbially, justly): equity, even place, plain, right(-eously), (made) straight, uprightness.
borrowed from מֵישַׁך; Meshak, an Israelite: Meshak.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin and doubtful significance; Meshak, the Babylonian name of מִישָׁאֵל: Meshak.
from יָשַׁע; safety; Mesha, an Israelite: Mesha.
a variation for מֵישָׁע; safety; Mesha, a Moabite: Mesha.

from יָשַׁר; evenness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity or concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) rectitude (only in plural with singular sense; often adverbially): agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, (things that are) right(-eously, things), sweetly, upright(-ly, -ness).
from יָתַר; a cord (of a tent) (compare יֶ֫תֶר) or the string (of a bow): cord, string.
sometimes makcowb; also (feminine Isaiah 53:3) makfobah; from כָּאַב; anguish or (figuratively) affliction: grief, pain, sorrow.
transitive participle of כָּבַר; plenty: abundance.
from the same as כַּבּוֹן; knoll; Macbena, a place in Palestine settled by him: Machbenah.
patrial from מַכְבֵּנָה; a Macbannite or native of Macbena: Machbanai.
from כָּבַר in the sense of covering (compare כְּבָרָה); a grate: grate.
from כָּבַר in the sense of covering; a cloth (as netted (compare מִכְבָּר)): thick cloth.

or (masculine) makkeh; (plural only) from נָכָה; a blow (in 2 Chronicles 2:10, of the flail); by implication, a wound; figuratively, carnage, also pestilence: beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, X sore, stripe, stroke, wound((-ed)).
from כָּוָה; a burn: that burneth, burning.
from כּוּן; properly, a fixture, i.e. a basis; generally a place, especially as an abode: foundation, habitation, (dwelling-, settled) place.
or mkonah; feminine of מָכוֹן; a pedestal, also a spot: base.
or mkorah; from the same as כּוּר in the sense of dipping; origin (as if a mine): birth, habitation, nativity.
probably from מוּך; pining; Maki, an Israelite: Machi.
from מָכַר; salesman; Makir, an Israelite: Machir.
patronymical from מָכִיר; a Makirite or descend. of Makir: of Machir.
a primitive root; to tumble (in ruins); figuratively, to perish: be brought low, decay.
or miklah; from כָּלָא; a pen (for flocks): ((sheep-))fold. Compare מִכְלוֹת.
from כָּלָה; completion (in plural concrete adverbial, wholly): perfect. Compare מִכְלָה.
from כָּלַל; perfection (i.e. concrete adverbial, splendidly): most gorgeously, all sorts.
from כָּלַל; perfection (of beauty): perfection.
from כָּלַל; something perfect, i.e. a splendid garment: all sorts.
from אָכַל; nourishment: food.
from the same as כַּמֹּן in the sense of hiding; treasure (as hidden): treasure.
(Ezra 2:2 or Mikmash; or Mikmash (Neh. 11:31); from כָּמַס; hidden; Mikmas or Mikmash, a place in Palestine: Mikmas, Mikmash.
or mikmor; from כָּמַר in the sense of blackening by heat; a (hunter's) net (as dark from concealment): net.
or mikmoreth; feminine of מַכְמֹרִים; a (fisher's) net: drag, net.
apparently from an unused root meaning to hide; concealment; Mikmethath, a place in Palestine: Michmethath.
from מָה and נָדַב with a particle interposed; what (is) like (a) liberal (man)?; Maknadbai, an Israelite: Machnadebai.
the same as מְכוֹנָה; a base; Mekonah, a place in Palestine: Mekonah.
the same as מְכוֹנָה; a spot: base.
from כָּמַס in the sense of hiding; (only in dual) drawers (from concealing the private parts): breeches.
probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate; an assessment (as based upon a census): tribute.
from כָּסָה; a covering, i.e. weather-boarding: covering.
feminine of מֶ֫כֶס; an enumeration; by implication, a valuation: number, worth.
from כָּסָה; a covering, i.e. garment; specifically, a coverlet (for a bed), an awning (from the sun); also the omentum (as covering the intestines): clothing, to cover, that which covereth.
from כָּפַל; a fold; Makpelah, a place in Palestine: Machpelah.
a primitive root; to sell, literally (as merchandise, a daughter in marriage, into slavery), or figuratively (to surrender): X at all, sell (away, -er, self).
from מָכַר; merchandise; also value: pay, price, ware.
from נָכַר; an acquaintance: acquaintance.
from כָּרָה; a pit (for salt): (salt-)pit.
probably from the same as כּוּר in the sense of stabbing; a sword: habitation.
from מָכַר; salesman; Mikri, an Israelite: Michri.
patrial from an unused name (the same as מְכֵרוֹת) of a place in Palestine: a Mekerathite, or inhabitant of MekerahMecherathite.

or mikshol; masculine from כָּשַׁל; a stumbling-block, literally or figuratively (obstacle, enticement (specifically an idol), scruple): caused to fall, offence, X (no-)thing offered, ruin, stumbling-block.
feminine from כָּשַׁל; a stumbling-block, but only figuratively (fall, enticement (idol)): ruin, stumbling-block.
from כָּתַב; a thing written, the characters, or a document (letter, copy, edict, poem): writing.
from כָּתַת; a fracture: bursting.
from כָּתַם; an engraving, i.e. (techn.) a poem: Michtam.
from כָּתַשׁ; a mortar; by analogy, a socket (of a tooth): hollow place, mortar.
the same as מַכְתֵּשׁ; dell; the Maktesh, a place in Jerusalem: Maktesh.

or malae (Esth. 7:5); a primitive root, to fill or (intransitively) be full of, in a wide application (literally and figuratively): accomplish, confirm, + consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, X draw, give in, go) full(-ly, -ly set, tale), (over-)flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a (hand-)full, + have wholly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָלֵא; to fill: fill, be full.
from מָלֵא; full (literally or figuratively) or filling (literally); also (concretely) fulness; adverbially, fully: X she that was with child, fill(-ed, -ed with), full(-ly), multitude, as is worth.
rarely mlowf; or mlow (Ezekiel 41:8); from מָלֵא; fulness (literally or figuratively): X all along, X all that is (there-)in, fill, (X that whereof...was) full, fulness, (hand-)full, multitude.
from מָלֵא; a fulfilling (only in plural), i.e. (literally) a setting (of gems), or (technically) consecration (also concretely, a dedicatory sacrifice): consecration, be set.
feminine of מָלֵא; something fulfilled, i.e. abundance (of produce): (first of ripe) fruit, fulness.
feminine of מִלֻּאּים; a filling, i.e. setting (of gems): inclosing, setting.
from an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy; a messenger; specifically, of God, i.e. an angel (also a prophet, priest or teacher): ambassador, angel, king, messenger.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַלְאָך; an angel: angel.

from the same as מַלְאָך; properly, deputyship, i.e. ministry; generally, employment (never servile) or work (abstractly or concretely); also property (as the result of labor): business, + cattle, + industrious, occupation, (+ -pied), + officer, thing (made), use, (manner of) work((-man), -manship).
from the same as מַלְאָך; a message: message.
from the same as מַלְאָך; ministrative; Malaki, a prophet: Malachi.
from מָלֵא; fulness, i.e. (concretely) a plump socket (of the eye): X fitly.
or malbush; from לָבַשׁ; a garment, or (collectively) clothing: apparel, raiment, vestment.
from לָבַן (denominative); a brick-kiln: brickkiln.
from מָלַל (plural masculine as if from milleh; a word; collectively, a discourse; figuratively, a topic: + answer, by-word, matter, any thing (what) to say, to speak(-ing), speak, talking, word.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִלִּים; a word, command, discourse, or subject: commandment, matter, thing. word.
or mil-loe (2 Kings 12:20); from מָלֵא; a rampart (as filled in), i.e. the citadel: Millo. See also בֵּית מִלּוֹא.
from מָלַח; sea-purslain (from its saltness): mallows.
or Malluwkiy (Neh. 12:14); from מָלַך; remnant; Malluk, the name of five Israelites: Malluch, Melichu (from the margin).
feminine passive participle of מָלַך; something ruled, i.e. a realm: kingdom, king's, X royal.
from לוּן; a lodgment, i.e. caravanserai or encampment: inn, place where...lodge, lodging (place).
feminine from לוּן; a hut, a hammock: cottage, lodge.
apparently from מָלַל; I have talked (i.e. loquacious): Mallothi, an Israelite:--Mallothi.

a primitive root; properly, to rub to pieces or pulverize; intransitively, to disappear as dust; also (as denominative from מֶ֫לַח) to salt whether internally (to season with salt) or externally (to rub with salt): X at all, salt, season, temper together, vanish away.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָלַח; to eat salt, i.e. (generally) subsist: + have maintenance.
(Aramaic) from מְלַח; salt: + maintenance, salt.
from מָלַח; properly, powder, i.e. (specifically) salt (as easily pulverized and dissolved: salt((-pit)).
from מָלַח in its original sense; a rag or old garment: rotten rag.
from מָלַח in its second. sense; a sailor (as following "the salt"): mariner.
from מָלַח (in its denominative sense); properly, salted (i.e. land (אָ֫רֶץ being understood)), i.e. a desert: barren land(-ness), salt (land).
from לָחַם (in the sense of fighting); a battle (i.e. the engagement); generally, war (i.e. warfare): battle, fight(-ing), war((-rior)).

a primitive root; properly, to be smooth, i.e. (by implication) to escape (as if by slipperiness); causatively, to release or rescue; specifically, to bring forth young, emit sparks: deliver (self), escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save, X speedily, X surely.
from מָלַט, cement (from its plastic smoothness): clay.
from מֶ֫לֶט and יָהּ; (whom) Jah has delivered; Melatjah, a Gibeonite: Melatiah.
from מְלַל (in the sense of cropping (compare מוּל)); a head of grain (as cut off): ear.
from לִיץ; an aphorism; also a satire: interpretation, taunting.

a primitive root; to reign; inceptively, to ascend the throne; causatively, to induct into royalty; hence (by implication) to take counsel: consult, X indeed, be (make, set a, set up) king, be (make) queen, (begin to, make to) reign(-ing), rule, X surely.
from מָלַך; a king: king, royal.
the same as מֶ֫לֶך; king; Melek, the name of two Israelites: Melech, Hammelech (by including the article).
(Aramaic) corresponding to מֶ֫לֶך; a king: king, royal.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to מָלַך in the sense of consultation: advice: counsel.
from מָלַך; Molek (i.e. king), the chief deity of the Ammonites: Molech. Compare מִלְכֹּם.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַלְכָּה; a queen: queen.
from לָכַד; a snare: trap.
a form of מַלְכָּה; queen; Milcah, the name of a Hebrewess and of an Israelite: Milcah.
feminine of מֶ֫לֶך; a queen: queen.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַלְכוּת; dominion (abstractly or concretely): kingdom, kingly, realm, reign.
or malkuth; or (in plural) malkuyah; from מָלַך; a rule; concretely, a dominion: empire, kingdom, realm, reign, royal.
from מֶ֫לֶך and אֵל; king of (i.e. appointed by) God; Malkiel, an Israelite: Malchiel.
patronymical from מַלְכִּיאֵל; a Malkielite or descendant of Malkiel: Malchielite.
or Malkiyahuw (Jer. 38:6); from מֶ֫לֶך and יָהּ; king of (i.e. appointed by) Jah; Malkijah, the name of ten Israelites: Malchiah, Malchijah.
from מֶ֫לֶך and צֶ֫דֶק; king of right; Malki-Tsedek, an early king in Palestine: Melchizedek.
from מֶ֫לֶך and רוּם; king of a high one (i.e. of exaltation); Malkiram, an Israelite: Malchiram.
from מֶ֫לֶך and שׁ֫וּעַ; king of wealth; Malkishua, an Israelite: Malchishua.
or Milkowm; from מֶ֫לֶך for מֹ֫לֶך; Malcam or Milcom, the national idol of the Ammonites: Malcham, Milcom.
from מָלַך; a queen: queen.
feminine active participle of מָלַך; queen; Moleketh, an Israelitess: Hammoleketh (including the article).
a primitive root; to speak (mostly poetical) or say: say, speak, utter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָלַל; to speak: say, speak(-ing).
from מָלַל; talkative; Milalai, an Israelite: Milalai.
from לָמַד; a goad for oxen: goad.
a primitive root; to be smooth, i.e. (figuratively) pleasant: be sweet.
of Persian derivation; the butler or other officer in the Babylonian court: Melzar.
a primitive root; to crack a joint; by implication, to wring the neck of a fowl (without separating it): wring off.
from לָקַח; transitively (in dual) the jaws (as taking food); intransitively, spoil (and captives) (as taken): booty, jaws, prey.
from לָקַשׁ; the spring rain (compare לָ֫קֶשׁ); figuratively, eloquence: latter rain.
or malqach; from לָקַח; (only in dual) tweezers: snuffers, tongs.
from an unused root meaning to spread out; a wardrobe (i.e. room where clothing is spread): vestry.
transp. for מְתַלְּעוֹת; a grinder, i.e. back tooth: great tooth.
from מָגַר (in the sense of depositing); a granary: barn.
from מָדַד; a measure: measure.
or (transp.) Mowmukan (Esth. 1:16); of Persian derivation; Memucan or Momucan, a Persian satrap: Memucan.
from מוּת; a mortal disease; concretely, a corpse: death.
from an unused root meaning to alienate; a mongrel, i.e. born of a Jewish father and a heathen mother: bastard.
from מָכַר; merchandise; abstractly, a selling: X ought, (that which cometh of) sale, that which...sold, ware.
feminine of מִמְכָּר; a sale: + sold as.
from מָלַך; dominion, i.e. (abstractly) the estate (rule) or (concretely) the country (realm): kingdom, king's, reign, royal.
a form of מַמְלָכָה and equiv. to it: kingdom, reign.
from מָסַך; mixture, i.e. (specifically) wine mixed (with water or spices): drink-offering, mixed wine.
from an unused root meaning to grieve; sorrow: bitterness.
from מָרָא(in the sense of vigor); lusty; Mamre, an Amorite: Mamre.
from מָרַר; a bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) calamity: bitterness.
from מָשַׁח, in the sense of expansion; outspread (i.e. with outstretched wings): anointed.
from מָשַׁל; a ruler or (abstractly) rule: dominion, that ruled.
feminine of מִמְשָׁל; rule; also (concretely in plural) a realm or a ruler: dominion, government, power, to rule.
from the same as מֶ֫שֶׁק; a possession: breeding.
from מָתַק; something sweet (literally or figuratively): (most) sweet.
from מָה; literally, a whatness (so to speak), i.e. manna (so called from the question about it): manna.
(Aramaic) from מָה; who or what (properly, interrogatively, hence, also indefinitely and relatively): what, who(-msoever, + -so).

or minniy; or minney (constructive plural); (Isaiah 30:11); for מִנִּים; properly, a part of; hence (prepositionally), from or out of in many senses (as follows): above, after, among, at, because of, by (reason of), from (among), in, X neither, X nor, (out) of, over, since, X then, through, X whether, with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִן: according, after, + because, + before, by, for, from, X him, X more than, (out) of, part, since, X these, to, upon, + when.

from an unused root meaning to apportion; a part; hence, a musical chord (as parted into strings): in (the same) (Psalm 68:23), stringed instrument (Psalm 150:4), whereby (Psalm 45:8 (defective plural)).
(Aramaic) or mnah (Aramaic); corresponding to מָנָא; to count, appoint: number, ordain, set.
(Aramaic) passive participle of מְנָא; numbered: Mene.
from נָגַן; a satire: music.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַדָּע; wisdom or intelligence: knowledge, reason, understanding.
a primitive root; properly, to weigh out; by implication, to allot or constitute officially; also to enumerate or enroll: appoint, count, number, prepare, set, tell.
from מָנָא; properly, a fixed weight or measured amount, i.e. (techn.) a maneh or mina: maneh, pound.
from מָנָא; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (figuratively) a portion of time, i.e. an instance: time.
from מָנָא; properly, something weighed out, i.e. (generally) a division; specifically (of food) a ration; also a lot: such things as belonged, part, portion.
from נָהַג; the driving (of a chariot): driving.
from נָהַר; properly, a channel or fissure, i.e. (by implication) a cavern: den.
from נוּד a nodding or toss (of the head in derision): shaking.
from נ֫וּחַ; quiet, i.e. (concretely) a settled spot, or (figuratively) a home: (place of) rest.
the same as מָנ֫וֹחַ; rest; Manoach, an Israelite: Manoah.

or mnuchah; feminine of מָנ֫וֹחַ; repose or (adverbially) peacefully; figuratively, consolation (specifically, matrimony); hence (concretely) an abode: comfortable, ease, quiet, rest(-ing place), still.
from נוּן; a continuator, i.e. heir: son.
from נוּס; a retreat (literally or figuratively); abstractly, a fleeing: X apace, escape, way to flee, flight, refuge.
or mnucah; feminine of מָנוֹס; retreat: fleeing, flight.
from נִיר; a yoke (properly, for plowing), i.e. the frame of a loom: beam.
or mnorah; feminine of מָנוֹר (in the original sense of נֵר); a chandelier: candlestick.
from נָזַר; a prince: crowned.

from an unused root meaning to apportion, i.e. bestow; a donation; euphemistically, tribute; specifically a sacrificial offering (usually bloodless and voluntary): gift, oblation, (meat) offering, present, sacrifice.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִנְחָה; a sacrificial offering: oblation, meat offering.
from נָחַם; comforter; Menachem, an Israelite: Menahem.
from נ֫וּחַ; rest; Manachath, the name of an Edomite and of a place in Moab: Manahath.
from מָנָא; the Apportioner, i.e. Fate (as an idol): number.
of foreign derivation; Minni, an Armenian province: Minni.
from מִן and יָמִין; from (the) right hand; Minjamin, the name of two Israelites: Miniamin. Compare מִיָּמִין.
(Aramaic) from מְנָא; enumeration: number.
from the same as מִנִּים; enumeration; Minnith, a place East of the Jordan: Minnith.
from נָלָה; completion, i.e. (in produce) wealth: perfection.
a primitive root; to debar (negatively or positively) from benefit or injury: deny, keep (back), refrain, restrain, withhold.
or maniul; from נָעַל; a bolt: lock.
from נָעַל; a bolt: shoe.
from נָעֵם; a delicacy: dainty.
from נ֫וּעַ; a sistrum (so called from its rattling sound): cornet.
from נָקָה; a sacrificial basin (for holding blood): bowl.
from נָשָׁה; causing to forget; Menashsheh, a grandson of Jacob, also the tribe descended from him, and its territory: Manasseh.
from מְנַשֶּׁה; a Menashshite or descendant of Menashsheh: of Manasseh, Manassites.
from מָנָא; an allotment (by courtesy, law or providence): portion.
or mic; from מָסַס; properly, a burden (as causing to faint), i.e. a tax in the form of forced labor: discomfited, levy, task(-master), tribute(-tary).
from מָסַס; fainting, i.e. (figuratively) disconsolate: is afflicted.
plural masculine mcibbiym; or feminine mcibbowth; from סָבַב; a divan (as enclosing the room); abstractly (adverbial) around: that compass about, (place) round about, at table.
from סָגַר; a fastener, i.e. (of a person) a smith, (of a thing) a prison: prison, smith.
from סָגַר; something enclosing, i.e. a margin (of a region, of a panel); concretely, a stronghold: border, close place, hole.
from יָסַד; a foundation: foundation.
from the same as סְדָרִים; a colonnade or internal portico (from its rows of pillars): porch.
a primitive root; to dissolve: make to consume away, (make to) melt, water.
from מָסַס (in the sense of flowing); abundance, i.e. (adverbially) liberally: tribute.
from נָסָה; a testing, of men (judicial) or of God (querulous): temptation, trial.
the same as מַסָּה; Massah, a place in the Desert: Massah.
apparently from an unused root meaning to cover; a veil: vail.
for מְשׂוּכָה; a hedge: thorn hedge.
from נָסַח in the sense of staving off; a cordon, (adverbially) or (as a) military barrier: broken down.
from סָחַר; trade: traffic.
a primitive root; to mix, especially wine (with spices): mingle.
from מָסַך; a mixture, i.e. of wine with spices: mixture.
from סָכַך; a cover, i.e. veil: covering, curtain, hanging.
from סָכַך; a covering, i.e. garniture: covering.

from נָסַך; properly, a pouring over, i.e. fusion of metal (especially a cast image); by implication, a libation, i.e. league; concretely a coverlet (as if poured out): covering, molten (image), vail.
from סִכְלוּת; indigent: poor (man).
by transp. from כָּנַס; a magazine: store(-house), treasure.
from מִסְכֵּן; indigence: scarceness.
from נָסַך in the sense of spreading out; something expanded, i.e. the warp in a loom (as stretched out to receive the woof): web.
from סָלַל; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked), literally or figuratively; specifically a viaduct, a staircase: causeway, course, highway, path, terrace.
from סָלַל; a thoroughfare (as turnpiked): highway.
or micmer; also (feminine) macmrah; or micmrah; or even masmrah (Eccles. 12:11); from סָמַר; a peg (as bristling from the surface): nail.
a primitive root; to liquefy; figuratively, to waste (with disease), to faint (with fatigue, fear or grief): discourage, faint, be loosed, melt (away), refuse, X utterly.
from נָסַע; a departure (from striking the tents), i.e. march (not necessarily a single day's travel); by implication, a station (or point of departure): journey(-ing).
from נָסַע in the sense of projecting; a missile (spear or arrow); also a quarry (whence stones are, as it were, ejected): before it was brought, dart.
' from סָעַד; a balustrade (for stairs): pillar.
from סָפַד; a lamentation: lamentation, one mourneth, mourning, wailing.
from an unused root meaning to collect; fodder: provender.
from סָפַח; a veil (as spread out): kerchief.
from סָפַח; scruf (as spreading over the surface): scab.

from סָפַר; a number, definite (arithmetical) or indefinite (large, innumerable; small, a few); also (abstractly) narration: + abundance, account, X all, X few, (in-)finite, (certain) number(-ed), tale, telling, + time.
the same as מֶלְקָחַ֫יִם; number; Mispar, an Israelite: Mizpar. Compare מִסְפֶּ֫רֶת.
feminine of מַלְכוּ; enumeration; Mispereth, an Israelite: Mispereth. Compare מֶלְתָּחָה.
a primitive root; to sunder, i.e. (transitively) set apart, or (reflex.) apostatize: commit, deliver.
from יָסַר; admonition: instruction.
from אָסַר; a band: bond.
from סָתַר; a refuge: covert.
from סָתַר; properly, a hider, i.e. (abstractly) a hiding, i.e. aversion: hid.
from סָתַר; properly, a concealer, i.e. a covert: secret(-ly, place).
from עָבַד; an act: work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מַעְבָּדִים; an act: work.
from עָבָה; properly, compact (part of soil), i.e. loam: clay.
or feminine mapabarah; from עָבַר; a crossing-place (of a river, a ford; of a mountain, a pass); abstractly, a transit, i.e. (figuratively) overwhelming: ford, place where...pass, passage.
or feminine mapgalah; from the same as עָגֹל; a track (literally or figuratively); also a rampart (as circular): going, path, trench, way((-side)).
a primitive root; to waver: make to shake, slide, slip.
from עָדָה; ornamental; Maadai, an Israelite: Maadai.
from עָדָה and יָהּ; ornament of Jah; Maadjah, an Israelite: Maadiah. Compare מוֹעַדְיָה.
or (feminine) maadannah; from עָדַן; a delicacy or (abstractly) pleasure (adverbially, cheerfully): dainty, delicately, delight.
by transitive from עָנַד; a bond, i.e. group: influence.
from עָדַר; a (weeding) hoe: mattock.
(Aramaic) or m(ae (Aramaic); corresponding to מְעֵי; only in plural the bowels: belly.

from an unused root probably meaning to be soft; used only in plural the intestines, or (collectively) the abdomen, figuratively, sympathy; by implication, a vest; by extens. the stomach, the uterus (or of men, the seat of generation), the heart (figuratively): belly, bowels, X heart, womb.
feminine of מְעֵי; the belly, i.e. (figuratively) interior: gravel.
from עוּג; a cake of bread (with לַעֲגֵי a table- buffoon, i.e. parasite): cake, feast.
(also mauwz); or mahoz (also ma,uz; from עָזַז; a fortified place; figuratively, a defence: force, fort(-ress), rock, strength(-en), (X most) strong (hold).
from מָעַך; oppressed; Maok, a Philistine: Maoch.

or maiyn (1 Chronicles 4:41); from the same as עֹנַת; an abode, of God (the Tabernacle or the Temple), men (their home) or animals (their lair); hence, a retreat (asylum): den, dwelling((-)place), habitation.
the same as מָעוֹן; a residence; Maon, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine: Maon, Maonites. Compare בֵּית בַּ֫עַל מְעוֹן, מְעוּנִים.
or msonah; feminine of מָעוֹן, and meaning the same: den, habitation, (dwelling) place, refuge.
or Msiyniy; probably patrial from מָעוֹן; a Meunite, or inhabitant of Maon (only in plural): Mehunim(-s), Meunim.
plural of מְעוֹנַת; habitative; Meonothai, an Israelite: Meonothai.
from עוּף in the sense of covering with shade (compare מוּעָף); darkness: dimness.
from עוּר; nakedness, i.e. (in plural) the pudenda: nakedness.
or Ma.azyahuw; probably from עוּז (in the sense of protection) and יָהּ; rescue of Jah; Maazjah, the name of two Israelites: Maaziah.

a primitive root; properly, to pare off, i.e. lessen; intransitively, to be (or causatively, to make) small or few (or figuratively, ineffective): suffer to decrease, diminish, (be, X borrow a, give, make) few (in number, -ness), gather least (little), be (seem) little, (X give the) less, be minished, bring to nothing.
or miat; from מָעַט; a little or few (often adverbial or compar.): almost (some, very) few(-er, -est), lightly, little (while), (very) small (matter, thing), some, soon, X very.
passive adjective of מָעַט; thinned (as to the edge), i.e. sharp: wrapped up.
from עָטָה; a vestment: garment.
from עָטַף; a cloak: mantle.
from עָוָה; a pile of rubbish (as contorted), i.e. a ruin (compare עִי): heap.
probably from מְעֵי; sympathetic; Maai, an Israelite: Maai.
from מָעַל in the sense of covering; a robe (i.e. upper and outer garment): cloke, coat, mantle, robe.

or ma ynow (Psa. 114:8); or (feminine) ma yanah; from עַ֫יִן (as a denominative in the sense of a spring); a fountain (also collectively), figuratively, a source (of satisfaction): fountain, spring, well.
a primitive root; to press, i.e. to pierce, emasculate, handle: bruised, stuck, be pressed.

or Mamakath (Josh. 13:13); from מָעַך; depression; Maakah (or Maakath), the name of a place in Syria, also of a Mesopotamian, of three Israelites, and of four Israelitesses and one Syrian woman: Maachah, Maachathites. See also בֵּית מַעֲכָה.
patrial from מַעֲכָה; a Maakathite, or inhabitant of Maakah: Maachathite.
a primitive root; properly, to cover up; used only figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. treacherously: transgress, (commit, do a) trespass(-ing).
from מָעַל; treachery, i.e. sin: falsehood, grievously, sore, transgression, trespass, X very.
from עָלָה; properly, the upper part, used only adverbially with prefix upward, above, overhead, from the top, etc.above, exceeding(-ly), forward, on (X very) high, over, up(-on, -ward), very.
(Aramaic) from עֲלַל; (only in plural as singular) the setting (of the sun): going down.
from עָלָה; a raising (of the hands): lifting up.

from עָלָה; an elevation, i.e. (concretely) acclivity or platform; abstractly (the relation or state) a rise or (figuratively) priority: ascent, before, chiefest, cliff, that goeth up, going up, hill, mounting up, stairs.

feminine of מַעֲלֶה; elevation, i.e. the act (literally, a journey to a higher place, figuratively, a thought arising), or (concretely) the condition (literally, a step or grade-mark, figuratively, a superiority of station); specifically a climactic progression (in certain Psalms): things that come up, (high) degree, deal, go up, stair, step, story.
from מַעֲלֶה and (the plural of) עַקְרָב; Steep of Scorpions, a place in the Desert: Maaleh- accrabim, the ascent (going up) of Akrabbim.
from עָלַל; an act (good or bad): doing, endeavour, invention, work.
from עָמַד; (figuratively) a position: attendance, office, place, state.
from עָמַד; literally, a foothold: standing.
from עָמַס; burdensomeness: burdensome.
from עָמַק; a deep: deep, depth.

from עָנָה; properly, heed, i.e. purpose; used only adverbially, on account of (as a motive or an aim), teleologically, in order that: because of, to the end (intent) that, for (to,... 's sake), + lest, that, to.
from עָנָה; a reply (favorable or contradictory): answer, X himself.
from עָנָה, in the sense of depression or tilling; a furrow: + acre, furrow.
from עָצָה; closure; Maats, an Israelite: Maaz.
from עָצַב; anguish: sorrow.
from an usused root meaning to hew; an axe: ax, tongs.
from עָצַר; objectively, a hindrance: restraint.
from עָצַר; subjectively, control: rule.
from an unused root meaning to repress; a parapet: battlement.
from עָקַשׁ; a crook (in a road): crooked thing.
from עָרָה; a nude place, i.e. (literally) the pudenda, or (figuratively) a vacant space: nakedness, proportion.
from עָרַב, in the sense of trading; traffic; by implication, mercantile goods: market, merchandise.
or (feminine) maearabah; from עָרַב, in the sense of shading; the west (as a region of the evening sun): west.
from עָרָה; a nude place, i.e. a common: meadows.
feminine of מַעֲרֵה; an open spot: army (from the margin).
from עוּר; a cavern (as dark): cave, den, hole.
the same as מְעָרָה; cave; Mearah, a place in PalestineMearah.
from עָרַך; an arrangement, i.e. (figuratively) mental disposition: preparation.
feminine of מַעַרְכֵי; an arrangement; concretely, a pile; specifically a military array: army, fight, be set in order, ordered place, rank, row.
from עָרַך; an arrangement, i.e. (concretely) a pile (of loaves): row, shewbread.
from עָרֹם, in the sense of stripping; bare: naked.
from עָרַץ; violence: terror.
a form of מַעֲרוֹת; waste; Maarath, a place in Palestine: Maarath.

from עָשָׂה; an action (good or bad); generally, a transaction; abstractly, activity; by implication, a product (specifically, a poem) or (generally) property: act, art, + bakemeat, business, deed, do(-ing), labor, thing made, ware of making, occupation, thing offered, operation, possession, X well, ((handy-, needle-, net-))work(ing, - manship), wrought.
from עָשָׂה; operative; Maasai, an Israelite: Maasiai.
or Maaseyahuw; from מַעֲשֶׂה and יָהּ; work of Jah; Maasejah, the name of sixteen Israelites: Maaseiah.
from עָשַׁק; oppression: oppression, X oppressor.
or maasar; and (in plural) feminine maasrah; from עָשָׂר; a tenth; especially a tithetenth (part), tithe(-ing).
of Egyptian origin: Moph, the capital of Lower EgyptMemphis. Compare נֹף.
from פָּגַע; an object of attack: mark.
from נָפַח; a breathing out (of life), i.e. expiring: giving up.
from נָפַח; the bellows (i.e. blower) of a forge: bellows.
or Mphibosheth; probably from פָּאָה and בֹּ֫שֶׁת; dispeller of shame (i.e. of Baal); Mephibosheth, the name of two Israelites: Mephibosheth.
a plural apparently from נוּף; wavings; Muppim, an Israelite: Muppim. Compare שֻׁפִּים.
from פּוּץ; a breaker, i.e. mallet: maul.
from נָפַל; a falling off, i.e. chaff; also something pendulous, i.e. a flap: flake, refuse.
from פָּלָא; a miracle: wondrous work.
from פָּלַג; a classification: division.
or mappelah; from נָפַל; something fallen, i.e. a ruin: ruin(-ous).
from פָּלַט; an escape: escape.
from פָּלַץ; a terror, i.e. an idol: idol.
from an unused root meaning to balance; a poising: balancing.
from נָפַל; fall, i.e. decadence; concretely, a ruin; specifically a carcase: carcase, fall, ruin.
or (feminine) miph.alah; from פָּעַל; a performance: work.
from נָפַץ; a smiting to pieces: slaughter.
from נָפַץ; a smiter, i.e. a war club: battle ax.
from פָּקַד; an appointment, i.e. mandate; concretely, a designated spot; specifically, a census: appointed place, commandment, number.
the same as מִפְקָד; assignment; Miphkad, the name of a gate in Jerusalem: Miphkad.
from פָּרַץ; a break (in the shore), i.e. a haven: breach.
from פָּרַק; properly, a fracture, i.e. joint (vertebrae) of the neck: neck.
from פָּרַשׂ; an expansion: that which...spreadest forth, spreading.
from פָּשַׂע; a stride, i.e. (by euphemism) the crotch: buttocks.
from פָּתַח; an opener, i.e. a key: key.
from פָּתַח; an aperture, i.e. (figuratively) utterance: opening.
from the same as פָּ֫תֶן; a stretcher, i.e. a sill: threshold.
or mowts (Zephaniah 2:2); from מִיץ; chaff (as pressed out, i.e. winnowed or (rather) threshed loose): chaff.

a primitive root; properly, to come forth to, i.e. appear or exist; transitively, to attain, i.e. find or acquire; figuratively, to occur, meet or be present: + be able, befall, being, catch, X certainly, (cause to) come (on, to, to hand), deliver, be enough (cause to) find(-ing, occasion, out), get (hold upon), X have (here), be here, hit, be left, light (up-)on, meet (with), X occasion serve, (be) present, ready, speed, suffice, take hold on.
from נָצַב; a fixed spot; figuratively, an office, a military post: garrison, station, place where...stood.
from נָצַב; a station, i.e. military post: mount.
or mitstsabah; feminine of מַצָּב; a military guard: army, garrison.
feminine (causatively) participle of נָצַב; something stationed, i.e. a column or (memorial stone); by analogy, an idol: garrison, (standing) image, pillar.
apparently from מָצָא and יָהּ; found of Jah; Metsobajah, a place in Palestine: Mesobaite.
from נָצַב; something stationary, i.e. a monumental stone; also the stock of a tree: pillar, substance.
or mtsad; or (feminine) mtsadah; from צוּד; a fastness (as a covert of ambush): castle, fort, (strong) hold, munition.
a primitive root; to suck out; by implication, to drain, to squeeze out: suck, wring (out).
active participle feminine of מָצָה; drained; Motsah, a place in Palestine: Mozah.

from מָצַץ in the sense of greedily devouring for sweetness; properly, sweetness; concretely, sweet (i.e. not soured or bittered with yeast); specifically, an unfermented cake or loaf, or (elliptically) the festival of Passover (because no leaven was then used): unleaved (bread, cake), without leaven.
from נָצָה; a quarrel: contention, debate, strife.
from צָהַל; a whinnying (through impatience for battle or lust): neighing.
or (feminine) mtsowdah; or mtsodah; from צוּד; a net (for capturing animals or fishes): also (by interchange for mtsad) a fastness or (beseiging) tower:--bulwark, hold, munition, net, snare.
or (feminine) mtsuwdah; or mtsudah; for מְצוֹד; a net, or (abstractly) capture; also a fastness; --castle, defense, fort(-ress), (strong) hold, be hunted, net, snare, strong place.
from צָוָה; a command, whether human or divine (collectively, the Law): (which was) commanded(-ment), law, ordinance, precept.
or mtsolah; also mtsuwlah; or mtsulah; from the same as צוּלָה; a deep place (of water or mud): bottom, deep, depth.
from צוּק; a narrow place, i.e. (abstractly and figuratively) confinement or disability: anguish, distress, straitness.
or matsuq; from צוּק; something narrow, i.e. a column or hilltop: pillar, situate.
or mtsuqah; feminine of מָצוּק; narrowness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble: anguish, distress.

or matsuwr; from צוּר; something hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of besiegers), (abstractly) a siege, (figuratively) distress; or (subjectively) a fastness: besieged, bulwark, defence, fenced, fortress, siege, strong (hold), tower.
the same as מָצוֹר in the sense of a limit; Egypt (as the border of Palestine): besieged places, defense, fortified.

or mtsurah; feminine of מָצוֹר; a hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of siege), or (subjectively) a rampart (of protection), (abstractly) fortification: fenced (city, fort, munition, strong hold.
from נָצָה; a quarrel: that contended.
from an unused root meaning to be clear, i.e. conspicuous; the forehead (as open and prominent): brow, forehead, + impudent.
from the same as מֵ֫צַח; a shin-piece of armor (as prominent), only plural: greaves.
from צָלַל; a tinkler, i.e. a bell: bell.
from צָלַל; shade: bottom.
from צָלַל; (only dual) double tinklers, i.e. cymbals: cymbals.
from צָנַף; a tiara, i.e. official turban (of a king or high priest): diadem, mitre.
from יָצַע; a couch: bed.
from צָעַד; a step; figuratively, companionship: going, step.
feminine of מִצְעָר; properly, littleness; concretely, diminutive: little.
from צָעַר; petty (in size or number); adverbially, a short (time): little one (while), small.
the same as מִצְעָר; Mitsar, a peak of Lebanon: Mizar.
from צָפָה; an observatory, especially for military purposes: watch tower.
the same as מִצְפֶּה; Mitspeh, the name of five places in Palestine: Mizpeh, watch tower. Compare מִצְפָּה.
feminine of מִצְפֶּה; Mitspah, the name of two places in Palestine: Mitspah. (This seems rather to be only an orthographic variation of מִצְפֶּה when "in pause".)
from צָפַן; a secret (place or thing, perhaps, treasure): hidden thing.
a primitive root; to suck: milk.
from קֵבָה; something tight, i.e. (figuratively) trouble: distress, pain, strait.
from מִצְרָ֫יִם; a Mitsrite, or inhabitant of Mitsrajim: Egyptian, of Egypt.
dual of מָצוֹר; Mitsrajim, i.e. Upper and Lower Egypt: Egypt, Egyptians, Mizraim.
from צָרַף; a crucible: fining pot.
from מָקַק; properly, a melting, i.e. putridityrottenness, stink.
from נָקַב; properly, a perforatrix, i.e. a hammer (as piercing): hammer.
from נָקַב; properly, a perforator, i.e. a hammer (as piercing); also (intransitively) a perforation, i.e. a quarry: hammer, hole.
from the same as נָקֹד in the denominative sense of herding (compare נֹקֵד); fold; Makkedah, a place in PalestineMakkedah.
or miqqdash (Exod. 15:17); from קָדַשׁ; a consecrated thing or place, especially, a palace, sanctuary (whether of Jehovah or of idols) or asylum: chapel, hallowed part, holy place, sanctuary.
or (feminine) maqhelah; from קָהַל; an assembly: congregation.
plural of מַקְהֵלִים (feminine); assemblies; Makheloth, a place in the Desert: Makheloth.

or miqveh (1 Kings 10:28); or miqvet (2 Chron. 1:16); from קָוָה; something waited for, i.e. confidence (objective or subjective); also a collection, i.e. (of water) a pond, or (of men and horses) a caravan or drove: abiding, gathering together, hope, linen yarn, plenty (of water), pool.
feminine of מִקְוֶה; a collection, i.e. (of water) a reservoir: ditch.

or maqom; also (feminine) mqowmah; or mqomah; from קוּם; properly, a standing, i.e. a spot; but used widely of a locality (general or specific); also (figuratively) of a condition (of body or mind): country, X home, X open, place, room, space, X whither(-soever).

or maqor; from קוּר; properly, something dug, i.e. a (general) source (of water, even when naturally flowing; also of tears, blood (by euphemism, of the female pudenda); figuratively, of happiness, wisdom, progeny): fountain, issue, spring, well(-spring).
from לָקַח; reception: taking.
from לָקַח; something received, i.e. merchandise (purchased): ware.
from קָטַר; something to fume (incense) on i.e. a hearth place: to burn...upon.
feminine of מִקְטַר; something to fume (incense) in, i.e. a coal-pan: censer.
: ; or (feminine) maqqlah; from an unused root meaning apparently to germinate; a shoot, i.e. stick (with leaves on, or for walking, striking, guiding, divining): rod, ((hand-))staff.
(or perhaps mik-kel-ohth') plural of (feminine) מַקֵּל; rods; Mikloth, a place in the Desert: Mikloth.
from קָלַט in the sense of taking in; an asylum (as a receptacle): refuge.
from קָלַע; a sculpture (probably in bas-relief): carved (figure), carving, graving.
from קָנָה; something bought, i.e. property, but only livestock; abstractly, acquisition: cattle, flock, herd, possession, purchase, substance.
feminine of מִקְנֶה; properly, a buying, i.e. acquisition; concretely, a piece of property (land or living); also the sum paid: (he that is) bought, possession, piece, purchase.
from מִקְנֶה and יָהּ; possession of Jah; Miknejah, an Israelite: Mikneiah.
from קָסַם; an augury: divination.
from קָצַץ; end; Makats, a place in Palestine: Makaz.
or maqtsoa; or (feminine) maqtso-ah; from קָצַע in the denominative sense of bending; an angle or recess: corner, turning.
from קָצַע; a scraper, i.e. a carving chisel: plane.
from קָצַע in the denominative sense of bending; an angle: corner.
' a primitive root; to melt; figuratively, to flow, dwindle, vanish: consume away, be corrupt, dissolve, pine away.
from קָרָא; something called out, i.e. a public meeting (the act, the persons, or the place); also a rehearsal: assembly, calling, convocation, reading.
from קָרָה; something met with, i.e. an accident or fortune: something befallen, befalleth, chance, event, hap(-peneth).
from קָרָה; properly, something meeting, i.e. a frame (of timbers): building.
from the same as קַר; a cooling off: X summer.
from קָשָׁה in the sense of knotting up round and hard; something turned (rounded), i.e. a curl (of tresses): X well (set) hair.
feminine of מִקְשֶׁה; rounded work, i.e. moulded by hammering (repousse): beaten (out of one piece, work), upright, whole piece.
denominative from קִשֻּׁאּים; literally, a cucumbered field, i.e. a cucumber patch: garden of cucumbers.
or (feminine) marah; from מָרַר; bitter (literally or figuratively); also (as noun) bitterness, or (adverbially) bitterly: + angry, bitter(-ly, -ness), chafed, discontented, X great, heavy.
from מָרַר in its original sense of distillation; a drop: drop.
or mowr; from מָרַר; myrrh (as distilling in drops, and also as bitter): myrrh.
a primitive root; to rebel; hence (through the idea of maltreating) to whip, i.e. lash (self with wings, as the ostrich in running): be filthy, lift up self.
for מָר feminine; bitter; Mara, a symbolic name of Naomi: Mara.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to מָרָא in the sense of domineering; a master: lord, Lord.
of foreign derivation; Merodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king: Merodach-baladan. Compare מְרֹדָך.

from רָאָה; a view (the act of seeing); also an appearance (the thing seen), whether (real) a shape (especially if handsome, comeliness; often plural the looks), or (mental) a vision: X apparently, appearance(-reth), X as soon as beautiful(-ly), countenance, fair, favoured, form, goodly, to look (up) on (to), look(-eth), pattern, to see, seem, sight, visage, vision.
feminine of מַרְאֶה; a vision; also (causatively) a mirror: looking glass, vision.
apparently feminine passive causative participle of רָאָה; something conspicuous, i.e. the craw of a bird (from its prominence): crop.
denominative from רֹאשׁ; properly, headship, i.e. (plural for collective) dominion: principality.
or Mareshah; formed like מַרְאֲשׁוֹת; summit; Mareshah, the name of two Israelites and of a place in Palestine: Mareshah.
formed like מַרְאֲשׁוֹת; properly, a headpiece, i.e. (plural for adverbial) at (or as) the head-rest (or pillow): bolster, head, pillow. Compare מַרְגְּלֹת.
from רָבַב; increase; Merab, a daughter of Saul: Merab.
from רָבַד; a coverlet: covering of tapestry.
from רָבָה; properly, increasing; as noun, greatness, or (adverbially) greatly: great, increase.
from רָבָה; abundance, i.e. a great quantity: much.
from רָבָה; a multitude; also offspring; specifically interest (on capital): greatest part, greatness, increase, multitude.
from רָבַץ; a reclining place, i.e. fold (for flocks): couching place, place to lie down.
from an unused root meaning to tie up; a stall (for cattle): X fat(-ted), stall.
from רָגַע; a resting place: rest.
denominative from רָ֫גֶל; (plural for collective) a footpiece, i.e. (adverbially) at the foot, or (direct.) the foot itself: feet. Compare מְרַאֲשׁוֹת.
from רָגַם; a stone-heap: sling.
from רָגַע; rest: refreshing.
a primitive root; to rebel: rebel(-lious).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to מָרַד; rebellion: rebellion.
from מָרַד; rebellion: rebellion.
the same as מֶ֫רֶד; Mered, an Israelite: Mered.
(Aramaic) from the same as מְרַד; rebellious: rebellious.
from מָרַד; rebelliousness: X rebellious.
of foreign derivation; Merodak, a Babylonian idol: Merodach. Compare מְרֹאדַךְ בַּלְאָדָן.
of foreign derivation; Mordecai, an Israelite: Mordecai.
from רָדַף; persecuted: persecuted.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bitter (or unpleasant); (figuratively) to rebel (or resist; causatively, to provoke): bitter, change, be disobedient, disobey, grievously, provocation, provoke(-ing), (be) rebel (against, -lious).
the same as מָר feminine; bitter; Marah, a place in the Desert: Marah.
from מָרַר; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble: grief.
a form of מֹרַת; trouble: bitterness.
from רוּד in the sense of maltreatment; an outcast; (abstractly) destitution: cast out, misery.
of uncertain derivation; Meroz, a place in Palestine: Meroz.
from מָרַח; bruised, i.e. emasculated: broken.

from רוּם; altitude, i.e. concretely (an elevated place), abstractly (elevation, figuratively (elation), or adverbially (aloft): (far) above, dignity, haughty, height, (most, on) high (one, place), loftily, upward.
formed like מָרוֹם; height; Merom, a lake in Palestine: Merom.
from רוּץ; a run (the trial of speed): race.
or mrutsah; feminine of מֵרוֹץ; a race (the act), whether the manner or the progress: course, running. Compare מְרֻצָה.
from מָרַק; properly, rubbed; but used abstractly, a rubbing (with perfumery): purification.
plural of מָר feminine; bitter springs; Maroth, a place in Palestine: Maroth.
from an unused root meaning to scream; a cry, i.e. (of job), a revel: banquet.
formed like מִרְזַח; a cry, i.e. (of grief) a lamentation: mourning.
a primitive root; properly, to soften by rubbing or pressure; hence (medicinally) to apply as an emollient: lay for a plaister.
from רָחַב; enlargement, either literally (an open space, usually in a good sense), or figuratively (liberty): breadth, large place (room).
:  : from רָחַק; remoteness, i.e. (concretely) a distant place; often (adverbially) from afar: (a-, dwell in, very) far (country, off). See also בֵּית הַמֶּרְחָק.
from רָחַשׁ; a stew-pan: fryingpan.
a primitive root; to polish; by implication, to make bald (the head), to gall (the shoulder); also, to sharpen: bright, furbish, (have his) hair (be) fallen off, peeled, pluck off (hair).
(Aramaic) corresponding to מָרַט; to pull off: be plucked.
from מָרָה; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) rebellion; concretely, bitter, or rebellious: bitter, (most) rebel(-lion, -lious).
from מָרָא in the sense of grossness, through the idea of domineering (compare מָרֵא); stall-fed; often (as noun) a beeve: fat (fed) beast (cattle, -ling).
from רִיב and בַּ֫עַל; quarreller of Baal, Merib-Baal, an epithet of Gideon: Merib-baal. Compare מְרִי בַּ֫עַל.
from רִיב; quarrel: provocation, strife.
the same as מְרִיבָה; Meribah, the name of two places in the Desert: Meribah.
from מֶ֫רִי and בַּ֫עַל; rebellion of (i.e. against) Baal; Meri-Baal, an epithet of Gideon: Meri-baal. Compare מְרִיב בַּ֫עַל.
from מָרָה; rebellion; Merajah, an Israelite: Meraiah. Compare יִמְרָה.
plural of מְרָיָה; rebellious; Merajoth, the name of two Israelites: Meraioth.
from מֶ֫רִי; rebelliously; Mirjam, the name of two Israelitesses: Miriam.
from מָרַר; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) grief: bitterness.
from מָרַר; bitter, i.e. poisonous: bitter.
perhaps from רָכַך; softness, i.e. (figuratively) fear: faintness.
from רָכַב; a chariot; also a seat (in a vehicle): chariot, covering, saddle.
feminine of מֶרְכָּב; a chariot: chariot. See also בֵּית מַרְכָּבוֹת.
from רָכַל; a mart: merchandise.
from רָמָה in the sense of deceiving; fraud: craft, deceit(-ful, -fully), false, feigned, guile, subtilly, treachery.
the same as מִרְמָה; Mirmah, an Israelite: Mirma.
plural from רוּם; heights; Meremoth, the name of two Israelites: Meremoth.
from רָמַס; abasement (the act or the thing): tread (down)-ing, (to be) trodden (down) under foot.
patrial from an unused noun; a Meronothite, or inhabitant of some (otherwise unknown) Meronoth.: Meronothite.
of foreign derivation; Meres, a Persian: Meres.
of foreign derivation; Marsena, a Persian: Marsena.
from רָעַע; used as (abstract) noun, wickedness: do mischief.
from רָעָה in the sense of companionship; a friend: companion, friend.
from רָעָה in the sense of feeding; pasture (the place or the act); also the haunt of wild animals: feeding place, pasture.
from רָעָה in the sense of feeding; pasturage; concretely, a flock: flock, pasture.
from רָעַל; perhaps, earthquake; Maralah, a place in Palestine: Maralah.

from רָפָא; properly, curative, i.e. literally (concretely) a medicine, or (abstractly) a cure; figuratively (concretely) deliverance, or (abstractly) placidity: ((in-))cure(-able), healing(-lth), remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding.
from רָפַשׂ; muddled water: that which...have fouled.
a primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to be pungent or vehement; to irritate: embolden, be forcible, grievous, sore.
from רָצַץ; oppression: violence. See also מְרוּצָה.
from רָצַע; an awl: aul.
from רָצַף; a pavement: pavement.
a primitive root; to polish; by implication, to sharpen; also to rinse: bright, furbish, scour.
from מָרַק; soup (as if a rinsing): broth. See also פְּרַק.
from רָקַח; a spicy herb: X sweet.
feminine of מֶרְקָחִים; abstractly, a seasoning (with spicery); concretely, an unguent-kettle (for preparing spiced oil): pot of ointment, X well.
from רָקַח; an aromatic unguent; also an unguent-pot: prepared by the apothecaries' art, compound, ointment.

a primitive root; properly, to trickle (see מַר); but used only as a denominative from מָר; to be (causatively, make) bitter (literally or figuratively): (be, be in, deal, have, make) bitter(-ly, - ness), be moved with choler, (be, have sorely, it) grieved(-eth), provoke, vex.
or mrowr; from מָרַר; a bitter herbbitter(-ness).
from מָרַר; bile (from its bitterness): gall.
or mrowrah; from מָרַר; properly, bitterness; concretely, a bitter thing; specifically bile; also venom (of a serpent): bitter (thing), gall.
from מָרַר; bitter; Merari, an Israelite: Merari. See also מְרָרִי.
from מְרָרִי; a Merarite (collectively), or decendants of Merari: Merarites.
from רָשַׁע; a female wicked doer: wicked woman.
dual of מָר feminine; double bitterness; Merathajim, an epithet of Babylon: Merathaim.
of foreign derivation; Mash, a son of Aram, and the people descended from him: Mash.
of foreign derivation; Mesha, a place in Arabia: Mesha.

from נָשָׂא; a burden; specifically, tribute, or (abstractly) porterage; figuratively, an utterance, chiefly a doom, especially singing; mental, desire: burden, carry away, prophecy, X they set, song, tribute.
the same as מַשָּׂא; burden; Massa, a son of Ishmael: Massa.
from נָשָׁה; a loan; by implication, interest on a debt: exaction, usury.
from נָשָׂא; partiality (as a lifting up): respect.
from שָׁאַב; a trough for cattle to drink from: place of drawing water.
from נָשָׂא; a conflagration (from the rising of smoke): burden.
feminine of מַשָּׁא; a loan: X any(- thing), debt.
from נָשָׁא; dissimulation: deceit.
from שָׁאַל; request; Mishal, a place in Palestine: Mishal, Misheal. Compare מָשָׁל.
from שָׁאַל; a request: desire, petition.
from שָׁאַר in the original sense of swelling; a kneading-trough (in which the dough rises): kneading trough, store.

from נָשָׂא; properly, (abstractly) a raising (as of the hands in prayer), or rising (of flame); figuratively, an utterance; concretely, a beacon (as raised); a present (as taken), mess, or tribute; figuratively, a reproach (as a burden): burden, collection, sign of fire, (great) flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation, reward.
from שָׁבַץ; a brocade; by analogy, a (reticulated) setting of a gem: ouch, wrought.
from שָׁבַר; the orifice of the womb (from which the fetus breaks forth): birth, breaking forth.
from שָׁבַר; a breaker (of the sea): billow, wave.
from שָׁבַת; cessation, i.e. destruction: sabbath.
from שָׂגַב; properly, a cliff (or other lofty or inaccessible place); abstractly, altitude; figuratively, a refugedefence, high fort (tower), refuge, Misgab, a place in Moab:--Misgab.
from שָׁגָה; an error: oversight.
a primitive root; to pull out (literally or figuratively): draw(out).
from מָשָׁה; drawing out (of the water), i.e. rescued; Mosheh, the Israelite lawgiver: Moses.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מֹשֶׁה: Moses.
from נָשָׁה; a debt: + creditor.
or mshoah; from the same as שׁוֹאָה; (a) ruin, abstractly (the act) or concretely (the wreck): desolation, waste.
or mashshu ah; for מְשֹׁאָה; ruin: desolation, destruction.
from שׁוּב; returned; Meshobab, an Israelite: Meshobab.
or mshubah; from שׁוּב; apostasy: backsliding, turning away.
from an unused root meaning to stray; mistake: error.
or mishshowt; from שׁוּט; an oar: oar.
or msukah; from שׂוּך; a hedge: hedge.
from an unused root meaning to plunder; spoilation: spoil.
from an unused root meaning to rasp; a saw: saw.
from an unused root meaning apparently to divide; a measure (for liquids): measure.
from שׂוּשׂ; delight, concretely (the cause or object) or abstractly (the feeling): joy, mirth, rejoice.
a primitive root; to rub with oil, i.e. to anoint; by implication, to consecrate; also to paint: anoint, paint.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to מָשַׁח; oil: oil.
or moshchah; from מָשַׁח; unction (the act); by implication, a consecratory gift: (to be) anointed(-ing), ointment.
from שָׁחַת; destructive, i.e. (as noun) destruction, literally (specifically a snare) or figuratively (corruption): corruption, (to) destroy(-ing), destruction, trap, X utterly.
from שַׁחֲצוֹם; a laughing-stock: scorn.
from שָׁחַר in the sense of day breaking; dawn: morning.
for מַשְׁחִית; destruction: destroying.
or moshchath; from שָׁחַת; disfigurement: corruption, marred.
or mishtach; from שָׁטַח; a spreading-place: (to) spread (forth, -ing, upon).
from the same as שֹׁטֵט; enmity: hatred.
from שֹׁטֵר; jurisdiction: dominion.
from מָשָׁה; silk (as drawn from the cocoon): silk.
from an equiv. to שְׁזַב and אֵל; delivered of God; Meshezabel, an Israelite: Meshezabeel.
from מָשַׁח; anointed; usually a consecrated person (as a king, priest, or saint); specifically, the Messiah: anointed, Messiah.

a primitive root; to draw, used in a great variety of applications (including to sow, to sound, to prolong, to develop, to march, to remove, to delay, to be tall, etc.): draw (along, out), continue, defer, extend, forbear, X give, handle, make (pro-, sound)long, X sow, scatter, stretch out.
from מָשַׁך; a sowing; also a possession: precious, price.
the same in form as מֶ֫שֶׁך, but probably of foreign derivation; Meshek, a son of Japheth, and the people descended from him: Mesech, Meshech.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִשְׁכָּב; a bed: bed.
from שָׁכַב; a bed (figuratively, a bier); abstractly, sleep; by euphemism, carnal intercourse: bed((-chamber)), couch, lieth (lying) with.
from שָׂכַל; instructive, i.e. a didactic poem: Maschil.
from the same as שֶׂ֫כוּ; a figure (carved on stone, the wall, or any object); figuratively, imagination: conceit, image(-ry), picture, X wish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to מִשְׁכָּן; residence: habitation.

from שָׁכַן; a residence (including a shepherd's hut, the lair of animals, figuratively, the grave; also the Temple); specifically, the Tabernacle (properly, its wooden walls): dwelleth, dwelling (place), habitation, tabernacle, tent.
from שָׂכַר; wages or a reward: reward, wages.
a primitive root; to rule: (have, make to have) dominion, governor, X indeed, reign, (bear, cause to, have) rule(-ing, -r), have power.

denominative from מָשָׁל; to liken, i.e. (transitively) to use figurative language (an allegory, adage, song or the like); intransitively, to resemble: be(-come) like, compare, use (as a) proverb, speak (in proverbs), utter.

apparently from מָשַׁל in some original sense of superiority in mental action; properly, a pithy maxim, usually of metaphorical nature; hence, a simile (as an adage, poem, discourse): byword, like, parable, proverb.
for מִשְׁאָל; Mashal, a place in Palestine: Mashal.
from מָשַׁל; a satire: byword.
(1) from מָשַׁל; empire; (2) from מָשַׁל; a parallel: dominion, like.

or mishloach; also mishlach; from שָׁלַח; a sending out, i.e. (abstractly) presentation (favorable), or seizure (unfavorable); also (concretely) a place of dismissal, or a business to be discharged: to lay, to put, sending (forth), to set.
feminine of מִשְׁלַח; a mission, i.e. (abstractly) and favorable) release, or (concretely and unfavorable) an army: discharge, sending.
from שָׁלַם; allied; Meshullam, the name of seventeen Israelites: Meshullam.
plural from שָׁלַם; reconciliations: Meshillemoth, an Israelite:--Meshillemoth. Compare מְשִׁלֵּמִית.
or Mshelemyahuw; from שָׁלַם and יָהּ; ally of Jah; Meshelemjah, an Israelite: Meshelemiah.
from שָׁלַם; reconciliation; Meshillemith, an Israelite: Meshillemith. Compare מְשִׁלֵּמוֹת.
feminine of מְשֻׁלָּם; Meshullemeth, an Israelitess: Meshullemeth.
from שָׁמֵם; a waste or amazement: astonishment, desolate.
from שָׁמַן; fat, i.e. (literally and abstractly) fatness; but usually (figuratively and concretely) a rich dish, a fertile field, a robust man: fat (one, -ness, -test, -test place).
from שָׁמַן; fatness; Mashmannah, an Israelite: Mishmannah.
from שָׁמַע; a report: hearing.
the same as מִשְׁמַע; Mishma, the name of a son of Ishmael, and of an Israelite: Mishma.
