from עָבַר; properly, a region across; but used only adverbially (with or without a preposition) on the opposite side (especially of the Jordan; ususally meaning the east): X against, beyond, by, X from, over, passage, quarter, (other, this) side, straight.
the same as עֵ֫בֶר; Eber, the name of two patriarchs and four Israelites: Eber, Heber.
feminine of עֵ֫בֶר; an outburst of passion: anger, rage, wrath.
from עָבַר; a crossing-place: ferry, plain (from the margin).
patronymic from עֵ֫בֶר; an Eberite (i.e. Hebrew) or descendant of Eber: Hebrew(-ess, woman).
the same as עִבְרִי; Ibri, an Israelite: Ibri.
plural of עֵ֫בֶר; regions beyond; Abarim, a place in Palestine: Abarim, passages.
from עֵ֫בֶר; transitional; Ebron, a place in Palestine: Hebron. Perhaps a clerical error for עַבְדּוֹן.
feminine of עֶבְרֹן; Ebronah, place in the Desert: Ebronah.
a primitive root; to dry up: be rotten.
a primitive root; to interlace, i.e. (figuratively) to pervert: wrap up.
or rabowth; from עָבַת; intwined, i.e. dense: thick.
or rabowth; or (feminine) tabothah; the same as עָבֹת; something intwined, i.e. a string, wreath or foliage: band, cord, rope, thick bough (branch), wreathen (chain).
a primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. to love (sensually): dote, lover.
from עָגַב; love (concretely), i.e. amative words: much love, very lovely.
from עָגַב; love (abstractly), i.e. amorousness: inordinate love.
from עוּג; an ash-cake (as round): cake (upon the hearth).
passive part (but with active sense) of an unused root meaning to twitter: probably the swallow: swallow.
from the same as עָגֹל; something round, i.e. a ring (for the ears): earring.
from the same as עָגֹל; a (male) calf (as frisking round), especially one nearly grown (i.e. a steer): bullock, calf.
or magowl; from an unused root meaning to revolve, circular: round.
feminine of עֵ֫גֶל; a (female) calf, especially one nearly grown (i.e. a heifer): calf, cow, heifer.
the same as עֶגְלָה; Eglah, a wife of David: Eglah.
from the same as עָגֹל; something revolving, i.e. a wheeled vehicle:--cart, chariot, wagon
from עֵ֫גֶל; vituline; Eglon, the name of a place in Palestine and of a Moabitish king: Eglon.
a primitive root; to be sad: grieve.
a primitive root; to debar, i.e. from marriage: stay.

from עָדָה; properly, a (peremptory) terminus, i.e. (by implication) duration, in the sense of advance or perpetuity (substantially as a noun, either with or without a preposition): eternity, ever(- lasting, -more), old, perpetually, + world without end.

properly, the same as עַד (used as a preposition, adverb or conjunction; especially with a preposition); as far (or long, or much) as, whether of space (even unto) or time (during, while, until) or degree (equally with): against, and, as, at, before, by (that), even (to), for(-asmuch as), (hither-)to, + how long, into, as long (much) as, (so) that, till, toward, until, when, while, (+ as) yet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עַד; X and, at, for, (hither-)to, on till, (un-)to, until, within.
the same as עַד in the sense of the aim of an attack; booty: prey.
contracted from עוּד; concretely, a witness; abstractly, testimony; specifically, a recorder, i.e. prince: witness.
from an unused root meaning to set a period (compare עָדָה, עוּד); the menstrual flux (as periodical); by implication (in plural) soiling: filthy.
(Aramaic) or adah (Aramaic); corresponding to עָדָה: alter, depart, pass (away), remove, take (away).
a primitive root; to advance, i.e. pass on or continue; causatively, to remove; specifically, to bedeck (i.e. bring an ornament upon): adorn, deck (self), pass by, take away.
from עָדָה; ornament; Adah, the name of two women: Adah.

feminine of עֵד in the original sense of fixture; a stated assemblage (specifically, a concourse, or generally, a family or crowd): assembly, company, congregation, multitude, people, swarm. Compare עֵדָה.
feminine of עֵד in its techn. sense; testimonytestimony, witness. Compare עֵדָה.
or Iddowo; or Iddiy; from עָדָה; timely; Iddo (or Iddi), the name of five Israelites: Iddo. Compare יִדּוֹ, יֶעְדּוֹ.
feminine of עֵד; testimony: testimony, witness.
from עָדָה in the sense of trappings; finery; generally an outfit; specifically, a headstall: X excellent, mouth, ornament.
from עֶ֫דִי and אֵל; ornament of God; Adiel, the name of three Israelites: Adiel.
or Adayahuw; from עָדָה and יָהּ; Jah has adorned; Adajah, the name of eight Israelites: Adaiah.
from עָדַן; voluptuous: given to pleasures.
the same as עֲדִינָה; Adin, the name of two Israelites: Adin.
from עֲדִינָה; effeminacy; Adina, an Israelite: Adina.
probably from עֲדִינָה in the original sense of slender (i.e. a spear); his spear: Adino.
dual of a feminine of עַד; double prey; Adithajim, a place in Palestine: Adithaim.
probably from an unused root of uncertain meaning; Adlai, an Israelite: Adlai.
probably from the passive participle of the same as עַדְלָי; Adullam, a place in Palestine: Adullam.
patrial from עֲדֻלָּם; an Adullamite or native of Adullam: Adullamite.
a primitive root; to be soft or pleasant; figuratively and reflexively, to live voluptuously: delight self.
or radennah; from עַד and הֵן; till now: yet.
from עָדַן; pleasure; Eden, a place in Mesopotamia: Eden.
or (feminine) aednah; from עָדַן; pleasure: delicate, delight, pleasure. See also בֵּית עֵ֫דֶן.
the same as עֲדָנִים (masculine); Eden, the region of Adam's home: Eden.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of עִדִּים; a set time; technically, a year: time.
from עָדַן; pleasure; Adna, the name of two Israelites: Adna.
from עָדַן; pleasure; Adnah, the name of two Israelites: Adnah.
from עֵדָה; festival; Adadah, a place in Palestine: Adadah.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, have) redundant: be more, odd number, be (have) over (and above), overplus, remain.
a primitive root; to arrange, as a battle, a vineyard (to hoe); hence, to muster and so to miss (or find wanting): dig, fail, keep (rank), lack.
from עָדַר; an arrangement (i.e. drove); Eder, an Israelite: Ader.
from עָדַר; an arrangement, i.e. muster (of animals): drove, flock, herd.
the same as עֵ֫דֶר; Eder, the name of an Israelite and of two places in Palestine: Edar, Eder.
from עֵ֫דֶר and אֵל; flock of God; Adriel, an Israelite: Adriel.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a lentil: lentile.
a primitive root; to be dense or dark, i.e. to becloud: cover with a cloud.
active participle of עָבַד; serving; Obed, the name of five Israelites: Obed.
of foreign derivation; Obal, a son of Joktan: Obal.
a primitive root; properly, to gyrate; but used only as a denominative from עֻגָה, to bake (round cakes on the hearth): bake.
probably from עוּג; round; Og, a king of Bashan: Og.
or buggab; from עָגַב in the original sense of breathing; a reed-instrument of music: organ.

a primitive root; to duplicate or repeat; by implication, to protest, testify (as by reiteration); intensively, to encompass, restore (as a sort of reduplication): admonish, charge, earnestly, lift up, protest, call (take) to record, relieve, rob, solemnly, stand upright, testify, give warning, (bear, call to, give, take to) witness.

or rod; from עוּד; properly, iteration or continuance; used only adverbially (with or without preposition), again, repeatedly, still, more: again, X all life long, at all, besides, but, else, further(-more), henceforth, (any) longer, (any) more(-over), X once, since, (be) still, when, (good, the) while (having being), (as, because, whether, while) yet (within).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עוֹד: while.
or Oded; from עוּד; reiteration; Oded, the name of two Israelites: Oded.
a primitive root; to crook, literally or figuratively (as follows): do amiss, bow down, make crooked, commit iniquity, pervert, (do) perverse(-ly), trouble, X turn, do wickedly, do wrong.
intensive from עָוָה abbreviated; overthrow: X overturn.
or Avvae (2 Kings 17:24); for עַוָּה; Ivvah or Avva, a region of Assyria: Ava, Ivah.
a primitive root; to be strong; causatively, to stregthen, i.e. (figuratively) to save (by flight): gather (self, self to flee), retire.
patrial from עַוָּא; an Avvite or native of Avvah (only plural): Avims, Avites.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to עָוָה; perverseness: iniquity.
from עוּל; a babe: young child, little one.
from עָוַל; perverse (morally): ungodly.
plural of עַוִּים; Avvim (as inhabited by Avvites), a place in Palestine (with the article prefix): Avim.
or (perhaps Ayowth, as if plural of עַי) Ayuwth; from עָוָה; ruin; Avvith (or Avvoth), a place in Palestine: Avith.
a primitive root; to suckle, i.e. give milk: milch, (ewe great) with young.
from עוּל; a babe: sucking child, infant.
a primitive root; to distort (morally): deal unjustly, unrighteous.
or lavel; and (feminine) lavlah; or owlah; or .olah; from עָוַל; (moral) evil: iniquity, perverseness, unjust(-ly), unrighteousness(-ly); wicked(-ness).
intensive from עָוַל; evil (morally): unjust, unrighteous, wicked.
or lolal; from עוּל; a suckling: babe, (young) child, infant, little one.

or lolam; from עָלַם; properly, concealed, i.e. the vanishing point; generally, time out of mind (past or future), i.e. (practically) eternity; frequentatively, adverbial (especially with prepositional prefix) always: alway(-s), ancient (time), any more, continuance, eternal, (for, (n-))ever(-lasting, -more, of old), lasting, long (time), (of) old (time), perpetual, at any time, (beginning of the) world (+ without end). Compare נֵ֫צַח, עַד.
denominative from עַ֫יִן; to watch (with jealosy): eye.
or oavown (2 Kings 7:9; Psalm 51:5 (7)); from עָוָה; perversity, i.e. (moral) evil: fault, iniquity, mischeif, punishment (of iniquity), sin.
from an unused root apparently meaning to dwell together; sexual (cohabitation): duty of marriage.
from עָוָה; perversity: X perverse.

a primitive root; to cover (with wings or obscurity); hence (as denominative from עוֹף) to fly; also (by implication of dimness) to faint (from the darkness of swooning): brandish, be (wax) faint, flee away, fly (away), X set, shine forth, weary.
from עוּף; a bird (as covered with feathers, or rather as covering with wings), often collectively: bird, that flieth, flying, fowl.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עוֹף: fowl.
or mophereth; feminine participle active of עָפַר; lead (from its dusty color): lead.
from עוֹף; birdlike; Ephai, an Israelite: Ephai (from margin).
a primitive root; to consult: take advice ((counsel) together).
apparently from עוּץ; consultation; Uts, a son of Aram, also a Seirite, and the regions settled by them.: Uz.
a primitive root; to pack: be pressed.
a primitive root (rather identical with עוּר through the idea of opening the eyes); to wake (literally or figuratively): (a-)wake(-n, up), lift up (self), X master, raise (up), stir up (self).
a primitive root; to (be) bare: be made naked.
(Aramaic) chaff (as the naked husk): chaff.
from עוּר; skin (as naked); by implication, hide, leather: hide, leather, skin.
a primitive root (rather denominatively from עוֹר through the idea of a film over the eyes); to blind: blind, put out. See also עַ֫יִר.
intensive from עָוַר; blind (literally or figuratively): blind (men, people).
and (feminine) avvereth; from עִוְרוֹת; blindness: blind(-ness).
a primitive root; to hasten: assemble self.
for עוּשׁ; to hasten, i.e. succor: speak in season.
a primitive root; to wrest: bow self, (make) crooked., falsifying, overthrow, deal perversely, pervert, subvert, turn upside down.
from עָוַת; oppression: wrong.
from עוּת; succoring; Uthai, the name of two Israelites: Uthai.
from עָזַז; strong, vehement, harsh: fierce, + greedy, mighty, power, roughly, strong.
from עָזַז; a she-goat (as strong), but masculine in plural (which also is used ellipt. for goat's hair): (she) goat, kid.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֵז: goat.
or (fully) rowz; from עָזַז; strength in various applications (force, security, majesty, praise): boldness, loud, might, power, strength, strong.
or (Uzzah; feminine of עֹז; strength; Uzza or Uzzah, the name of five Israelites: Uzza, Uzzah.
from עֵז and אָזַל; goat of departure; the scapegoat: scapegoat.
a primitive root; to loosen, i.e. relinquish, permit, etc.: commit self, fail, forsake, fortify, help, leave (destitute, off), refuse, X surely.
from עָזַב in the sense of letting go (for a price, i.e. selling); trade, i.e. the place (mart) or the payment (revenue): fair, ware.
from עָז and the root of בּוּקָה; stern depopulator; Azbuk, an Israelite: Azbuk.
from עָז and גָּד; stern troop; Azgad, an Israelite: Azgad.
feminine of עָז; strong; Azzah, a place in Palestine: Azzah, Gaza.
feminine passive participle of עָזַב; desertion (of inhabitants): forsaking.
the same as עֲזוּבָה; Azubah, the name of two Israelitesses: Azubah.
from עָזַז; forcibleness: might, strength.
from עָזַז; forcible; collectively and concretely, an army: power, strong.
or Azzur; from עָזַר; helpful; Azzur, the name of three Israelites: Azur, Azzur.
a primitive root; to be stout (literally or figuratively): harden, impudent, prevail, strengthen (self), be strong.
from עָזַז; strong; Azaz, an Israelite: Azaz.
from עָזַז and יָהּ; Jah has strengthened; Azazjah, the name of three Israelites: Azaziah.
from עָזַז; forceful; Uzzi, the name of six Israelites: Uzzi.
perhaps for עֻזִּיָּה; Uzzija, an Israelite: Uzzia.
from עוּז and אֵל; strengthened of God; Aziel, an Israelite: Aziel. Compare יַעֲזִיאֵל.
from עֹז and אֵל; strength of God; Uzziel, the name of six Israelites: Uzziel.
patronymically from עֻזִּיאֵל; an Uzzielite (collectively) or descendants of Uzziel: Uzzielites.
or Uzziyahuw; from עֹז and יָהּ; strength of Jah; Uzzijah, the name of five Israelites: Uzziah.
from עוּז; strengthfulness; Aziza, an Israelite: Aziza.
from עָז and מָ֫וֶת; strong one of death; Azmaveth, the name of three Israelites and of a place in Palestine: Azmaveth. See also בֵּית עַזְמָ֫וֶת.
from עָז; strong one; Azzan, an Israelite: Azzan.
probably feminine of עֹז; probably the sea-eagle (from its strength): ospray.
a primitive root; to grub over: fence about.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to עָזַק; a signet-ring (as engraved): signet.
from עָזַק; tilled; Azekah, a place in Palestine: Azekah.
a primitive root; to surround, i.e. protect or aid: help, succour.
from עָזַר; help; Ezer, the name of two Israelites: Ezer. Compare עֵ֫זֶר.
from עָזַר; aid: help.
the same as עֵ֫זֶר; Ezer, the name of four Israelites: Ezer. Compare עָ֫זֶר.
a variation of עֶזְרָה; Ezra, an Israelite: Ezra.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֶזְרָא; Ezra, an Israelite --Ezra.
from עָזַר and אֵל; God has helped; Azarel, the name of five Israelites: Azarael, Azareel.
or mezrath (Psa. 60:11 (13); 108:12 (13)); feminine of עֵ֫זֶר; aid: help(-ed, -er).
the same as עֶזְרָה; Ezrah, an Israelite: Ezrah.
from עָזַר in its original meaning of surrounding; an inclosure; also a border: court, settle.
from עֵ֫זֶר; helpful; Ezri, an Israelite: Ezri.
from עֵ֫זֶר and אֵל; help of God; Azriel, the name of three Israelites: Azriel.
or Azaryahuw; from עָזַר and יָהּ; Jah has helped; Azarjah, the name of nineteen Israelites: Azariah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֲזַרְיָה; Azarjah, one of Daniel's companions: Azariah.
from עֵ֫זֶר and active participle of קוּם; help of an enemy; Azrikam, the name of four Israelites: Azrikam.
patrial from עַזָּה; an Azzathite or inhabitant of Azzah: Gazathite, Gazite.
from עִיט (contracted) in the sense of swooping, i.e. side-long stroke; a stylus or marking stick: pen.
(Aramaic) from יְעַט; prudence: counsel.
a primitive root; to wrap, i.e. cover, veil, cloth, or roll: array self, be clad, (put a) cover (-ing, self), fill, put on, X surely, turn aside.
from an unused root meaning apparently to contain; a receptacle (for milk, i.e. pail; figuratively, breast): breast.
from an unused root meaning to sneeze; sneezing: sneezing.
of uncertain derivation; a bat: bat.
a primitive root; to shroud, i.e. clothe (whether transitive or reflex.); hence (from the idea of darkness) to languishcover (over), fail, faint, feebler, hide self, be overwhelmed, swoon.
a primitive root; to encircle (for attack or protection); especially to crown (literally or figuratively): compass, crown.
from עָטַר; a crown: crown.
the same as עֲטָרָה; Atarah, an Israelitess: Atarah.
or Ataroth; plural of עֲטָרָה; Ataroth, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine: Ataroth.
from the same as עֲטָרוֹת and אַדָּר; crowns of Addar; Atroth-Addar, a place in Palestine: Ataroth-adar(-addar).
from the same as עֲטָרוֹת and בָּ֫יִת and יוֹאָב; crowns of the house of Joab; Atroth-beth-Joab, a place in Palestine: Ataroth the house of Joab.
from the same as עֲטָרוֹת and a name otherwise unused (being from the same as שָׂפַן) meaning hidden; crowns of Shophan; Atroth-Shophan, a place in Palestine: Atroth, Shophan (as if two places).
from עָוָה; a ruin (as if overturned): heap.
or (feminine) Aya( (Neh. 11:31); or Ayath (Isaiah 10:28); for עִי; Ai, Aja or Ajath, a place in Palestine: Ai, Aija, Aijath, Hai.
perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be bald; bare; Ebal, a mountain of Palestine: Ebal.
from עִי; ruin; Ijon, a place in Palestine: Ijon.
a primitive root; to swoop down upon (literally or figuratively): fly, rail.
from עִיט; a hawk or other bird of prey: bird, fowl, ravenous (bird).
from עָ֫יִט; hawk-ground; Etam, a place in Palestine: Etam.
from the plural of עִי and the plural of the active participle of עָבַר with the article interposed; ruins of the passers; Ije-ha-Abarim, a place near Palestine: Ije-abarim.
plural of עִי; ruins; Ijim, a place in the Desert.: Iim.
for עוֹלָם: ever.
from עָלָה; elevated; Ilai, an Israelite: Ilai.
or Owlam (Ezra 10:2; Jeremiah 49:36); probably from עָלַם; hidden, i.e. distant; Elam, a son of Shem and his descendants, with their country; also of six Israelites: Elam.
of doubtful origin and authenticity; probably meaning strength: mighty.

probably a primitive word; an eye (literally or figuratively); by analogy, a fountain (as the eye of the landscape): affliction, outward appearance, + before, + think best, colour, conceit, + be content, countenance, + displease, eye((-brow), (-d), -sight), face, + favour, fountain, furrow (from the margin), X him, + humble, knowledge, look, (+ well), X me, open(-ly), + (not) please, presence, + regard, resemblance, sight, X thee, X them, + think, X us, well, X you(-rselves).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עַ֫יִן; an eye: eye.
the same as עַ֫יִן; fountain; Ajin, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine: Ain.
from עַ֫יִן and גֶּ֫דִי; fountain of a kid; En-Gedi, a place in Palestine: En-gedi.
from עַ֫יִן and the plural of גָּן; fountain of gardens; En-Gannim, a place in Palestine: En-gannim.
: ; or Eyn-Dor; from עַ֫יִן and דּוֹר; fountain of dwelling; En-Dor, a place in Palestine: En-dor.
from עַ֫יִן and the active participle of קָרָא; fountain of One calling; En-hak-Kore, a place near Palestine: En-hakhore.
from עַ֫יִן and the feminine of a derivative from חָדַד; fountain of sharpness; En-Chaddah, a place in Palestine: En-haddah.
from עַ֫יִן and the same as חָצוֹר; fountain of a village; En-Chatsor, a place in Palestine: En-hazor.
from עַ֫יִן and a derivative of חָרַד; fountain of trembling; En-Charod, a place in Palestine: well of Harod.
or Eynam; dual of עַ֫יִן; double fountain; Enajim or Enam, a place in Palestine: Enaim, openly (Genesis 38:21).
from עַ֫יִן and מִשְׁפָּט; fountain of judgment; En-Mishpat, a place near Palestine: En-mishpat.
from עַ֫יִן; having eyes; Enan, an Israelite: Enan. Compare חֲצַר עֵינָן.
עַ֫יִן and the dual of עֵ֫גֶל; fountain of two calves; En-Eglajim, a place in Palestine: En-eglaim.
from עַ֫יִן and the active participle of רָגַל; fountain of a traveller; En-Rogel, a place near Jerusalem: En-rogel.
from עַ֫יִן and רִמּוֹן; fountain of a pomegranate; En-Rimmon, a place in Palestine: En-rimmon.
from עַ֫יִן and שָׁ֫מֶשׁ; fountain of the sun; En-Shemesh, a place in Palestine: En-shemesh.
from עַ֫יִן and the plural of תַּנִּים; fountain of jackals; En-Tannim, a pool near Jerusalem: dragon well.
from עַ֫יִן and תַּפּ֫וּחַ; fountain of an apple-tree; En-Tappuach, a place in Palestine: En-tappuah.
a primitive root; to languish: be wearied.
from עִיף; languid: faint, thirsty, weary.
feminine from עוּף; obscurity (as if from covering): darkness.
the same as עֵיפָה; Ephah, the name of a son of Midian, and of the region settled by him; also of an Israelite and of an Israelitess: Ephah.

or (in the plural) par; or ayar (Judges 10:4); from עוּר a city (a place guarded by waking or a watch) in the widest sense (even of a mere encampment or post): Ai (from margin), city, court (from margin), town.
the same as עִיר; Ir, an Israelite: Ir.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to עוּר; a watcher, i.e. an angel (as guardian): watcher.
from עוּר in the sense of raising (i.e. bearing a burden); properly, a young ass (as just broken to a load); hence an ass-colt: (ass) colt, foal, young ass.
from עוּר; wakefulness; Ira, the name of three Israelites: Ira.
from the same as עֲרָד; fugitive; Irad, an antediluvian: Irad.
from עִיר and מֶ֫לַח with the article of substance interp.; city of (the) salt; Ir-ham-Melach, a place near Palestine: the city of salt.
from עִיר and the plural of תָּמָר with the article interpolated; city of the palmtrees; Ir-hat-Temarim, a place in Palestine: the city of palmtrees.
from עִיר; a citizen; Iru, an Israelite: Iru.
from עִיר; urbane; Iri, an Israelite: Iri.
from עִיר; city-wise; Iram, an Idumaean: Iram.
or merom; from עָרֹם; nudity: naked(- ness).
from עִיר and נָחָשׁ; city of a serpent; Ir-Nachash, a place in Palestine: Ir-nahash.
from עִיר and שָׁ֫מֶשׁ; city of the sun; Ir-Shemesh, a place in Palestine: Ir-shemesh.
or Ash; from עוּשׁ; the constellation of the Great Bear (perhaps from its migration through the heavens)Arcturus.
probably for עַכְבָּר; Akbor, the name of an Idumaean and of two Israelites: Achbor.
probably from an unused root in the literal sense of entangling; a spider (as weaving a network): spider.
probably from the same as עַכָּבִישׁ in the secondary sense of attacking; a mouse (as nibbling): mouse.
apparently from an unused root meaning to hem in; Akko (from its situation on a bay): Accho.
from עָכַר; troubled; Akor, the name of a place in Palestine: Achor.
from an unused root meaning to trouble; troublesome; Akan, an Israelite: Achan. Compare עָכָר.
a primitive root; properly, to tie, specifically, with fetters; but used only as denominative from עֲכָסִים; to put on anklets: make a tinkling ornament.
from עָכַס; a fetter; hence, an anklet: stocks, tinkling ornament.
feminine of עֲכָסִים; anklet; Aksah, an Israelitess: Achsah.
a primitive root; properly, to roil water; figuratively, to disturb or affict: trouble, stir.
from עָכַר; troublesome; Akar, an Israelite: Achar. Compare עָכָן.
from עָכַר; muddler; Okran, an Israelite: Ocran.
probably from an unused root meaning to coil; an asp (from lurking coiled up): adder.
from עָלָה; properly, the top; specifically, the highest (i.e. God); also (adverb) aloft, to Jehovah: above, high, most High.

properly, the same as עָל used as a preposition (in the singular or plural often with prefix, or as conjunction with a particle following); above, over, upon, or against (yet always in this last relation with a downward aspect) in a great variety of applications (as follow): above, according to(-ly), after, (as) against, among, and, X as, at, because of, beside (the rest of), between, beyond the time, X both and, by (reason of), X had the charge of, concerning for, in (that), (forth, out) of, (from) (off), (up-)on, over, than, through(-out), to, touching, X with.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עַל: about, against, concerning, for, (there-)fore, from, in, X more, of, (there-, up-)on, (in-)to, + why with.
or mowl; from עָלַל; a yoke (as imposed on the neck), literally or figuratively: yoke.
(Aramaic) from עַל; above: over.
feminine of עֹל; burden; Ulla, an Israelite: Ulla.
from an unused root meaning to stutter; stuttering: stammerer.

a primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative (as follow): arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up, + shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, X mention, mount up, offer, make to pay, + perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֹלָה; a holocaust: burnt offering.
from עָלָה; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage: branch, leaf.

or mowlah; feminine active participle of עָלָה; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke): ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also עָ֫וֶל.
(Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to עָלָה; a pretext (as arising artificially): occasion.
for עָ֫וֶל; moral perverseness: iniquity.
or Alyah; the same as עַלְוָה; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean: Aliah, Alvah.
passive participle of עָלַם in the denominative sense of עָ֫לֶם; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor: youth.
or Alyan; from עָלָה; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean: Alian, Alvan.
feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech: horse-leech.
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult: be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
from עָלַז; exultant: that rejoiceth.
feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk: dark, twilight.
from עָלָה; a pestle (as lifted): pestle.
from עָלָה; lofty; Eli, an Israelite high-priest: Eli.
from עָלָה; high; i.e. comparative: upper.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עִלִּית; supreme (i.e. God): (most) high.
feminine from עָלָה; something lofty, i.e. a stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky: ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour.
from עָלָה; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme: (Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֶלְיוֹן; the Supreme: Most high.
from עָלַז; exultant:--joyous, (that) rejoice(-ing)
from עָלַל in the sense of completing; probably a crucible (as working over the metal): furnace.

or malilah; from עָלַל in the sense of effecting; an exploit (of God), or a performance (of man, often in a bad sense); by implication, an opportunity: act(-ion), deed, doing, invention, occasion, work.
for עֲלִילָה; (miraculous) execution: work.
from עָלַץ; exultation: rejoicing.
from עָלָה; a second-story room: chamber. Compare עֲלִיָּה.

a primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal): abuse, affect, X child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָלַל (in the sense of thrusting oneself in), to enter; causatively, to introduce: bring in, come in, go in.
feminine active participle of עָלַל; only in plural gleanings; by extens. gleaning-time: (gleaning) (of the) grapes, grapegleanings.
a primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. conceal (literally or figuratively): X any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עוֹלָם; remote time, i.e. the future or past indefinitely; often adverb, forever: for ((n-))ever (lasting), old.
from עָלַם; properly, something kept out of sight (compare עַלְמָה), i.e. a lad: young man, stripling.
feminine of עָ֫לֶם; a lass (as veiled or private): damsel, maid, virgin.
from עָלַם; hidden; Almon, a place in Palestine See also עַלְמֹן דִּבְלָתָ֫יְמָה.
plural of עַלְמָה; properly, girls, i.e. the soprano or female voice, perhaps falsetto: Alamoth.
(Aramaic) patrial from a name corresponding to עֵילָם contracted; an Elamite or inhabitant of Elam: Elamite.
from the same as עַלְמוֹן and the dual of דְּבֵלִים (compare בֵּית דִּבְלָתַ֫יִם) with enclitic of direction; Almon towards Diblathajim; Almon-Diblathajemah, a place in Moab: Almon-dilathaim.
from עָלַם; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites: Alameth, Alemeth.
a primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. exult, wave joyously: X peacock, rejoice, solace self.
a prim root; to sip up: suck up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to צְלָעֹת; a rib: rib.
a primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid: faint, overlaid, wrap self.
from עָלַף; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning: fainted.
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult: be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
from עָמַם; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock: folk, men, nation, people.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָם: people.

from עָמַם; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. in conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English): accompanying, against, and, as (X long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of, (un-)to, with(-al).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עִם: by, from, like, to(-ward), with.

a primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive): abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair, + serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-)stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.
for מָעַד; to shake: be at a stand.
from עָמַד; a spot (as being fixed): place, (+ where) stood, upright.
prol. for עִם; along with: against, by, from, + me, + mine, of, + that I take, unto, upon, with(-in.)
from עָמַד; a station, i.e. domicile: standing.
from עָמַם; conjunction, i.e. society; mostly adverb or preposition (with prepositional prefix), near, beside, along with: (over) against, at, beside, hard by, in points.
the same as עֻמַּת; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine: Ummah.
or ammud; from עָמַד; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. platform: X apiece, pillar.
from עָם; tribal, i.e. inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country: Ammon, Ammonites.
patronymically from עַמּוֹן; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish: Ammonite(-s).
feminine of עַמּוֹנִי; an Ammonitess: Ammonite(-ss).
from עָמַס; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet: Amos.
from עָמַק; deep; Amok, an Israelite: Amok.
from עָם and אֵל; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites: Ammiel.
from עָם and הוֹד; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites: Ammihud.
from עָם and זָבַד; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite: Ammizabad.
from עָם and חוּר; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince: Ammihud (from the margin).
from עָם and נָדַב; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites: Amminadab.
from עָם and נָדִיב; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite: Amminadib.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עִמְקֵי; profound, i.e. unsearchable, deep.
from עָמַר; a bunch of grain: handful, sheaf.
from עָם and שַׁדָּי; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite: Ammishaddai.
from a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man: another, fellow, neighbour.
a primitive root; to toil, i.e. work severely and with irksomeness: (take) labour (in).

from עָמַל; toil, i.e. wearing effort; hence, worry, wheth. of body or mind: grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness.
the same as עָמָל; Amal, an Israelite: Amal.
from עָמַל; toiling; concretely, a laborer; figuratively, sorrowful: that laboureth, that is a misery, had taken (labour), wicked, workman.
probably of foreign origin; Amalek, a descendant of Esau; also his posterity and their country: Amalek.
patronymically from עֲמָלֵק; an Amalekite (or collectively the Amalekites) or descendants of Amalek: Amalekite(-s).
a primitive root; to associate; by implication, to overshadow (by huddling together): become dim, hide.
from עִם and אֵל with a pronominal suffix inserted; with us (is) God; Immanuel, a type name of Isaiah's son: Immanuel.
or mamas; a primitive root; to load, i.e. impose a burden (or figuratively, infliction): be borne, (heavy) burden (self), lade, load, put.
from עָמַס and יָהּ; Jah has loaded; Amasjah, an Israelite: Amasiah.
from עָם and עַד; people of time; Amad, a place in Palestine: Amad.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) deep (literally or figuratively): (be, have, make, seek) deep(-ly), depth, be profound.
from עָמַק; a vale (i.e. broad depression): dale, vale, valley (often used as a part of proper names). See also בֵּית הָעֵ֫מֶק.
from עָמַק; depth: depth.
from עָמַק; deep (literally or figuratively): deeper, depth, strange.
from עָמַק; deep (literally or figuratively): (X exceeding) deep (thing).
a primitive root; properly, apparently to heap; figuratively, to chastise (as if piling blows); specifically (as denominative from עֹ֫מֶר) to gather grain: bind sheaves, make merchandise of.
(Aramaic) corresponding to צָ֫מֶר; wool: wool.
from עָמַר; properly, a heap, i.e. a sheaf; also an omer, as a dry measure: omer, sheaf.
from עָמַר; a (ruined) heap; Amorah, a place in Palestine: Gomorrah.
from עָמַר; heaping; Omri, an Israelite: Omri.
probably from עָם and רוּם; high people; Amram, the name of two Israelites: Amram.
from עַמְרָם; an Amramite or descendant of Amram: Amramite.
from עָמַס; burden; Amasa, the name of two Israelites: Amasa.
from עָמַס; burdensome; Amasai, the name of three Israelites: Amasai.
probably from עָמַס; burdensome; Amashsay, an Israelite: Amashai.
from the same as עֲנָבִים; fruit; Anab, a place in Palestine: Anab.
from an unused root probably meaning to bear fruit; a grape: (ripe) grape, wine.
a primitive root; to be soft or pliable, i.e. (figuratively) effeminate or luxurious: delicate(-ness), (have) delight (self), sport self.
from עָנַג; luxury: delight, pleasant.
from עָנַג; luxurious: delicate.
a primitive root; to lace fast: bind, tie.

a primitive root; properly, to eye or (generally) to heed, i.e. pay attention; by implication, to respond; by extens. to begin to speak; specifically to sing, shout, testify, announce: give account, afflict (by mistake for `anah), (cause to, give) answer, bring low (by mistake for `anah), cry, hear, Leannoth, lift up, say, X scholar, (give a) shout, sing (together by course), speak, testify, utter, (bear) witness. See also בֵּית עֲנוֹת, בֵּית עֲנָת.

a primitive root (possibly rather ident. with עָנָה through the idea of looking down or browbeating); to depress literally or figuratively, transitive or intransitive (in various applications, as follows): abase self, afflict(-ion, self), answer (by mistake for `anah), chasten self, deal hardly with, defile, exercise, force, gentleness, humble (self), hurt, ravish, sing (by mistake for `anah), speak (by mistake for `anah), submit self, weaken, X in any wise.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָנָה: answer, speak.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָנָה: poor.
probably from עָנָה; an answer; Anah, the name of two Edomites and one Edomitess: Anah.
or (by intermixture with עָנִי) Aanayv; from עָנָה; depressed (figuratively), in mind (gentle) or circumstances (needy, especially saintly): humble, lowly, meek, poor. Compare עָנִי.
passive participle from the same as עֲנָבִים; borne (as fruit); Anub, an Israelite: Anub.
feminine of עָנָו; mildness (royal); also (concretely) oppressed: gentleness, meekness.
from עָנָו; condescension, human and subjective (modesty), or divine and objective (clemency): gentleness, humility, meekness.
from עָנָה; affliction: affliction.
from עָנָה; depression, i.e. misery: afflicted(-ion), trouble.

from עָנָה; depressed, in mind or circumstances (practically the same as עָנָו, although the margin constantly disputes this, making עָנָו subjective and עָנִי objective): afflicted, humble, lowly, needy, poor.
from עָנָה; afflicted; Unni, the name of two Israelites: Unni.
from עָנָה; Jah has answered; Anajah, the name of two Israelites: Anaiah.
for plural of עַ֫יִן; fountains; Anim, a place in Palestine: Anim.
from עָנָה; ado, i.e. (generally) employment or (specifically) an affair: business, travail.
from the dual of עַ֫יִן; two fountains; Anem, a place in Palestine: Anem.
as if plural of some Egyptian word; Anamim, a son of Mizraim and his descendants, with their country: Anamim.
of foreign origin; Anammelek, an Assyrian deity: Anammelech.

a primitive root; to cover; used only as a denominative from עָנָן, to cloud over; figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. practise magic: X bring, enchanter, Meonemin, observe(-r of) times, soothsayer, sorcerer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָנָן: cloud.
from עָנַן; a cloud (as covering the sky), i.e. the nimbus or thunder-cloud: cloud(-y).
the same as עָנָן; cloud; Anan, an Israelite: Anan.
feminine of עָנָן; cloudiness: cloud.
from עָנָן; cloudy; Anani, an Israelite: Anani.
from עָנַן and יָהּ; Jah has covered; Ananjah, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine: Ananiah.
(Aramaic) or deneph (Aramaic); corresponding to עָנָף: bough, branch.
from an unused root meaning to cover; a twig (as covering the limbs): bough, branch.
from the same as עָנָף; branching: full of branches.

a primitive root; properly, to choke; used only as denominative from עֲנָק, to collar, i.e. adorn with a necklace; figuratively, to fit out with supplies: compass about as a chain, furnish, liberally.
from עָנַק; a necklace (as if strangling): chain.
the same as עֲנָק; Anak, a Canaanite: Anak.
patronymically from עֲנָק; an Anakite or descendant of Anak: Anakim.
probably for נַ֫עַר; Aner, a Amorite, also a place in Palestine: Aner.
a primitive root; properly, to urge; by implication, to inflict a penalty, specifically, to fine: amerce, condemn, punish, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֹ֫נֶשׁ; a mulct: confiscation.
from עָנַשׁ; a fine: punishment, tribute.
from עָנָה; answer; Anath, an Israelite: Anath.
plural of עֲנָת; Anathoth, the name of two Israelites, also of a place in Pal: Anathoth.
or Annthowthiy; patrial from עֲנָתוֹת; a Antothite or inhabitant of Anathoth: of Anathoth, Anethothite, Anetothite, Antothite.
from the same as עֲנָתוֹת and יָהּ; answers of Jah; Anthothijah, an Israelite: Antothijah.
from עָסַס; must or fresh grape-juice (as just trodden out): juice, new (sweet) wine.
a primitive root; to squeeze out juice; figuratively, to trample: tread down.
from an unused root meaning to cover; a bough (as covering the tree): branch.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֳפָאּים; a twig; bough, i.e. (collectively) foliage: leaves.
a primitive root; to swell; figuratively, be elated: be lifted up, presume.
from עָפַל; a tumor; also a mound, i.e. fortress: emerod, fort, strong hold, tower.
the same as עֹ֫פֶל; Ophel, a ridge in Jerusalem: Ophel.
from an unused noun (denoting a place in Palestine; from an unused root of uncertain meaning); an Ophnite (collectively) or inhabitants of Ophen: Ophni.
from עוּף; an eyelash (as fluttering); figuratively, morning ray: dawning, eye-lid.
:  : a primitive root: meaning either to be gray or perhaps rather to pulverize; used only as denominative from עָפָר, to be dust: cast (dust).
probably a variation of עֹ֫פֶר; gazelle; Epher, the name of an Arabian and of two Israelites: Epher.
from עָפַר; a fawn (from the dusty color): young roe (hart).
from עָפַר; dust (as powdered or gray); hence, clay, earth, mud: ashes, dust, earth, ground, morter, powder, rubbish.
feminine of עֹ֫פֶר; female fawn; Ophrah, the name of an Israelite and of two places in Palestine: Ophrah.
from the same as עֵ֫פֶר; fawn-like; Ephron, the name of a Canaanite and of two places in Palestine: Ephron, Ephrain (from the margin).
from עָצָה; a tree (from its firmness); hence, wood (plural sticks): + carpenter, gallows, helve, + pine, plank, staff, stalk, stick, stock, timber, tree, wood.
a primitive root; properly, to carve, i.e. fabricate or fashion; hence (in a bad sense) to worry, pain or angerdisplease, grieve, hurt, make, be sorry, vex, worship, wrest.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָצַב; to afflict: lamentable.
from עָצַב; an earthen vessel; usually (painful) toil; also a pang (whether of body or mind): grievous, idol, labor, sorrow.
a variation of עֶ֫צֶב; an idol (as fashioned); also pain (bodily or mental): idol, sorrow, X wicked.
from עָצַב; an (idolatrous) image: idol, image.
from עָצַב; a (hired) workman: labour.
from עָצַב; worrisomeness, i.e. labor or pain: sorrow, toil.
from עָצַב; a idol; also, a pain or wound: sorrow, wound.
a primitive root; properly, to fasten (or make firm), i.e. to close (the eyes): shut.
from עָצָה; the spine (as giving firmness to the body): backbone.
feminine of עֵץ; timber: trees.
from יָעַץ; advice; by implication, plan; also prudence: advice, advisement, counsel(l-(or)), purpose.
or matsum; passive participle of עָצַם; powerful (specifically, a paw); by implication, numerous: + feeble, great, mighty, must, strong.
or shorter `Etsyon, from עָצֶה and גָּ֫בֶר; backbone-like of a man; Etsjon-Geber, a place on the Red Sea: Ezion-geber.
a primitive root; to lean idly, i.e. to be indolent or slack: be slothful.
from עָצַל; indolent: slothful, sluggard.
feminine of עָצֵל; (as abstractly) indolence: slothfulness.
rom עָצַל; indolence: idleness.

a primitive root; to bind fast, i.e. close (the eyes); intransitively, to be (causatively, make) powerful or numerous; denominatively (from עָ֫צֶם) to crunch the bones: break the bones, close, be great, be increased, be (wax) mighty(-ier), be more, shut, be(-come, make) strong(-er).
from עָצַם; a bone (as strong); by extension, the body; figuratively, the substance, i.e. (as pron.) selfsame: body, bone, X life, (self-)same, strength, X very.
the same as עָ֫צֶם; bone; Etsem, a place in Palestine: Azem, Ezem.
from עָצַם; power; hence, body: might, strong, substance.
feminine of עֹ֫צֶם; powerfulness; by extension, numerousness: abundance, strength.
feminine of עָצוּם; a bulwark, i.e. (figuratively) argument: strong.
or Atsmon; from עָ֫צֶם; bone-like; Atsmon, a place near Palestine: Azmon.
from an unused root meaning to be sharp or strong; a spear: Eznite (from the margin).

a primitive root; to inclose; by analogy, to hold back; also to maintain, rule, assemble: X be able, close up, detain, fast, keep (self close, still), prevail, recover, refrain, X reign, restrain, retain, shut (up), slack, stay, stop, withhold (self).
from עָצַר; restraint: + magistrate.
from עָצַר; closure; also constraint: X barren, oppression, X prison.
or matsereth; from עָצַר; an assembly, especially on a festival or holiday: (solemn) assembly (meeting).

a primitive root; properly, to swell out or up; used only as denominative from עִקְּבֵי, to seize by the heel; figuratively, to circumvent (as if tripping up the heels); also to restrain (as if holding by the heel): take by the heel, stay, supplant, X utterly.

from עָקַב in the sense of עִקְּבֵי; a heel, i.e. (figuratively) the last of anything (used adverbially, for ever); also result, i.e. compensation; and so (adverb with preposition or relatively) on account of: X because, by, end, for, if, reward.
or (feminine) hiqqbah; from עָקַב; a heel (as protuberant); hence, a track; figuratively, the rear (of an army): heel, (horse-)hoof, last, lier in wait (by mistake for `aqeb), (foot-)step.
from עָקַב in its denominative sense; a lier in wait: heel (by mistake for `aqeb).
from עָקַב; in the original sense, a knoll (as swelling up); in the denominative sense (transitive) fraudulent or (intransitive) tracked: crooked, deceitful, polluted.
feminine of an unused form from עָקַב meaning a trick; trickery: subtilty.
a primitive root; to tie with thongs: bind.
from עָקַד; striped (with bands): ring straked.
from עוּק; constraint: oppression.
from עָקַב; insidious; Akkub, the name of five Israelites: Akkub.
a primitive root; to wrest: wrong.
from עָקַל; winding: by(-way), crooked way.
from עָקַל; tortuous: crooked.
from an unused root meaning to twist; tortuous; Akan, an Idummaean: Akan. Compare יַעֲקָן.
a primitive root; to pluck up (especially by the roots); specifically, to hamstring; figuratively, to exterminate: dig down, hough, pluck up, root up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָקַר: pluck up by the roots.
from עָקַר. figuratively, a transplanted person, i.e. naturalized citizen: stock.
the same as עֵ֫קֶר; Eker, an Israelite: Eker.
from עָקַר; sterile (as if extirpated in the generative organs): (X male or female) barren (woman).
(Aramaic) from עֲקַר; a stock: stump.
of uncertain derivation; a scorpion; figuratively, a scourge or knotted whip: scorpion.
from עָקַר; eradication; Ekron, a place in Palestine: Ekron.
or Eqroniy; patrial from עֶקְרוֹן; an Ekronite or inhabitant of Ekron: Ekronite.
a primitive root; to knot or distort; figuratively, to pervert (act or declare perverse): make crooked, (prove, that is) perverse(-rt).
from עָקַשׁ; distorted; hence, false: crooked, froward, perverse.
the same as עִקֵּשׁ; perverse; Ikkesh, an Israelite: Ikkesh.
from עִקֵּשׁ; perversity: X froward.
the same as עִיר; a city; Ar, a place in Moab: Ar.
from עוּר; a foe (as watchful for mischief): enemy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָר: enemy.
from עוּר; watchful; Er, the name of two Israelites: Er.

a primitive root; to braid, i.e. intermix; technically, to traffic (as if by barter); also or give to be security (as a kind of exchange): engage, (inter-)meddle (with), mingle (self), mortgage, occupy, give pledges, be(-come, put in) surety, undertake.
a primitive root (identical with עָרַב through the idea of close association); to be agreeable: be pleasant(-ing), take pleasure in, be sweet.
a primitive root (identical with עָרַב through the idea of covering with a texture); to grow dusky at sundown: be darkened, (toward) evening.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָרַב; to commingle: mingle (self), mix.
or Arab; from עָרַב in the figurative sense of sterility; Arab (i.e. Arabia), a country East of Palestine: Arabia.
from עָרַב; dusk: + day, even(-ing, tide), night.
or mereb (1 Kings 10:15), (with the article prefix); from עָרַב; the web (or transverse threads of cloth); also a mixture, (or mongrel race): Arabia, mingled people, mixed (multitude), woof.
from עָרַב; a willow (from the use of osiers as wattles): willow.
from עָרֵב; pleasant: sweet.
from עָרַב; a mosquito (from its swarming): divers sorts of flies, swarm.
or mowreb; from עָרַב; a raven (from its dusky hue): raven.
or Owreb; the same as עֹרֵב; Oreb, the name of a Midianite and of the cliff near the Jordan: Oreb.

from עָרַב (in the sense of sterility); a desert; especially (with the article prefix) the (generally) sterile valley of the Jordan and its continuation to the Red Sea: Arabah, champaign, desert, evening, heaven, plain, wilderness. See also בֵּית הָעֲרָבָה.
feminine passive participle of עֲנַמֶּ֫לֶך in the sense of a bargain or exchange; something given as security, i.e. (literally) a token (of safety) or (metaphorically) a bondsman: pledge, surety.
from עָרַב (in the sense of exchange); a pawn (given as security): pledge.
or Arbiy; patrial from עֲרָב; an Arabian or inhabitant of Arab (i.e. Arabia): Arabian.
patrial from בֵּית הָעֲרָבָה; an Arbathite or inhabitant of (Beth-)Arabah: Arbahite.
a primitive root; to long for: cry, pant.
from an unused root meaning to sequester itself; fugitive; Arad, the name of a place near Palestine, also of a Canaanite and an Israelite: Arad.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָרוֹד; an onager: wild ass.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bare; hence, to empty, pour out, demolish: leave destitute, discover, empty, make naked, pour (out), rase, spread self, uncover.
feminine from עָרָה; a naked (i.e. level) plot: paper reed.
or iarugah; feminine passive participle of עָרַג; something piled up (as if (figuratively) raised by mental aspiration), i.e. a paterre: bed, furrow.
from the same as עֲרָד; an onager (from his lonesome habits): wild ass.
from עָרָה; nudity, literally (especially the pudenda) or figuratively (disgrace, blemish): nakedness, shame, unclean(-ness).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֶרְוָה; nakedness, i.e. (figuratively) impoverishment: dishonor.
or marom; from עָרֹם (in its original sense); nude, either partially or totally: naked.
passive participle of עָרֹם; cunning (usually in a bad sense): crafty, prudent, subtil.
or sarear; from עָרַר reduplicated; a juniper (from its nudity of situation): health.
or `Aro`er; or `Ar`owr; the same as עֲרוֹעֵר; nudity of situation; Aroer, the name of three places in or near Palestine: Aroer.
passive participle of עָרַץ; feared, i.e. (concretely) a horrible place or chasm: cliffs.
from עוּר; watchful; Eri, an Israelite: Eri.
patronymically of עֵרִי; a Erite (collectively) or descendants of Eri: Erites.
for עֶרְוָה; nudity: bare, naked, X quite.
from an unused root meaning to comminute; meal: dough.
from עָרַף; the sky (as dropping at the horizon): heaven.
from עָרַץ; fearful, i.e. powerful or tyrannical: mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent.
from עָרַר; bare, i.e. destitute (of children): childless.

a primitive root; to set in a row, i.e. arrange, put in order (in a very wide variety of applications): put (set) (the battle, self) in array, compare, direct, equal, esteem, estimate, expert (in war), furnish, handle, join (battle), ordain, (lay, put, reckon up, set) (in) order, prepare, tax, value.
from עָרַך; a pile, equipment, estimate: equal, estimation, (things that are set in) order, price, proportion, X set at, suit, taxation, X valuest.

a primitive root; properly, to strip; but used as denominative from עָרֵל; to expose or remove the prepuce, whether literal (to go naked) or figurative (to refrain from using): count uncircumcised, foreskin to be uncovered.
rom עָרֵל; properly, exposed, i.e. projecting loose (as to the prepuce); used only technically, uncircumcised (i.e. still having the prepuce uncurtailed): uncircumcised (person).
feminine of עָרֵל; the prepuce: foreskin, + uncircumcised.

a primitive root; properly, to be (or make) bare; but used only in the derivative sense (through the idea perhaps of smoothness) to be cunning (usually in a bad sense): X very, beware, take crafty (counsel), be prudent, deal subtilly.
a primitive root; to pile up: gather together.
from עָרֹם; a stratagem: craftiness.
(Jer. 50:26) or (feminine) aremah; from עָרַם; a heap; specifically, a sheaf: heap (of corn), sheaf.
feminine of עֹ֫רֶם; trickery; or (in a good sense) discretion: guile, prudence, subtilty, wilily, wisdom.
probably from עָרֹם; the plane tree (from its smooth and shed bark): chestnut tree.
probably from עוּר; watchful; Eran, an Israelite: Eran.
patronymically from עֵרָן; an Eranite or descendant (collectively) of Eran: Eranites.
from עָרַר; naked, i.e. (figuratively) poor: destitute. See also עֲרוֹעֵר.
patronymically from עַרְעוֹר; an Aroerite or inhabitant of Aroer: Aroerite.
a primitive root; to droop; hence, to drip: drop (down).

a primitive root (identical with עָרַף through the idea of sloping); properly, to bend downward; but used only as a denominative from עֹ֫רֶף, to break the neck; hence (figuratively) to destroy: that is beheaded, break down, break (cut off, strike off) neck.
from עָרַף; the nape or back of the neck (as declining); hence, the back generally (whether literal or figurative)back ((stiff-)neck((-ed).
feminine of עֹ֫רֶף; mane; Orpah, a Moabites: Orpah.
probably from עָרַף; gloom (as of a lowering sky): (gross, thick) dark (cloud, -ness).
a primitive root; to awe or (intransitive) to dread; hence, to harass: be affrighted (afraid, dread, feared, terrified), break, dread, fear, oppress, prevail, shake terribly.
a primitive root; to gnaw, i.e. (figuratively) eat (by hyberbole); also (participle) a pain: fleeing, sinew.
patrial from an unused name meaning a tush; an Arkite or inhabitant of Erek: Arkite.
a primitive root; to bare; figuratively, to demolish: make bare, break, raise up (perhaps by clerical error for raze), X utterly.
from an unused root meaning perhaps to arch; a couch (properly, with a canopy): bed(-stead), couch.
from עָשֵׁשׁ; a moth: moth. See also עָשׁ.
from an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green); grass (or any tender shoot): grass, herb.

a primitive root; to do or make, in the broadest sense and widest application (as follows): accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow, bring forth, bruise, be busy, X certainly, have the charge of, commit, deal (with), deck, + displease, do, (ready) dress(-ed), (put in) execute(-ion), exercise, fashion, + feast, (fight-)ing man, + finish, fit, fly, follow, fulfill, furnish, gather, get, go about, govern, grant, great, + hinder, hold ((a feast)), X indeed, + be industrious, + journey, keep, labour, maintain, make, be meet, observe, be occupied, offer, + officer, pare, bring (come) to pass, perform, pracise, prepare, procure, provide, put, requite, X sacrifice, serve, set, shew, X sin, spend, X surely, take, X thoroughly, trim, X very, + vex, be (warr-)ior, work(-man), yield, use.
from עָשָׂה and אֵל; God has made; Asahel, the name of four Israelites: Asahel.
apparently a form of the passive participle of עָשָׂה in the original sense of handling; rough (i.e. sensibly felt); Esav, a son of Isaac, including his posterity: Esau.
from עָשַׁק; oppressive (as noun, a tyrant): oppressor.
or mashuq; passive participle of עָשַׁק; used in plural masculine as abstractly, tyranny: oppressed(-ion). (Doubtful.)
or masor; from עָ֫שֶׂר; ten; by abbrev. ten strings, and so a decachord: (instrument of) ten (strings, -th).
from עָשַׁת; shining, i.e. polished: bright.
for עָשׁוֹת; bright; Ashvath, an Israelite: Ashvath.
from עָשָׂה and אֵל; made of God; Asiel, an Israelite: Asiel.
from עָשָׂה and יָהּ; Jah has made; Asajah, the name of three or four Israelites: Asaiah.
from עָשַׁר; rich, whether literal or figurative (noble): rich (man).
from עָ֫שֶׂר; tenth; by abbreviation, tenth month or (feminine) part: tenth (part).
a primitive root; to smoke, whether literal or figurative: be angry (be on a) smoke.
from עָשַׁן; smoky: smoking.
from עָשַׁן; smoke, literally or figuratively (vapor, dust, anger): smoke(-ing).
the same as עָשָׁן; Ashan, a place in Palestine: Ashan.
a primitive root (identical with עָשַׁק); to press upon, i.e. quarrel; --strive with.
from עָשַׂק; strife: Esek.
a primitive root (compare עָשַׂק); to press upon, i.e. oppress, defraud, violate, overflow: get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, (use) oppress((-ion)), -or), do violence (wrong).
from עָשַׁק; oppression; Eshek, an Israelite: Eshek.
from עָשַׁק; injury, fraud, (subjectively) distress, (concretely) unjust gain: cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing (deceitfully gotten).
feminine of עֹ֫שֶׁק; anguish: oppressed.
masculine of term aasarah; from עָשַׂר; ten (as an accumulation to the extent of the digits): ten, (fif-, seven-)teen.
(Aramaic) masculine aasrah (Aramaic); corresponding to עָ֫שֶׂר; ten: ten, + twelve.

a primitive root (ident. with עָשַׁר); to accumulate; but used only as denominative from עָ֫שֶׂר; to tithe, i.e. to take or give a tenth: X surely, give (take) the tenth, (have, take) tithe(-ing, -s), X truly.
a primitive root; properly, to accumulate; chiefly (specifically) to grow (causatively, make) rich: be(-come, en-, make, make self, wax) rich, make (1 Kings 22:48 marg). See עָשָׂר.
from עָשַׁר; wealth: X far (richer), riches.
for עָ֫שֶׂר; ten (only in combination), i.e. -teen; also (ordinal) -teenth: (eigh-, fif-, four-, nine-, seven-, six-, thir-)teen(-th), + eleven(-th), + sixscore thousand, + twelve(-th).
or oissaron; from עָ֫שֶׂר; (fractional) a tenth part: tenth deal.
from עָ֫שֶׂר; twenty; also (ordinal) twentieth: (six-)score, twenty(-ieth).
(Aramaic) corresponding to עֶשְׂרִים: twenty.
a primitive root; probably to shrink, i.e. fail: be consumed.
a primitive root; probably to be sleek, i.e. glossy; hence (through the idea of polishing) to excogitate (as if forming in the mind): shine, think.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָשַׁת; to purpose: think.
from עָשַׁת; a fabric: bright.
from עָשַׁת; cogitation: thought.
apparently masculine plural construction of עֶ֫שֶׁת in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with עָשָׂר in lieu of אֶחָד) eleven or (ordinal) eleventh: + eleven(-th).
from עָשַׁת; thinking: thought.
probably from עָשַׁר; increase: flock.

or Ashtaroth; plural of עַשְׁתְּרוֹת; Ashtaroth, the name of a Sidonian deity, and of a place East of the Jordan: Asharoth, Astaroth. See also בֵּית עַשְׁתָּרוֹת, עַשְׁתֹּ֫רֶת, עַשְׁתְּרֹת קַרְנַ֫יִם.
probably for עַשְׁתְּרוֹת; Ashtoreth, the Phoenician goddess of love (and increase): Ashtoreth.
patrial from עַשְׁתָּרוֹת; an Ashterathite or inhabitant of Ashtaroth: Ashterathite.
from עַשְׁתָּרוֹת and the dual of קָ֫רֶן; Ashtaroth of (the) double horns (a symbol of the deity); Ashteroth-Karnaim, a place East of the Jordan: Ashtoreth Karnaim.

from עַד; time, especially (adverb with preposition) now, when, etc.: + after, (al-)ways, X certain, + continually, + evening, long, (due) season, so (long) as, (even-, evening-, noon-)tide, ((meal-)), what) time, when.
a primitive root; to prepare: make fit, be ready to become.
from עֵת; at this time, whether adverb, conjunction or expletive: henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas.
passive participle of עָתַד; prepared: ready.
or sattud; from עָתַד; prepared, i.e. full grown; spoken only (in plural) of he-goats, or (figuratively) leaders of the people: chief one, (he) goat, ram.
from עֵת; timely: fit.
for עִתִּי; Attai, the name of three Israelites: Attai.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָתִיד; prepared: ready.
from עָתַד; prepared; by implication, skilful; feminine plural the future; also treasure: things that shall come, ready, treasures.
from עוּת and יָהּ; Jah has helped; Athajah, an Israelite: Athaiah.
from עָתַק; properly, antique, i.e. venerable or splendid: durable.
from עָתַק; removed, i.e. weaned; also antique: ancient, drawn.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עַתִּיקִים; venerable: ancient.
from an unused root meaning to sojourn; lodging; Athak, a place in Palestine: Athach.
from an unused root meaning to compress; constringent; Athlai, an Israelite: Athlai.
or Athalyahuw; from the same as עַתְלָי and יָהּ; Jah has constrained; Athaljah, the name of an Israelitess and two Israelites: Athaliah.
a primitive root; probably to glow, i.e. (figuratively) be desolated: be darkened.
from an unused root meaning to force; forcible; Othni, an Israelite: Othni.
from the same as עָתְנִי and אֵל; force of God; Othniel, an Israelite: Othniel.
a primitive root; to remove (intransitive or transitive) figuratively, to grow old; specifically, to transcribe: copy out, leave off, become (wax) old, remove.
from עָתַק; antique, i.e. valued: durable.
from עָתַק in the sense of license; impudent: arrogancy, grievous (hard) things, stiff.
from עֵת and קַיָּם; time of a judge; Eth-Katsin, a place in Palestine: Ittah-kazin (by including directive enclitic).
a primitive root (rather denominative from עֶ֫תֶר); to burn incense in worship, i.e. intercede (reciprocally, listen to prayer): intreat, (make) pray(-er).
a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) abundant: deceitful, multiply.
from עָתַר; abundance; Ether, a place in Palestine: Ether.
from עָתַר; incense (as increasing to a volume of smoke); hence (from עָתַר) a worshipper: suppliant, thick.
from עָתַר; copiousness: abundance.
a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow away: scatter into corners.
feminine of פֹּה; properly, mouth in a figurative sense, i.e. direction, region, extremity: corner, end, quarter, side.

a primitive root; to gleam, i.e. (causatively) embellish; figuratively, to boast; also to explain (i.e. make clear) oneself; denominative from פֻּארָה, to shake a tree: beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify (self), glory, vaunt self.
from פָּאַר; an embellishment, i.e. fancy head-dress: beauty, bonnet, goodly, ornament, tire.
or pora'h; or pu'rah; from פָּאַר; properly, ornamentation, i.e. (plural) foliage (including the limbs) as bright green: bough, branch, sprig.
from פָּאַר; properly, illuminated, i.e. a glow; as noun, a flush (of anxiety): blackness.
from פָּאַר; ornamental; Paran, a desert of Arabia: Paran.
from an unused root meaning to be torpid, i.e. crude; an unripe fig: green fig.
or piggul; from an unused root meaning to stink; properly, fetid, i.e. (figuratively) unclean (ceremonially): abominable(-tion, thing).

a primitive root; to impinge, by accident or violence, or (figuratively) by importunity: come (betwixt), cause to entreat, fall (upon), make intercession, intercessor, intreat, lay, light (upon), meet (together), pray, reach, run.
from פָּגַע; impact (casual): chance, occurent.
from פֶּ֫גַע and אֵל; accident of God; Pagiel, an Israelite: Pagiel.
a primitive root; to relax, i.e. become exhausted: be faint.
from פָּגַר; a carcase (as limp), whether of man or beast; figuratively, an idolatrous image: carcase, corpse, dead body.
a primitive root; to come in contact with, whether by accident or violence; figuratively, to concur: meet (with, together).
a primitive root; to sever, i.e. ransom; gener. to release, preserve: X at all, deliver, X by any means, ransom, (that are to be, let be) redeem(-ed), rescue, X surely.
from פָּדָה and אֵל; God has ransomed; Pedahel, an Israelite: Pedahel.
from פָּדָה and צוּר; a rock (i.e. God) has ransomed; Pedahtsur, an Israelite: Pedahzur.
passive participle of פָּדָה. ransomed (and so occurring under פָּדָה); as abstractly (in plural masculine) a ransom: (that are) to be (that were) redeemed.
from פָּדָה; ransom; Padon, one of the Nethinim. -- Padon.
or pduth; from קֵ֫דְמָה; distinction; also deliverance: division, redeem, redemption.
or Pdayahuw; from פָּדָה and יָהּ; Jah has ransomed; Pedajah, the name of six Israelites: Pedaiah.
or pidyom; also pidyown; or pidyon; from פָּדָה; a ransom; --ransom, that were redeemed, redemption.
from an unused root meaning to extend; a plateau; or Paddan Aram; from the same and אֲרָם; the table-land of Aram; Paddan or Paddan-Aram, a region of Syria: Padan, Padan-aram.
a primitive root; to retrieve: deliver.
from an unused root meaning to be greasy; suet: fat.

from פָּאָה; the mouth (as the means of blowing), whether literal or figurative (particularly speech); specifically edge, portion or side; adverbially (with preposition) according to: accord(-ing as, -ing to), after, appointment, assent, collar, command(-ment), X eat, edge, end, entry, + file, hole, X in, mind, mouth, part, portion, X (should) say(-ing), sentence, skirt, sound, speech, X spoken, talk, tenor, X to, + two-edged, wish, word.

or po6 (Job 38:11); or pow; probably from a primitive inseparable particle "p" (of demonstrative force) and הוּא; this place (French ici), i.e. here or hence: here, hither, the one (other, this, that) side.
or Puvvah; from פָּאָה; a blast; Puah or Puvvah, the name of two Israelites: Phuvah, Pua, Puah.
a primitive root; to be sluggish: cease, be feeble, faint, be slacked.
from פּוּג; intermission: rest.
a primitive root; to puff, i.e. blow with the breath or air; hence, to fan (as a breeze), to utter, to kindle (a fire), to scoff: blow (upon), break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter.
of foreign origin; Put, a son of Ham, also the name of his descendants or their region, and of a Persian tribe: Phut, Put.
from an unused root (probably meaning to disparage) and אֵל; contempt of God; Putiel, an Israelite: Putiel.
of Egyptian derivation: Potiphar, an Egyptian: Potiphar.
of Egyptian derivation; Poti-Phera, an Egyptian: Poti-pherah.
from an unused root meaning to paint; dye (specifically, stibium for the eyes): fair colours, glistering, paint(-ed) (-ing).
from an unused root meaning to be thick; a bean (as plump): beans.
of foreign origin; Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe: Pul.
a primitive root meaning to turn, i.e. be perplexed: be distracted.
patronymically from an unused name meaning a turn; a Punite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Pun: Punites.
from פּוּן; perplexity; Punon, a place in the Desert: Punon.
from an unused root meaning to glitter; brilliancy; Puah, an Israelitess: Puah.

a primitive root; to dash in pieces, literally or figuratively (especially to disperse): break (dash, shake) in (to) pieces, cast (abroad), disperse (selves), drive, retire, scatter (abroad), spread abroad.
a primitive root; to waver: stumble, move.

a primitive root (identical with פִּיק through the idea of dropping out; compare נְפַק); to issue, i.e. furnish; causatively, to secure; figuratively, to succeed: afford, draw out, further, get, obtain.
from פִּיק; a stumbling-block: grief.
a primitive root; to crush: break, bring to nought, X utterly take.
also (plural) Puwriym; or Puriym; from פּוּר; a lot (as by means of a broken piece): Pur, Purim.
from פּוּר; a wine-press (as crushing the grapes): winepress.
of Persian origin; Poratha, a son of Haman: Poratha.
a primitive root; to spread; figuratively, act proudly: grow up, be grown fat, spread selves, be scattered.
patronymically from an unused name meaning a hinge; a Puthite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Puth: Puhites (as if from Puw'ah).
from פָּזַז; pure (gold); hence, gold itself (as refined): fine (pure) gold.
a primitive root; to refine (gold): best (gold).
a primitive root (identical with פָּזַז); to solidify (as if by refining); also to spring (as if separating the limbs): leap, be made strong.
a primitive root; to scatter, whether in enmity or bounty: disperse, scatter (abroad).
from פָּחַח; a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina): gin, (thin) plate, snare.
a primitive root; to be startled (by a sudden alarm); hence, to fear in general: be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake.
from פָּחַד; a (sudden) alarm (properly, the object feared, by implication, the feeling): dread(-ful), fear, (thing) great (fear, -ly feared), terror.
the same as פַּ֫חַד; a testicle (as a cause of shame akin to fear): stone.
feminine of פַּ֫חַד; alarm (i.e. awe): fear.
of foreign origin; a prefect (of a city or small district): captain, deputy, governor.
(Aramaic) corresponding to פַּח: captain, governor.
a primitive root; to bubble up or froth (as boiling water), i.e. (figuratively) to be unimportant: light.
from פָּחַז; ebullition, i.e. froth (figuratively, lust): unstable.
from פָּחַז; frivolity: lightness.
a primitive root; to batter out; but used only as denominative from פָּח, to spread a net: be snared.
perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be black; a coal, whether charred or live: coals.
(Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning to fashion; a potter: potter.
probably from an unused root apparently meaning to dig; a pit, especially for catching animals: hole, pit, snare.
from פַּ֫חַת and מוֹאָב; pit of Moab; Pachath-Moab, an Israelite: Pahath-moab.
from the same as פַּ֫חַת; a hole (by mildew in a garment): fret inward.
of foreign derivation; a gem, probably the topaz: topaz.
passive participle of פָּטַר; opened, i.e. (as noun) a bud: open.
from פָּטַר; open, i.e. unoccupied: free.
intensively from an unused root meaning to pound; a hammer: hammer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of פַּטִּישׁ; a gown (as if hammered out wide): hose.
a primitive root; to cleave or burst through, i.e. (causatively) to emit, whether literal or figurative (gape): dismiss, free, let (shoot) out, slip away.
or pitrah; from פָּטַר; a fissure, i.e. (concretely) firstling (as opening the matrix): firstling, openeth, such as open.
of Egyptian origin; Pi-Beseth, a place in Egypt: Pi-beseth.
from an unused root probably meaning to pierce; (figuratively) misfortune: destruction, ruin.
or piyah; feminine of פֶּה; an edge(two-)edge(-d).

from פֶּה and the feminine plural of a noun (from the same root as חֹר), with the article interpolated; mouth of the gorges; Pi-ha-Chiroth, a place in Egypt: Pi-hahiroth. (In Numbers 14:19 without Pi-.)
from פּ֫וּחַ; a powder (as easily puffed away), i.e. ashes or dust: ashes.
apparently from פֶּה and כֹּל; mouth of all; Picol, a Philistine: Phichol.
or pilegesh; of uncertain derivation; a concubine; also (masculine) a paramour: concubine, paramour.
probably from an unused root meaning to be plump; obesity: collops.
apparently from פֶּה and a variation of נָחָשׁ; mouth of a serpent; Pinechas, the name of three Israelites: Phinehas.
probably the same as פּוּנֹן; Pinon, an Idumaean: Pinon.
for פֵּיוֹת; an edge or tooth: tooth, X two-edged.
from פּוּק; a tottering: smite together.
from פּוּשׁ; dispersive; Pishon, a river of Eden: Pison.
probably from the same as פּוֹת; expansive; Pithon, an Israelite: Pithon.
from פָּכָה; a flask (from which a liquid may flow): box, vial.
a primitive root; to pour: run out.

from the active participle (of the same form as the first word) feminine of an unused root (meaning to entrap) and plural of צֶ֫בִי; trap of gazelles; Pokereth-Tsebajim, one of the "servants of Solomon": Pochereth of Zebaim.

a primitive root; properly, perhaps to separate, i.e. distinguish (literally or figuratively); by implication, to be (causatively, make) great, difficult, wonderful: accomplish, (arise...too, be too) hard, hidden, things too high, (be, do, do a, shew) marvelous(-ly, -els, things, work), miracles, perform, separate, make singular, (be, great, make) wonderful(-ers, -ly, things, works), wondrous (things, works, -ly).
from פָּלָא; a miracle: marvellous thing, wonder(-ful, -fully).
or paliy1; from פָּלָא; remarkable: secret, wonderful.
patronymically from פַּלּוּא; a Palluite (collectively) or descendants of Pallu: Palluites.
a primitive root; to split (literally or figuratively): divide.
(Aramaic) corresponding to פָּלַג: divided.
(Aramaic) from פְּלַג; a half: dividing.
from פָּלַג; a rill (i.e. small channel of water, as in irrigation): river, stream.
the same as פֶּ֫לֶג; earthquake; Peleg, a son of Shem: Peleg.
from פָּלַג; a runlet, i.e. gully: division, river.
from פָּלַג; a section: division.
(Aramaic) corresponding to פְּלֻגּוֹת: division.
from an unused root meaning to divide; a cleaver, i.e. iron armature (of a chariot): torch.
of uncertain derivation; Pildash, a relative of Abraham: Pildash.
a primitive root; to distinguish (literally or figuratively): put a difference, show marvellous, separate, set apart, sever, make wonderfully.
from פָּלָה; distinguished; Pallu, an Israelite: Pallu, Phallu.
patronymically from an unused name (from פָּלָה) meaning separate; a Pelonite or inhabitant of an unknown PalonPelonite.
a primitive root; to slice, i.e. break open or pierce: bring forth, cleave, cut, shred, strike through.
(Aramaic) corresponding to פָּלַח; to serve or worship: minister, serve.
from פָּלַח; a slice: piece.
from פֶּ֫לַח; slicing; Pilcha, an Israelite: Pilcha.
(Aramaic) from פְּלַח; worship: service.
a primitive root; to slip out, i.e. escape; causatively, to deliver: calve, carry away safe, deliver, (cause to) escape.
from פָּלַט; escape; Pelet, the name of two Israelites: Pelet. See also בֵּית פֶּ֫לֶט.
from פָּלַט; escape: deliverance, escape.
from פָּלַט; delivered; Palti, the name of two Israelites: Palti, Phalti.
patronymically from פַּלְטִי; a Paltite or descendant of Palti: Paltite.
for פַּלְטִי; Piltai, an Israelite: Piltai.
from the same as פָּ֫לֶט and אֵל; deliverance of God; Paltiel, the name of two Israelites: Paltiel, Phaltiel.
or Platyahuw; from פָּלַט and יָהּ; Jah has delivered; Pelatjah, the name of four Israelites: Pelatiah.
or Pla.yah; from פָּלָא and יָהּ; Jah has distinguished; Pelajah, the name of three Israelites: Pelaiah.
or paleyt; or palet; from פָּלַט; a refugee: (that have) escape(-d, -th), fugitive.
or pletah; feminine of פָּלִיט; deliverance; concretely, an escaped portion: deliverance, (that is) escape(-d), remnant.
from פָּלַל; a magistrate: judge.
feminine of פְּלִילִים; justice: judgment.
from פְּלִילִים; judicial: judge.
feminine of פְּלִילִי; judicature: judgment.
from an unused root meaning to be round; a circuit (i.e. district); also a spindle (as whirled); hence, a crutch:--(di-)staff, participle
a primitive root; to judge (officially or mentally); by extension, to intercede, pray: intreat, judge(-ment), (make) pray(-er, -ing), make supplication.
from פָּלַל; judge; Palal, an Israelite: Palal.
from פָּלַל and יָהּ; Jah has judged; Pelaljah, an Israelite: Pelaliah.
probably for פְּלֹנִי; a certain one, i.e. so-and-so: certain.
from פָּלָה; such a one, i.e. a specified peccrson: such.
a primitive root; properly, to roll flat, i.e. prepare (a road); also to revolve, i.e. weigh (mentally): make, ponder, weigh.
from פָּלַס; a balance: scales, weight.
a primitive root; properly, perhaps to rend, i.e. (by implication) to quiver: tremble.
from פָּלַץ; affright: fearfulness, horror, trembling.
a primitive root; to roll (in dust): roll (wallow) self.
from פָּלַשׁ; rolling, i.e. migratory; Pelesheth, a region of Syria: Palestina, Palestine, Philistia, Philistines.
patrial from פְּלָ֫שֶׁת; a Pelishtite or inhabitant of Pelesheth: Philistine.
from an unused root meaning to flee; swiftness; Peleth, the name of two Israelites: Peleth.
from the same form as פֶּ֫לֶת; a courier (collectively) or official messenger: Pelethites.
(Aramaic) probably for פֶּה; the mouth (literally or figuratively): mouth.
from an unused root meaning to turn; an angle (of a street or wall): corner.
from פָּנָה; properly, removal; used only (in the construction) adverb as conjunction, lest: (lest) (peradventure), that...not.
of uncertain derivation; probably pastry: Pannag.

a primitive root; to turn; by implication, to face, i.e. appear, look, etc.: appear, at (even-)tide, behold, cast out, come on, X corner, dawning, empty, go away, lie, look, mark, pass away, prepare, regard, (have) respect (to), (re-)turn (aside, away, back, face, self), X right (early).
feminine of פֵּן; an angle; by implication, a pinnacle; figuratively, a chieftain: bulwark, chief, corner, stay, tower.
or (more properly,) Pniylel; from פָּנָה and אֵל; face of God; Penuel or Peniel, a place East of Jordan; also (as Penuel) the name of two Israelites: Peniel, Penuel.

plural (but always as singular) of an unused noun paneh from פָּנָה; the face (as the part that turns); used in a great variety of applications (literally and figuratively); also (with prepositional prefix) as a preposition (before, etc.): + accept, a-(be-)fore(-time), against, anger, X as (long as), at, + battle, + because (of), + beseech, countenance, edge, + employ, endure, + enquire, face, favour, fear of, for, forefront(-part), form(-er time, -ward), from, front, heaviness, X him(-self), + honourable, + impudent, + in, it, look(-eth) (- s), X me, + meet, X more than, mouth, of, off, (of) old (time), X on, open, + out of, over against, the partial, person, + please, presence, propect, was purposed, by reason of, + regard, right forth, + serve, X shewbread, sight, state, straight, + street, X thee, X them(-selves), through (+ - out), till, time(-s) past, (un-)to(-ward), + upon, upside (+ down), with(- in, + -stand), X ye, X you.
from פָּנִים with directive enclitic; faceward, i.e. indoors: (with-)in(-ner part, -ward).
from פָּנִים; interior: (with-)in(-ner, - ward).
or paniy; from the same as פֵּן; probably a pearl (as round): ruby.
probably feminine from פְּנִינִים contr.; Peninnah, an Israelitess: Peninnah.
a primitive root; to enervate: bring up.

from פָּסַס; properly, the palm (of the hand) or sole (of the foot) (compare פַּס); by implication (plural) a long and sleeved tunic (perhaps simply a wide one; from the original sense of the root, i.e. of many breadths): (divers) colours.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to פָּסַס; the palm (of the hand, as being spread out):--participle
a primitive root; to cut up, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate: consider.
from פָּסַג; a cleft; Pisgah, a mt. East of Jordan: Pisgah.
from פַּסִּים and the plural of דָּם; palm (i.e. dell) of bloodshed; Pas-Dammim, a place in Palestine: Pas-dammim. Compare אֶ֫פֶס דַּמִּים.
from פָּסַס; expansion, i.e. abundance: handful.
a primitive root; to hop, i.e. (figuratively) skip over (or spare); by implication, to hesitate; also (literally) to limp, to dance: halt, become lame, leap, pass over.
from פָּסַח; a pretermission, i.e. exemption; used only techically of the Jewish Passover (the festival or the victim): passover (offering).
from פָּסַח; limping; Paseach, the name of two Israelites: Paseah, Phaseah.
from פָּסַח; lame: lame.
from פָּסַל; an idol: carved (graven) image, quarry.
from an unused root meaning to divide; divider; Pasak, an Israelite: Pasach.
a primitive root; to carve, whether wood or stone: grave, hew.
from פָּסַל; an idol: carved (graven) image.
(Aramaic) or pcanteriyn (Aramaic); a transliteration of the Gr. psalterion; a lyre: psaltery.
a primitive root; probably to disperse, i.e. (intransitive) disappear: cease.
perhaps from פָּסַס; dispersion; Pispah, an Israelite: Pispah.
a primitive root; to scream: cry.
or Pamiy; from פָּעָה; screaming; Pau or Pai, a place in Edom: Pai, Pau.
from פָּעַר; a gap; Peor, a mountain East of Jordan; also (for בַּ֫עַל פְּעוֹר) a deity worshipped there: Peor. See also בֵּית פְּעוֹר.
a primitive root; to do or make (systematically and habitually), especially to practise: commit, (evil-) do(-er), make(-r), ordain, work(-er).
from פָּעַל; an act or work (concretely): act, deed, do, getting, maker, work.
feminine passive participle of פָּעַל; (abstractly) work: labour, reward, wages, work.
from פְּעֻלַּת; laborious; Peullethai, an Israelite: Peulthai.
a primitive root; to tap, i.e. beat regularly; hence (generally) to impel or agitate: move, trouble.

or (feminine) pa`amah; from פָּעַם; a stroke, literally or figuratively (in various applications, as follow): anvil, corner, foot(-step), going, (hundred-)fold, X now, (this) + once, order, rank, step, + thrice, ((often-)), second, this, two) time(-s), twice, wheel.
from פָּ֫עַם; a bell (as struck): bell.
a primitive root; to yawn, i.e. open wide (literally or figuratively): gape, open (wide).
from פָּעַר; yawning; Paarai, an Israelite: Paarai.
a primitive root; to rend, i.e. open (especially the mouth): deliver, gape, open, rid, utter.
a primitive root; to break out (in joyful sound): break (forth, forth into joy), make a loud noise.
from פָּצַר; bluntness: + file.
a primitive root; to peel: pill.
from פָּצַל; a peeling: strake.
a primitive root; to rend (by earthquake): break.
a primitive root; to split, i.e. wound: wound.
from פָּצַע; a wound: wound(-ing).
from an unused root meaning to dissever; dispersive; Pitstsets, a priest: Apses (including the article).
a primitive root; to peck at, i.e. (figuratively) stun or dull: press, urge, stubbornness.

a primitive root; to visit (with friendly or hostile intent); by analogy, to oversee, muster, charge, care for, miss, deposit, etc.: appoint, X at all, avenge, bestow, (appoint to have the, give a) charge, commit, count, deliver to keep, be empty, enjoin, go see, hurt, do judgment, lack, lay up, look, make, X by any means, miss, number, officer, (make) overseer, have (the) oversight, punish, reckon, (call to) remember(-brance), set (over), sum, X surely, visit, want.
