(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to רָאָה; aspect: form.
a primitive root; to tramp about, i.e. ramble (free or disconsolate): have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule.
a primitive root; to slake the thirst (occasionally of other appetites): bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly).
from רָוָה; sated (with drink): drunkenness, watered.
from an unused root probably meaning to cry out; outcry; Rohagah, an Israelite: Rohgah.
a primitive root (identical with ר֫וּחַ); properly, to breathe freely, i.e. revive; by implication, to have ample room: be refreshed, large.
from רָוַח; room, literally (an interval) or figuratively (deliverance): enlargement, space.
a primitive root; properly, to blow, i.e. breathe; only (literally) to smell or (by implication, perceive (figuratively, to anticipate, enjoy): accept, smell, X touch, make of quick understanding.

from ר֫וּחַ; wind; by resemblance breath, i.e. a sensible (or even violent) exhalation; figuratively, life, anger, unsubstantiality; by extension, a region of the sky; by resemblance spirit, but only of a rational being (including its expression and functions): air, anger, blast, breath, X cool, courage, mind, X quarter, X side, spirit((-ual)), tempest, X vain, ((whirl-))wind(-y).
(Aramaic) corresponding to ר֫וּחַ: mind, spirit, wind.
feminine of רֶ֫וַח; relief: breathing, respite.
from רָוָה; satisfaction: runneth over, wealthy.

a primitive root; to be high actively, to rise or raise (in various applications, literally or figuratively): bring up, exalt (self), extol, give, go up, haughty, heave (up), (be, lift up on, make on, set up on, too) high(-er, one), hold up, levy, lift(-er) up, (be) lofty, (X a-)loud, mount up, offer (up), + presumptuously, (be) promote(-ion), proud, set up, tall(-er), take (away, off, up), breed worms.
or rum; from רוּם; (literally) elevation or (figuratively) elation: haughtiness, height, X high.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רוּם; (figuratively only)extol, lift up (self), set up.
(Aramaic) from רוּם; (literally) altitude: height.
from רוּם; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) aloft: on high.
from רוּם; height; Rumah, a place in Palestine: Rumah.
feminine of רוֹם; elation, i.e. (adverbially) proudly: haughtily.
from רָמַם; exaltation, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) praise: be extolled.
feminine active participle of רָמַם; exaltation, i.e. praise: high.
(or Romam from רוּם and עֵ֫זֶר; I have raised up a help; Romamti-Ezer, an Israelite: Romamti- ezer.

a primitive root; to mar (especially by breaking); figuratively, to split the ears (with sound), i.e. shout (for alarm or joy): blow an alarm, cry (alarm, aloud, out), destroy, make a joyful noise, smart, shout (for joy), sound an alarm, triumph.
a primitive root; properly, to triturate (in a mortar), i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (by concussion): tremble.
a primitive root; to run (for whatever reason, especially to rush): break down, divide speedily, footman, guard, bring hastily, (make) run (away, through), post.
a primitive root; to pour out (literally or figuratively), i.e. empty: X arm, cast out, draw (out), (make) empty, pour forth (out).
a primitive root; to slaver (with spittle), i.e. (by analogy) to emit a fluid (ulcerous or natural): run.
a primitive root; to be destitute: lack, needy, (make self) poor (man).
probably for רְעוּת; friend; Ruth, a Moabitess: Ruth.
(Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning to attenuate, i.e. (figuratively) hide; a mystery: secret.
a primitive root; to emaciate, i.e. make (become) thin (literally or figuratively): famish, wax lean.
from רָזָה; thin: lean.
from רָזַן; prince; Rezon, a Syrian: Rezon.
from רָזָה; thinness: leanness, X scant.
from רָזַן; a dignitary: prince.
from רָזָה; thinness: leanness.
a primitive root; to twinkle the eye (in mockery): wink.
a primitive root; probably to be heavy, i.e. (figuratively) honorable: prince, ruler.
a primitive root; to broaden (intransitive or transitive, literal or figurative): be an en-(make) large(-ing), make room, make (open) wide.
from רָחַב; a width: breadth, broad place.
or rchowb; from רָחַב; a width, i.e. (concretely) avenue or area: broad place (way), street. See also בֵּית רְחוֹב.
or Rchowb; the same as רְחוֹב; Rechob, the name of a place in Syria, also of a Syrian and an Israelite: Rehob.
from רָחַב; width (literally or figuratively): breadth, broad, largeness, thickness, wideness.
from רָחַב; roomy, in any (or every) direction, literally or figuratively: broad, large, at liberty, proud, wide.
the same as רָחָב; proud; Rachab, a Canaanitess: Rahab.
or Rchoboth; plural of רְחוֹב; streets; Rechoboth, a place in Assyria and one in PalestineRehoboth.
or Rchabyahuw; from רָחַב and יָהּ; Jah has enlarged; Rechabjah, an Israelite: Rehabiah.
from רָחַב and עָם; a people has enlarged; Rechabam, an Israelite king: Rehoboam.
from an unused root meaning to pulverize; a mill-stone: mill (stone).
a form of רַחוּם; Rechum, the name of a Persian and of three Israelites: Rehum.
from רָחַם; compassionate: full of compassion, merciful.

or rachoq; from רָחַק; remote, literally or figuratively, of place or time; specifically, precious; often used adverbially (with preposition): (a-)far (abroad, off), long ago, of old, space, great while to come.
from the same as רְהָטִים; a panel (as resembling a trough): rafter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָחוֹק: far.
from an unused root meaning to journey; a ewe (the females being the predominant element of a flock) (as a good traveller): ewe, sheep.
the same as רָחֵל; Rachel, a wife of Jacob: Rachel.
a primitive root; to fondle; by implication, to love, especially to compassionate: have compassion (on, upon), love, (find, have, obtain, shew) mercy(-iful, on, upon), (have) pity, Ruhamah, X surely.
from רָחַם; compassion (in the plural); by extension, the womb (as cherishing the fetus); by implication, a maidenbowels, compassion, damsel, tender love, (great, tender) mercy, pity, womb.
the same as רָ֫חַם; pity; Racham, an Israelite: Raham.
from רָחַם; the womb (compare רָ֫חַם): matrix, womb.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָ֫חַם; (plural) pity: mercy.
or (feminine) rachamah; from רָחַם; a kind of vulture (supposed to be tender towards its young): gier- eagle.
feminine of רָ֫חַם; a maiden: damsel.
from רָחַם; compassionate: pitiful.
a primitive root; to brood; by implication, to be relaxed: flutter, move, shake.
a primitive root; to lave (the whole or a part of a thing): bathe (self), wash (self).
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָחַץ (probably through the accessory idea of ministering as a servant at the bath); to attend upon: trust.
from רָחַץ; a bath: wash(-pot).
feminine of רַ֫חַץ; a bathing place: washing.

a primitive root; to widen (in any direction), i.e. (intransitively) recede or (transitively) remove (literally or figuratively, of place or relation): (a-, be, cast, drive, get, go, keep (self), put, remove, be too, (wander), withdraw) far (away, off), loose, X refrain, very, (be) a good way (off).
from רָחַק; remote: that are far.
a primitive root; to gush: indite.
from ר֫וּחַ; a winnowing-fork (as blowing the chaff away): shovel.
a primitive root; to be moist: be wet.
from רָטַב; moist (with sap): green.
from an unused root meaning to tremble; terror: fear.
a root compounded from רָטֹב and טָפַשׁ; to be rejuvenated: be fresh.
a primitive root; to dash down: dash (in pieces).
from רָוָה; irrigation, i.e. a shower: watering.

or ruwb; a primitive root; properly, to toss, i.e. grapple; mostly figuratively, to wrangle, i.e. hold a controversy; (by implication) to defend: adversary, chide, complain, contend, debate, X ever, X lay wait, plead, rebuke, strive, X thoroughly.
or rib; from רִיב; a contest (personal or legal): + adversary, cause, chiding, contend(-tion), controversy, multitude (from the margin), pleading, strife, strive(-ing), suit.
from רִיב; contentious; Ribai, an Israelite: Ribai.
from ר֫וּחַ; odor (as if blown): savour, scent, smell.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רֵ֫יחַ: smell.
or riphah; from רוּף; (only plural), grits (as pounded): ground corn, wheat.
or (probably by orthographical error) Diyphath; of foreign origin; Riphath, a grandson of Japheth and his descendants: Riphath.
from רִיק; emptiness; figuratively, a worthless thing; adverbially, in vain: empty, to no purpose, (in) vain (thing), vanity.
or (shorter) req; from רִיק; empty; figuratively, worthless: emptied(-ty), vain (fellow, man).
from רֵק; emptily; figuratively (objective) ineffectually, (subjective) undeservedly: without cause, empty, in vain, void.
from רִיר; saliva; by resemblance, broth: spittle, white (of an egg).
or resh; or riysh; from רוּשׁ; poverty: poverty.
from רָכַך; tender (literally or figuratively); by implication, weak: faint((-hearted), soft, tender ((-hearted), one), weak.
from רָכַך; softness (figuratively): tenderness.

a primitive root; to ride (on an animal or in a vehicle); causatively, to place upon (for riding or generally), to despatch: bring (on (horse-)back), carry, get (oneself) up, on (horse-)back, put, (cause to, make to) ride (in a chariot, on, -r), set.
from רָכַב; a vehicle; by implication, a team; by extension, cavalry; by analogy a rider, i.e. the upper millstone: chariot, (upper) millstone, multitude (from the margin), wagon.
from רָכַב; rider; Rekab, the name of two Arabs and of two Israelites: Rechab.
from רָכַב; a charioteer: chariot man, driver of a chariot, horseman.
feminine of רֶ֫כֶב; a chariot (collectively): chariots.
probably feminine from רָכַך; softness; Rekah, a place in Palestine: Rechah.
from passive participle of רָכַב; a vehicle (as ridden on): chariot.
or rkush; from passive participle of רָכַשׁ; property (as gathered): good, riches, substance.
from רָכַל a scandal-monger (as travelling about): slander, carry tales, talebearer.
a primitive root; to soften (intransitively or transitively), used figuratively: (be) faint((-hearted)), mollify, (be, make) soft(-er), be tender.
a primitive root; to travel for trading: (spice) merchant.
from רָכַל; merchant; Rakal, a place in Palestine: Rachal.
feminine passive participle of רָכַל; trade (as peddled): merchandise, traffic.
a primitive root; to tie: bind.
from רָכַס; a mountain ridge (as of tied summits): rough place.
from רָכַס; a snare (as of tied meshes): pride.
a primitive root; to lay up, i.e. collect: gather, get.
from רָכַשׁ; a relay of animals on a post-route (as stored up for that purpose); by implication, a courser: dromedary, mule, swift beast.
active participle of רוּם; high; Ram, the name of an Arabian and of an Israelite: Ram. See also בֵּית הָרָם.
a primitive root; to hurl; specifically, to shoot; figuratively, to delude or betray (as if causing to fall): beguile, betray, (bow-)man, carry, deceive, throw.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָמָה; to throw, set, (figuratively) assess: cast (down), impose.
feminine active participle of רוּם; a height (as a seat of idolatry): high place.
the same as רָמָה; Ramah, the name of four places in Palestine: Ramah.
from רָמַם in the sense of breading (compare רוּם); a maggot (as rapidly bred), literally or figuratively: worm.
or rimmon; from רָמַם; a pomegranate, the tree (from its upright growth) or the fruit (also an artificial ornament): pomegranate.

or (shorter) Rimmon; or Rimmownow (1 Chronicles 6:62 (77)); the same as רִמּוֹן; Rimmon, the name of a Syrian deity, also of five places in Palestine: Remmon, Rimmon. The addition "-methoar" (Josh. 19:13) is ham-mthonar; passive participle of תָּאַר with the article; the (one) marked off, i.e. which pertains; mistaken for part of the name.
or Ramath Negeb; from the plural or construct form of רָמָה and נֶ֫גֶב; heights (or height) of the South; Ramoth-Negeb or Ramath-Negeb, a place in Palestine: south Ramoth, Ramath of the south.
from רוּם; a heap (of carcases): height.
from an unused root meaning to hurl; a lance (as thrown); especially the iron point: buckler, javelin, lancet, spear.
for אֲרַמִּי; a Ramite, i.e. Aramaean: Syrian.
from רוּם and יָהּ; Jah has raised; Ramjah, an Israelite: Ramiah.
from רָמָה; remissness, treachery: deceit(- ful, -fully), false, guile, idle, slack, slothful.
of foreign origin; a brood mare: dromedary.
from an unused root and יָהּ (perhaps meaning to deck); Jah has bedecked; Remaljah, an Israelite: Remaliah.
a primitive root; to rise (literally or figuratively): exalt, get (oneself) up, lift up (self), mount up.
from the active participle of רָמַם; exaltation: lifting up of self.
from רִמּוֹן and פָּ֫רֶץ; pomegranate of the breach; Rimmon-Perets, a place in the Desert: Rimmon-parez.
a primitive root; to tread upon (as a potter, in walking or abusively): oppressor, stamp upon, trample (under feet), tread (down, upon).
a primitive root; properly, to glide swiftly, i.e. to crawl or move with short steps; by analogy to swarm: creep, move.
from רָמַשׂ; a reptile or any other rapidly moving animal: that creepeth, creeping (moving) thing.
from רָמָה; height; Remeth, a place in Palestine: Remeth.
or Ramoth Giliad (2 Chronicles 22:5); from the plural of רָמָה and גִּלְעָד; heights of Gilad; Ramoth-Gilad, a place East of the Jordan: Ramoth-gilead, Ramoth in Gilead. See also רָאמוֹת.
from רָמָה and מִצְפֶּה with the article interpolated; height of the watch-tower; Ramath-ham- Mitspeh, a place in Palestine: Ramath-mizpeh.
patronymic of רָמָה; a Ramathite or inhabitant of Ramah: Ramathite.
from the dual of רָמָה and the plural of the active participle of צָפָה; double height of watchers; Ramathajim-Tsophim, a place in Palestine: Ramathaimzophim.
from רָמָה and לֶ֫חִי; height of a jaw-bone; Ramath-Lechi, a place in Palestine: Ramath-lehi.
from רָנַן; a shout (of deliverance): song.
a primitive root; to whiz: rattle.
from רָנַן; properly, a creaking (or shrill sound), i.e. shout (of joy or grief): cry, gladness, joy, proclamation, rejoicing, shouting, sing(-ing), triumph.
the same as רִנָּה; Rinnah, an Israelite: Rinnah.

a primitive root; properly, to creak (or emit a stridulous sound), i.e. to shout (usually for joy): aloud for joy, cry out, be joyful (greatly, make to) rejoice, (cause to) shout (for joy), (cause to) sing (aloud, for joy, out), triumph.
from רָנַן; an ostrich (from its wail): X goodly.
intensive from רָנַן; shouting (for joy): singing.
from רָנַן; a shout (for joy): joyful (voice), singing, triumphing.
from רָסַס; a ruin (as dripping to pieces); Rissah, a place in the Desert: Rissah.
from רָסַס; properly, dripping to pieces, i.e. a ruin; also a dew-drop: breach, drop.
from an unused root meaning to curb; a halter (as restraining); by implication, the jaw: bridle.
the same as רֶ֫סֶן; Resen, a place in Assyrian: Resen.
a primitive root; to comminute; used only as denominative from רְסִיסִים, to moisten (with drops): temper.

from רָעַע; bad or (as noun) evil (natural or moral)adversity, affliction, bad, calamity, + displease(-ure), distress, evil((- favouredness), man, thing), + exceedingly, X great, grief(-vous), harm, heavy, hurt(-ful), ill (favoured), + mark, mischief(-vous), misery, naught(-ty), noisome, + not please, sad(-ly), sore, sorrow, trouble, vex, wicked(-ly, -ness, one), worse(-st), wretchedness, wrong. (Incl. feminine raaah; as adjective or noun.).
from ר֫וּעַ; a crash (of thunder), noise (of war), shout (of joy): X aloud, noise, shouted.
or reya2; from רָעָה; an associate (more or less close): brother, companion, fellow, friend, husband, lover, neighbour, X (an-)other.
from רָעָה; a thought (as association of ideas): thought.
from רָעַע; badness (as marring), physically or morally: X be so bad, badness, (X be so) evil, naughtiness, sadness, sorrow, wickedness.
a primitive root; to hunger: (suffer to) famish, (be, have, suffer, suffer to) hunger(-ry).
from רָעֵב; hungry (more or less intensely): hunger bitten, hungry.
from רָעֵב; hunger (more or less extensive): dearth, famine, + famished, hunger.
from רָעֵב; famine: famine.
a primitive root: to shudder (more or less violently): tremble.
or (feminine) radah; from רָעַד; a shudder: trembling.

a primitive root; to tend a flock; i.e. pasture it; intransitively, to graze (literally or figuratively); generally to rule; by extension, to associate with (as a friend): X break, companion, keep company with, devour, eat up, evil entreat, feed, use as a friend, make friendship with, herdman, keep (sheep)(-er), pastor, + shearing house, shepherd, wander, waste.
from רָעָה; a (male) companion: friend.
feminine of רֵ֫עַ; a female associate: companion, fellow.
for רֹ֫עַ; breakage: broken, utterly.
for רֶ֫עִי in the sense of רֵ֫עַ; friend; Reu, a postdiluvian patriarch: Reu.
from the same as רְעוּ and אֵל; friend of God; Reuel, the name of Moses' father-in-law, also of an Edomite and an Israelite: Raguel, Reuel.
from רָעָה in the sense of רֵ֫עַ; a female associate; generally an additional one: + another, mate, neighbour.
probably from רָעָה; a feeding upon, i.e. grasping after: vexation.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רְעוּת; desire: pleasure, will.
from רָעָה; pasture: pasture.
from רֵ֫עַ; social; Rei, an Israelite: Rei.
from active participle of רָעָה; pastoral; as noun, a shepherd: shipherd.
feminine of רֵ֫עַ; a female associate: fellow, love.
from רָעָה in the sense of רְעוּת; desire: vexation.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רַעְיוֹן; a grasp. i.e. (figuratively) mental conception: cogitation, thought.
a primitive root; to reel, i.e. (figuratively) to brandish: terribly shake.
from רָעַל; a reeling (from intoxication): trembling.
feminine of רַ֫עַל; a long veil (as fluttering): muffler.
from רָעַל and יָהּ; made to tremble (i.e. fearful) of Jah; Reelajah, an Israelite: Reeliah.
a primitive root; to tumble, i.e. be violently agitated; specifically, to crash (of thunder); figuratively, to irritate (with anger): make to fret, roar, thunder, trouble.
from רָעַם; a peal of thunder: thunder.
feminine of רַ֫עַם; the mane of a horse (as quivering in the wind): thunder.
the same as רַעְמָה; Ramah, the name of a grandson of Ham, and of a place (perhaps founded by him): Raamah.
from רָעַם and יָהּ; Jah has shaken; Raamjah, an Israelite: Raamiah.
or Raamcec; of Egyptian origin; Rameses or Raamses, a place in Egypt: Raamses, Rameses.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רַעֲנָן; green, i.e. (figuratively) prosperous; --flourishing.
from an unused root meaning to be green; verdant; by analogy, new; figuratively, prosperous: green, flourishing.

a primitive root; properly, to spoil (literally, by breaking to pieces); figuratively, to make (or be) good for nothing, i.e. bad (physically, socially or morally): afflict, associate selves (by mistake for ra`ah), break (down, in pieces), + displease, (be, bring, do) evil (doer, entreat, man), show self friendly (by mistake for ra`ah), do harm, (do) hurt, (behave self, deal) ill, X indeed, do mischief, punish, still, vex, (do) wicked (doer, -ly), be (deal, do) worse.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָעַע: break, bruise.
a primitive root; to drip: distil, drop (down).
a primitive root; to break in pieces; figuratively, harass: dash in pieces, vex.

a primitive root; to undulate (as the earth, the sky, etc.; also a field of grain), partic. through fear; specifically, to spring (as a locust): make afraid, (re-)move, quake, (make to) shake, (make to) tremble.
from רָעַשׁ; vibration, bounding, uproar: commotion, confused noise, earthquake, fierceness, quaking, rattling, rushing, shaking.
or raphah; a primitive root; properly, to mend (by stitching), i.e. (figuratively) to cure: cure, (cause to) heal, physician, repair, X thoroughly, make whole. See רָפָה.
from רָפָא in the sense of רָפָה; properly, lax, i.e. (figuratively) a ghost (as dead; in plural only): dead, deceased.
or raphah; from רָפָא in the sense of invigorating; a giant: giant, Rapha, Rephaim(-s). See also בֵּית רָפָא.
or Raphah; probably the same as רָפָא; giant; Rapha or Raphah, the name of two Israelites: Rapha.
feminine passive participle of רָפָא; a medicament: heal(-ed), medicine.
from רָפָא; a cure: health.
from רָפָא and אֵל; God has cured; Rephael, an Israelite: Rephael.
a primitive root; to spread (a bed); by implication, to refresh: comfort, make (a bed), spread.

a primitive root; to slacken (in many applications, literal or figurative): abate, cease, consume, draw (toward evening), fail, (be) faint, be (wax) feeble, forsake, idle, leave, let alone (go, down), (be) slack, stay, be still, be slothful, (be) weak(-en). See רָפָא.
from רָפָה; slack (in body or mind): weak. raphah, Raphah. See רָפָא, רָפָא. riphah. See רִיפוֹת.
passive participle of רָפָא; cured; Raphu, an Israelite: Raphu.
from an unused root apparently meaning to sustain; support; Rephach, an Israelite: Rephah.
from רָפַד; a railing (as spread along): bottom.
plural of the masculine of the same as רְפִידַת; ballusters; Rephidim, a place in the Desert: Rephidim.
from רָפָא and יָהּ; Jah has cured; Rephajah, the name of five Israelites: Rephaiah.
from רָפָה; slackness: feebleness.
a primitive root; to trample, i.e. prostrate: humble self, submit self.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָפַס: stamp.
from רָפַס; a raft (as flat on the water): flote.
a primitive root; to recline: lean.
a primitive root; to trample, i.e. roil water: foul, trouble.
from רָפַשׂ; mud (as roiled): mire.
probably from רָפָה; a stall for cattle (from their resting there): stall.
contracted from רָצַץ; a fragment: piece.
a primitive root; to run; also to delight in: accept, run.
a primitive root; probably to look askant, i.e. (figuratively) be jealous: leap.

a primitive root; to be pleased with; specifically, to satisfy a debt: (be) accept(-able), accomplish, set affection, approve, consent with, delight (self), enjoy, (be, have a) favour(-able), like, observe, pardon, (be, have, take) please(-ure), reconcile self.
or ratson; from רָצָה; delight (especially as shown): (be) acceptable(-ance, -ed), delight, desire, favour, (good) pleasure, (own, self, voluntary) will, as...(what) would.
a primitive root; properly, to dash in pieces, i.e. kill (a human being), especially to murder: put to death, kill, (man-)slay(-er), murder(-er).
from רָצַח; a crushing; specifically, a murder-cry: slaughter, sword.
from רָצָה; delight; Ritsjah, an Israelite: Rezia.
probably for רָצוֹן; Retsin, the name of a Syrian and of an Israelite: Rezin.
a primitive root; to pierce: bore.
a denominative from רְצָפִים; to tessellate, i.e. embroider (as if with bright stones): pave.
for רֶ֫שֶׁף; a red-hot stone (for baking): coal.
the same as רְצָפִים; Retseph, a place in Assyrian: Rezeph.
feminine of רְצָפִים; a hot stone; also a tessellated pavement: live coal, pavement.
the same as רִצְפָה; Ritspah, an Israelitess: Rizpah.
a primitive root; to crack in pieces, literally or figuratively: break, bruise, crush, discourage, oppress, struggle together.
from רָקַק in its original sense; emaciated (as if flattened out): lean((-fleshed)), thin.

the same as רַקּוֹת as a noun; properly, leanness, i.e. (figuratively) limitation; only adverbial, merely, or conjunctional, although: but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless, nothing but, notwithstanding, only, save, so (that), surely, yet (so), in any wise.
from רָקַק; spittle: spit(-ting, -tle).
a primitive root; to decay (as by worm-eating): rot.
from רָקַב; decay (by caries): rottenness (thing).
from רָקָב; decay (by caries): rotten.
a primitive root; properly, to stamp, i.e. to spring about (wildly or for joy): dance, jump, leap, skip.
feminine of רַקּוֹת; properly, thinness, i.e. the side of the head: temple.
from רַקּוֹת; thinness; Rakkon, a place in Palestine: Rakkon.
a primitive root; to perfume: apothecary, compound, make (ointment), prepare, spice.
from רָקַח; properly, perfumery, i.e. (by implication) spicery (for flavor): spiced.
from רַקּוֹן; an aromatic: confection, ointment.
from רָקַח; a male perfumer: apothecary.
from רָקַח; a scented substance: perfume.
feminine of רִקֻּחֵי; a female perfumer: confectioner.
from רָקַע; properly, an expanse, i.e. the firmament or (apparently) visible arch of the sky: firmament.
from, רָקַק in its original sense; a thin cake; -- cake, wafer.
a primitive root; to variegate color, i.e. embroider; by implication, to fabricate: embroiderer, needlework, curiously work.
from רָקַם; versi-color; Rekem, the name of a place in Palestine, also of a Midianite and an Israelite: Rekem.
from רָקַם; variegation of color; specifically, embroidery: broidered (work), divers colours, (raiment of) needlework (on both sides).

a primitive root; to pound the earth (as a sign of passion); by analogy to expand (by hammering); by implication, to overlay (with thin sheets of metal): beat, make broad, spread abroad (forth, over, out, into plates), stamp, stretch.
from רָקַע; beaten out, i.e. a (metallic) plate: broad.
a primitive root; to spit: spit.
from רָקַק in its original sense of diffusing; a beach (as expanded shingle); Rakkath, a place in Palestine: Rakkath.
from an unused root meaning to have leave; a permit: grant.
a primitive root; to record: note.
(Aramaic) corresponding to רָשַׁם: sign, write.
a primitive root; to be (causatively, do or declare) wrong; by implication, to disturb, violate: condemn, make trouble, vex, be (commit, deal, depart, do) wicked(-ly, -ness).
from רָשַׁע; a wrong (especially moral): iniquity, wicked(-ness).
from רָשַׁע; morally wrong; concretely, an (actively) bad person: + condemned, guilty, ungodly, wicked (man), that did wrong.
feminine of רֶ֫שַׁע; wrong (especially moral): fault, wickedly(-ness).
from שָׂרַף; a live coal; by analogy lightning; figuratively, an arrow, (as flashing through the air); specifically, fever: arrow, (burning) coal, burning heat, + spark, hot thunderbolt.
the same as רֶ֫שֶׁף; Resheph, an Israelite: Resheph.
a primitive root; to demolish: impoverish.
from יָרַשׁ; a net (as catching animals): net(- work).
from רָתַק; a chain: chain.
a primitive root; to boil: boil.
from רָתַח; a boiling: X (boil) well.
from רָתַק; a chain: chain.
a primitive root; to yoke up (to the pole of a vehicle): bind.
or rothem; from רָתַם; the Spanish broom (from its pole-like stems): juniper (tree).
feminine of רֹ֫תֶם; Rithmah, a place in the Desert: Rithmah.
a primitive root; to fasten: bind.
feminine passive participle of רָתַק; something fastened, i.e. a chain: chain.
for רֶ֫טֶט; terror: trembling.
a primitive root; to bale up water: (woman to) draw(-er, water).
a primitive root; to rumble or moan: X mightily, roar.
from שָׁאַג; a rumbling or moan: roaring.
a primitive root; to rush; by implication, to desolate: be desolate, (make a) rush(-ing), (lay) waste.
a primitive root (identical with שָׁאָה through the idea of whirling to giddiness); to stun, i.e. (intransitively) be astonished: wonder.
from שָׁאָה; a tempest (as rushing): desolation.
or shol; from שָׁאַל; Hades or the world of the dead (as if a subterranean retreat), including its accessories and inmates: grave, hell, pit.
passive participle of שָׁאַל; asked; Shaul, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites: Saul, Shaul.
patronymic from שִׂטְנָה; a Shaulite or descendant of Shaul: Shaulites.
from שָׁאָה; uproar (as of rushing); by implication, destruction: X horrible, noise, pomp, rushing, tumult (X -uous).
from an unused root meaning to push aside; contempt: despite(-ful).
for active part of סוּט (compare שְׁאָט); one contemning: that (which) despise(-d).
from שָׁאָה; desolation: destruction.

or shael; a primitive root; to inquire; by implication, to request; by extension, to demand: ask (counsel, on), beg, borrow, lay to charge, consult, demand, desire, X earnestly, enquire, + greet, obtain leave, lend, pray, request, require, + salute, X straitly, X surely, wish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁאַל: ask, demand, require.
from שָׁאַל; request; Sheal, an Israelite: Sheal.
(Aramaic) from שְׁאֵל; properly, a question (at law), i.e. judicial decision or mandate: demand.
or shelah (1 Samuel 1:17); from שָׁאַל; a petition; by implication, a loan: loan, petition, request.
or Shaltiy(el; from שָׁאַל and אֵל; I have asked God; Shealtiel, an Israelite: Shalthiel, Shealtiel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שְׁאַלְתִּיאֵל: Shealtiel.
a primitive root; to loll, i.e. be peaceful: be at ease, be quiet, rest. See also בֵּית שְׁאָן.
from שָׁאַן; secure; in a bad sense, haughty: that is at ease, quiet, tumult. Compare שַׁלְאֲנָן.
a primitive root; to plunder: spoil.
a primitive root; to inhale eagerly; figuratively, to cover; by implication, to be angry; also to hasten: desire (earnestly), devour, haste, pant, snuff up, swallow up.
from שָׁאַר; barm or yeast-cake (as swelling by fermentation): leaven.
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. be (causatively, make) redundant: leave, (be) left, let, remain, remnant, reserve, the rest.
from שָׁאַר; a remainder: X other, remnant, residue, rest.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שְׁאָר: X whatsoever more, residue, rest.
from שָׁאַר; flesh (as swelling out), as living or for food; generally food of any kind; figuratively, kindred by bloodbody, flesh, food, (near) kin(-sman, -swoman), near (nigh) (of kin).
feminine of שְׁאֵר; female kindred by blood: near kinswomen.
the same as שַׁאֲרָה; Sheerah, an Israelitess: Sherah.
from שְׁאָר and שׁוּב; a remnant will return; Shear-Jashub, the symbolic name of one of Isaiah's sons: Shear-jashub.
from שָׁאַר; a remainder or residual (surviving, final) portion: that had escaped, be left, posterity, remain(-der), remnant, residue, rest.
from שָׁאָה; devastation: desolation.
from נָשָׂא; an elevation or leprous scab; figuratively, elation or cheerfulness; exaltation in rank or characterbe accepted, dignity, excellency, highness, raise up self, rising.
of foreign origin; Sheba, the name of three early progenitors of tribes and of an Ethiopian district: Sheba, Sabeans.
patronymic from שְׁבָא; a Shebaite or descendant of Sheba: Sabean.
from an unused root meaning to break up; a fragment, i.e. ruin: broken in pieces.
a primitive root; to transport into captivity: (bring away, carry, carry away, lead, lead away, take) captive(-s), drive (take) away.

from an unused root (probably identical with that of שָׁבָה through the idea of subdivision into flashes or streamers (compare שְׁבִיב) meaning to flame; a gem (from its sparkle), probably the agate: agate.
or Shuwbanel; from שָׁבָה (abbrev.) or שׁוּב and אֵל; captive (or returned) of God; Shebuel or Shubael, the name of two Israelites: Shebuel, Shubael.
or shabuan; also (feminine) shbu.ah; properly, passive participle of שָׁבַע as a denominative of שֶׁ֫בַע; literal, sevened, i.e. a week (specifically, of years): seven, week.
feminine passive participle of שָׁבַע; properly, something sworn, i.e. an oath: curse, oath, X sworn.
or shbiyth; from שָׁבָה; exile, concretely, prisoners; figuratively, a former state of prosperitycaptive(-ity).
a primitive root; properly, to address in a loud tone, i.e. (specifically) loud; figuratively, to pacify (as if by words): commend, glory, keep in, praise, still, triumph.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁבַח; to adulate, i.e. adore: praise.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁ֫בֶט; a clan: tribe.

from an unused root probably meaning to branch off; a scion, i.e. (literally) a stick (for punishing, writing, fighting, ruling, walking, etc.) or (figuratively) a clan: X correction, dart, rod, sceptre, staff, tribe.
of foreign origin; Shebat, a Jewish month: Sebat.
from שְׁבוֹ; exiled; captured; as noun, exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively); by extension, booty: captive(-ity), prisoners, X take away, that was taken.
from שָׁבָה; captor; Shobi, an Ammonite: Shobi.
for שֹׁבִי; Shobai, an Israelite: Shobai.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שְׁבִיב: flame.
from the same as שְׁבָבִים; flame (as split into tongues): spark.
feminine of שֶׁ֫בִי; exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively): captives(-ity).
feminine of the same as שֹׁבִי; captivation; Shobjah, an Israelite: Shachia (from the margin).
from the same as שֹׁ֫בֶל; a track or passage-way (as if flowing along): path.
from an unused root meaning to interweave; a netting for the hair: caul.
or shbi iy; ordinal from שִׁבְעִים; seventh: seventh (time).
from an unused root meaning to intwine; a netting (ornament to the capital of a column): net.
feminine of שְׂבָכִים; a net-work, i.e (in hunting) a snare, (in architecture) a ballustrade; also a reticulated ornament to a pillar: checker, lattice, network, snare, wreath(-enwork).
from an unused root meaning to flow; a lady's train (as trailing after her): leg.

or (feminine) shibboleth; from the same as שֹׁ֫בֶל; a stream (as flowing); also an ear of grain (as growing out); by analogy, a branch: branch, channel, ear (of corn), ((water-))flood, Shibboleth. Compare סִבֹּ֫לֶת.
from the same as שֹׁ֫בֶל; a snail (as if floating in its own slime): snail.
or (feminine) Sibmah; probably from בָּשָׂם; spice; Sebam or Sibmah, a place in Moab: Shebam, Shibmah, Sibmah.
:  : or Shebnah; from an unused root meaning to grow; growth; Shebna or Shebnah, an Israelite: Shebna, Shebnah.
or Shbanyahuw; from the same as שֶׁבְנָה and יָהּ; Jah has grown (i.e. prospered); Shebanjah, the name of three or four Israelites: Shebaniah.

or sabeay; a primitive root; to sate, i.e. fill to satisfaction (literally or figuratively): have enough, fill (full, self, with), be (to the) full (of), have plenty of, be satiate, satisfy (with), suffice, be weary of.
from שָׂבַע; copiousness: abundance, plenteous(- ness, -ly).
from שָׂבַע; satisfaction (of food or (figuratively) joy): fill, full(-ness), satisfying, be satisfied.
from שָׂבַע; satiated (in a pleasant or disagreeable sense): full (of), satisfied (with).

a primitive root; propr. to be complete, but used only as a denominative from שֶׁ֫בַע; to seven oneself, i.e. swear (as if by repeating a declaration seven times): adjure, charge (by an oath, with an oath), feed to the full (by mistake for saba`), take an oath, X straitly, (cause to, make to) swear.

or (masculine) shibrah; from שָׁבַע; a primitive cardinal number; seven (as the sacred full one); also (adverbially) seven times; by implication, a week; by extension, an indefinite number: (+ by) seven(-fold),-s, (-teen, -teenth), -th, times). Compare שִׁבְעָ֫נָה.
the same as שֶׁ֫בַע; seven; Sheba, the name of a place in Palestine, and of two Israelites: Sheba.
feminine of שָׂבָע; satiety: fulness.
feminine of שֹׂ֫בַע; satiety: (to have) enough, X till...be full, (un-)satiable, satisfy, X sufficiently.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שֶׁ֫בַע: seven (times).
masculine of שֶׁ֫בַע; seven(-th); Shebah, a well in Palestine: Shebah.
multiple of שֶׁ֫בַע; seventy: seventy, threescore and ten (+ -teen).
prol. for the masculine of שֶׁ֫בַע; seven: seven.
dual (adverbially) of שֶׁ֫בַע; seven- times: seven(-fold, times).
a primitive root; to interweave (colored) threads in squares; by implication (of reticulation) to inchase gems in gold: embroider, set.
from שָׁבַץ; entanglement, i.e. (figuratively) perplexity: anguish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of שׁוֹבֵק; to quit, i.e. allow to remain: leave, let alone.
erroneously shabar (Nehemiah 2:13, 15); a primitive root; to scrutinize; by implication (of watching) to expect (with hope and patience): hope, tarry, view, wait.
from שָׂבַר; expectation: hope.

a primitive root; to burst (literally or figuratively): break (down, off, in pieces, up), broken((-hearted)), bring to the birth, crush, destroy, hurt, quench, X quite, tear, view (by mistake for sabar).
denominative from שֶׁ֫בֶר; to deal in grain: buy, sell.

or sheber; from שָׁבַר; a fracture, figuratively, ruin; specifically, a solution (of a dream): affliction, breach, breaking, broken(-footed, -handed), bruise, crashing, destruction, hurt, interpretation, vexation.
the same as שָׁ֫בֶר; grain (as if broken into kernels): corn, victuals.
the same as שָׁ֫בֶר; Sheber, an Israelite: Sheber.
from שָׁבַר; rupture, i.e. a pang; figuratively, ruin: breaking, destruction.
plural of שָׁ֫בֶר; ruins; Shebarim, a place in Palestine: Shebarim.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁבַץ; to entangle, i.e. perplex: be astonished.

a primitive root; to repose, i.e. desist from exertion; used in many implied relations (causative, figurative or specific): (cause to, let, make to) cease, celebrate, cause (make) to fail, keep (sabbath), suffer to be lacking, leave, put away (down), (make to) rest, rid, still, take away.
from שָׁבַת; rest, interruption, cessation: cease, sit still, loss of time.
infinitive of יָשַׁב; properly, session; but used also concretely, an abode or locality: place, seat. Compare יֹשֵׁב בַּשֶּׁ֫בֶת.
intensive from שָׁבַת; intermission, i.e (specifically) the Sabbath: (+ every) sabbath.
from שַׁבָּת; a sabbatism or special holiday: rest, sabbath.
from שַׁבָּת; restful; Shabbethai, the name of three Israelites: Shabbethai.
:  : a primitive root; to grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (figuratively) laud: increase, magnify.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׂגָא; to increase: grow, be multiplied.
probably from שָׁגָה; erring; Shage, an Israelite: Shage.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively --defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.
a primitive root; to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology): X also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.
from שָׁגַג; a mistake or inadvertent transgression: error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly.
a primitive root; to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively): grow (up), increase.

a primitive root; to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured: (cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.
from שָׂגַב; aloft; Segub, the name of two Israelites: Segub.
a primitive root; to peep, i.e. glance sharply at: look (narrowly).
from שָׂגָא; (superlatively) mighty: excellent, great.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שַׂגִּיא; large (in size, quantity or number, also adverbial): exceeding, great(-ly); many, much, sore, very.
from שָׁגָה; a moral mistake: error.
or shiggayonah; from שָׁגָה; properly, aberration, i.e. (technically) a dithyramb or rambling poem: Shiggaion, Shigionoth.
a primitive root; to copulate with: lie with, ravish.
from שָׁגַל; a queen (from cohabitation): queen.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שֵׁגַל; a (legitimate) queen: wife.
a primitive root; to rave through insanity: (be, play the) mad (man).
from שָׁגַע; craziness: furiously, madness.
from an unused root probably meaning to eject; the fetus (as finally expelled): that cometh of, increase.
or shod; probably from שׁוּד (in its original sense) contracted; the breast of a woman or animal (as bulging): breast, pap, teat.
from שׁוּד; a daemon (as malignant): devil.
or showd (Job 5:21); from שׁוּד; violence, ravage: desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoil(-ed, -er, - ing), wasting.
a primitive root; to abrade, i.e. harrow a field: break clods, harrow.
a primitive root; properly, to be burly, i.e. (figuratively) powerful (passively, impregnable); by implication, to ravage: dead, destroy(-er), oppress, robber, spoil(-er), X utterly, (lay) waste.
or saday; from an unused root meaning to spread out; a field (as flat): country, field, ground, land, soil, X wild.
from שָׁדַד; a wife (as mistress of the house): X all sorts, musical instrument.
from שָׁדַד; the Almighty: Almighty.
from the same as שָׂדֶה and אוּר; spreader of light; Shedejur, an Israelite: Shedeur.
plural from the same as שָׂדֶה; flats; Siddim, a valley in Palestine: Siddim.
apparently from שָׂדֶה; a cultivated field; -- blasted, field.
a primitive root; to scorch: blast.
or shiddaphown; from שָׁדַף; blight: blasted(-ing).
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to endeavor: labour.
from an unused root meaning to regulate; a row, i.e. rank (of soldiers), story (of rooms): board, range.
probably of foreign origin; Shadrak, the Bab. name of one of Daniel's companions: Shadrach.
(Aramaic) the same as שַׁדְרַך: Shadrach.
or sey; probably from שָׁאָה through the idea of pushing out to graze; a member of a flock, i.e. a sheep or goat: (lesser, small) cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep. Compare שֶׂה.
from an unused root meaning to testify; a witness: record.
from an unused root probably mean to blanch; a gem, probably the beryl (from its pale green color): onyx.
the same as שֹׁ֫הַם; Shoham, an Israelite: Shoham.
from the same as סַ֫הַר; a round pendant for the neck: ornament, round tire like the moon.
from an unused root (akin to נָשָׂא and שׁוֹאָה) meaning to rise; a rising: arise.
or (feminine) showtah; or shoah; from an unused root meaning to rush over; a tempest; by implication, devastation: desolate(-ion), destroy, destruction, storm, wasteness.

or shav; from the same as שׁוֹאָה in the sense of desolating; evil (as destructive), literally (ruin) or morally (especially guile); figuratively idolatry (as false, subjective), uselessness (as deceptive, objective; also adverbially, in vain): false(-ly), lie, lying, vain, vanity.
from the same as שָׁוְא; false; Sheva, an Israelite: Sheva.

a primitive root; to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again: ((break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down, lie down, lodge, make, rejoice, send, take, weep)) X again, (cause to) answer (+ again), X in any case (wise), X at all, averse, bring (again, back, home again), call (to mind), carry again (back), cease, X certainly, come again (back), X consider, + continually, convert, deliver (again), + deny, draw back, fetch home again, X fro, get (oneself) (back) again, X give (again), go again (back, home), (go) out, hinder, let, (see) more, X needs, be past, X pay, pervert, pull in again, put (again, up again), recall, recompense, recover, refresh, relieve, render (again), requite, rescue, restore, retrieve, (cause to, make to) return, reverse, reward, + say nay, send back, set again, slide back, still, X surely, take back (off), (cause to, make to) turn (again, self again, away, back, back again, backward, from, off), withdraw.
from שׁוּב; apostate, i.e. idolatrous: backsliding, frowardly, turn away (from margin).
the same as שׁוֹבָב; rebellious; Shobab, the name of two Israelites: Shobab.
from שׁוּב; apostate, i.e. heathenish or (actually) heathen: backsliding.
from שׁוּב; a return: returning.
for סֻבְּכוֹ; a thicket, i.e. interlaced branches: thick boughs.
perhaps for שׂ֫וֹבֶך; Shobak, a Syrian: Shobach.
from the same as שֹׁ֫בֶל; overflowing; Shobal, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites: Shobal.
active participle from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare שְׁבַק); forsaking; Shobek, an Israelite: Shobek.
a primitive root; to retreat: turn back.
a primitive root; to hedge in: make to grow.
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. figuratively (by implication of insolence) to devastate: waste.

a primitive root; properly, to level, i.e. equalize; figuratively, to resemble; by implication, to adjust (i.e. counterbalance, be suitable, compose, place, yield, etc.): avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, (be, make) equal, lay, be (make, a-)like, make plain, profit, reckon.
a primitive root; to destroy: X substance (from the margin).
(Aramaic): corresponding to שָׁוָה; to resemble: make like.
from שָׁוָה; plain; Shaveh, a place in Palestine: Shaveh.
from the same as שָׁוֵה and the dual of קִרְיָה; plain of a double city; Shaveh-Kirjathajim, a place East of the Jordan: Shaveh Kiriathaim.
a primitive root; to muse pensively: meditate.
a primitive root; to sink, literally or figuratively: bow down, incline, humble.
from שׁ֫וּחַ; dell; Shuach, a son of Abraham: Shuah.
from שׁ֫וּחַ; a chasm: ditch, pit.
the same as שׁוּחָה; Shuchah, an Israelite: Shuah.
patronymic from שׁ֫וּחַ; a Shuchite or descendant of Shuach: Shuhite.
from שׁ֫וּחַ; humbly; Shucham, an Israelite: Shuham.
patronymic from שׁוּחָם; a Shuchamite (collectively): Shuhamites.
or (by permutation) cuwt; a primitive root; to detrude, i.e. (intransitively and figuratively) become derelict (wrongly practise; namely, idolatry): turn aside to.

a primitive root; properly, to push forth; (but used only figuratively) to lash, i.e. (the sea with oars) to row; by implication, to travel: go (about, through, to and fro), mariner, rower, run to and fro.
from שׁוּט; a lash (literally or figuratively): scourge, whip.
a primitive root; to entwine, i.e. shut in (for formation, protection or restraint): fence, (make an) hedge (up).
or (feminine) sowkah; from שׂוּך; a branch (as interleaved): bough.
or Sokoh; or Sowkow; from שׂוּך; Sokoh or Soko, the name of two places in Palestine: Shocho, Shochoh, Sochoh, Soco, Socoh.
probably patronymic from a name corresponding to שׂוֹך (feminine); a Sukathite or descendant of an unknown Israelite named Sukah: Suchathite.
from an unused root meaning to hang down; a skirt; by implication, a bottom edge: hem, skirt, train.
or sheylal (Micah 1:8); from שָׁלַל; nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive: spoiled, stripped.
from שָׁלַם; peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen: Shulamite.

or siym; a primitive root; to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically): X any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine, + disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark, + name, X on, ordain, order, + paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on), + regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew, + stedfastly, take, X tell, + tread down, ((over-))turn, X wholly, work.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שׂוּם: + command, give, lay, make, + name, + regard, set.
from an unused root meaning to exhale; garlic (from its rank odor): garlic.
or Shomer; active participle of שָׁמַר; keeper; Shomer, the name of two Israelites: Shomer.
from an unused root meaning to rest; quiet; Shuni, an Israelite: Shuni.
patronymic from שׁוּנִי; a Shunite (collectively) or descendants of Shuni: Shunites.
probably from the same as שׁוּנִי; quietly; Shunem, a place in Pal: Shunem.
patrial from שׁוּנֵם; a Shunammitess, or female inhabitant of Shunem: Shunamite.
a primitive root; properly, to be free; but used only causatively and reflexively, to halloo (for help, i.e. freedom from some trouble): cry (aloud, out), shout.
from שָׁוַע; a halloo: cry, riches.
the same as שׁ֫וּעַ; Shua, a Canaanite: Shua, Shuah.
from שָׁוַע in the original sense of freedom; a noble, i.e. liberal, opulent; also (as noun in the derived sense) a halloo: bountiful, crying, rich.
the same as שׁ֫וֹעַ; rich; Shoa, an Oriental people: Shoa.
from שָׁוַע; a halloo: cry.
from שָׁוַע; wealth; Shua, an Israelitess: Shua.
feminine of שֶׁ֫וַע; a hallooing: crying.
or shunal; from the same as שֹׁ֫עַל; a jackal (as a burrower): fox.
the same as שׁוּעָל; Shual, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine: Shual.
or shomer : active participle of שָׁעַר (as denominative from שַׁ֫עַר); a janitor: doorkeeper, porter.
a primitive root; properly, to gape, i.e. snap at; figuratively, to overwhelm: break, bruise, cover.
from שָׁפַך; poured; Shophak, a Syrian: Shophach.
patronymic from שְׁפוּפָן; a Shuphamite (collectively) or descendants of Shephupham: Shuphamite.
or shophar; from שָׁפַר in the original sense of incising; a cornet (as giving a clear sound) or curved horn: cornet, trumpet.
a primitive root; to run after or over, i.e. overflow: overflow, water.
from שׁוּק; a street (as run over): street.
from שׁוּק; the (lower) leg (as a runner): hip, leg, shoulder, thigh.
a primitive root; properly, to vanquish; by implication, to rule (causatively, crown): make princes, have power, reign. See סוּר.
a primitive root (identical with שׂוּר through the idea of reducing to pieces; compare מַשּׂוֹר); to saw: cut.
a primitive root; properly, to turn, i.e. travel about (as a harlot or a merchant): go, singular See also shiyr.

a primitive root (identical with שׁוּר through the idea of going round for inspection); to spy out, i.e. (generally) survey, (for evil) lurk for, (for good) care for: behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see.
from שִׁימוֹן; a foe (as lying in wait): enemy.
from שׁוּר; a wall (as going about): wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שׁוּר: wall.
the same as שׁוּר; Shur, a region of the Desert: Shur.
from שׁוּר; a bullock (as a traveller): bull(-ock), cow, ox, wall (by mistake for shuwr).
from שׂוּר in the primitive sense of סוּר; properly, a ring, i.e. (by analogy) a row (adverbially): principal.
the same as שֹׂרֵק; a vine; Sorek, a valley in Palestine: Sorek.
or siys; a primitive root; to be bright, i.e. cheerful: be glad, X greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.
from שׂוּשׂ; joyful; Shavsha, an Israelite: Shavsha.
or showshan; or shoshan; and (feminine) showshannah; from שׂוּשׂ; a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of arch. ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape): lily, Shoshannim.
the same as שׁוֹשָׁן; Shushan, a place in Persia: Shushan.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; a Shushankite (collectively) or inhabitants of some unknown place in Assyrian: Susanchites.
or (plural of former) Showshanniym Eduwth; from שׁוֹשָׁן and עֵדוּת; lily (or trumpet) of assemblage; Shushan-Eduth or Shoshannim-Eduth, the title of a popular song: Shoshannim-Eduth, Shushan-eduth.
probably from שָׁאָה and the same as תָּ֫לַח; crash of breakage; Shuthelach, the name of two Israelites: Shuthelah.
(Aramaic) corresponding to עָזַב; to leave, i.e. (causatively) free: deliver.
a primitive root; to tan (by sun-burning); figuratively (as if by a piercing ray) to scan: look up, see.
a primitive root; to twist (a thread of straw): twine.
from שָׁחַח; sunk, i.e. downcast: + humble.
for שִׂ֫יחַ; communion, i.e. (reflexively) meditation: thought.
a primitive root; to donate, i.e. bribe: hire, give a reward.
from שָׁחַד; a donation (venal or redemptive): bribe(-ry), gift, present, reward.
a primitive root; to swim; causatively, to inundate: (make to) swim.

a primitive root; to depress, i.e. prostrate (especially reflexive, in homage to royalty or God): bow (self) down, crouch, fall down (flat), humbly beseech, do (make) obeisance, do reverence, make to stoop, worship.
from שָׂחָה; a pond (for swimming): to swim in.
or schoq; from שָׂחַק; laughter (in merriment or defiance): derision, laughter(-ed to scorn, -ing), mocked, sport.
from שָׁחַר; dinginess, i.e. perhaps soot: coal.
from שָׁחָה; pit: pit.
a primitive root; to sink or depress (reflexive or causative): bend, bow (down), bring (cast) down, couch, humble self, be (bring) low, stoop.
a primitive root; to tread out, i.e. squeeze (grapes): press.
a primitive root; to slaughter (in sacrifice or massacre): kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter.
a primitive root (identical with שָׁחַט through the idea of striking); to hammer out: beat.
from שָׁחַט; slaughter: killing.
from an unused root probably meaning to burn; inflammation, i.e. an ulcer; --boil, botch.
or cachiysh; from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout; after-growth: (that) which springeth of the same.
from the same as שָׁ֫חַף; a board (as chipped thin): cieled with.
from שָׁחָה; a pit-fall (literally or figuratively): destruction, pit.
from an unused root probably meaning to roar; a lion (from his characteristic roar): (fierce) lion.
apparently from the same as שָׁ֫חַל through some obscure idea, perhaps that of peeling off by concussion of sound; a scale or shell, i.e. the aromatic mussel.: onycha.
from an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. emaciate; the gull (as thin): cuckoo.
from the same as שָׁ֫חַף; emaciation: consumption.
from an unused root apparently meaning to strut; haughtiness (as evinced by the attitude): X lion, pride.
from the same as שָׁ֫חַץ; proudly; Shachatsom, a place in Palestine: Shahazimah (from the margin).
a primitive root; to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play: deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.
a primitive root; to comminate (by trituration or attrition): beat, wear.
from שָׁחַק; a powder (as beaten small): by analogy, a thin vapor; by extension, the firmament: cloud, small dust, heaven, sky.
a primitive root (identical with שָׁחַר through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn); to be dim or dark (in color): be black.

a primitive root; properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking): (do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).
from שָׁחַר; dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial): day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth.
or shachowr; from שָׁחַר; properly, dusky, but also (absol.) jetty: black.
from שָׁחַר; a dawning, i.e. (figuratively) juvenescence: youth.
from שָׁחַר; swarthy: black.
from שָׁחַר and יָהּ; Jah has sought; Shecharjah, an Israelite: Shehariah.
dual of שָׁ֫חַר; double dawn; Shacharajim, an Israelite: Shaharaim.
a primitive root; to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively): batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, X utterly, waste(-r).
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁחַת: corrupt, fault.
from שׁ֫וּחַ; a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction: corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit.
or cet; from סוּט; a departure from right, i.e. sin: revolter, that turn aside.
a primitive root; to deviate from duty: decline, go aside, turn.
feminine of a derivative (only in the plural shittiym; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as שֹׁטֵט; the acacia (from its scourging thorns): shittah, shittim. See also בֵּית הַשִּׁטָּה.
a primitive root; to expand: all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.
active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from שׁוֹט) to flog; a goad: scourge.
the same as the plural of שִׁטִּים; acacia trees; Shittim, a place East of the Jordan: Shittim.
a primitive root; properly, to lurk for, i.e. persecute: hate, oppose self against.
a primitive root; to attack, (figuratively) accuse: (be an) adversary, resist.
from שָׂטַן; an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good: adversary, Satan, withstand.
from שָׂטַן; opposition (by letter): accusation.
the same as שִׂטְנָה; Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal: Sitnah.
a primitive root; to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer: drown, (over-)flow(- whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).
or sheteph; from שָׁטַף; a deluge (literally or figuratively): flood, outrageous, overflowing.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a side: side.
active participle of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write; properly, a scribe, i.e. (by analogy or implication) an official superintendent or magistrate: officer, overseer, ruler.
from the same as שֹׁטֵר; magisterial; Shitrai, an Israelite: Shitrai.
probably from שָׁוָה; a gift (as available): present.
from the same as שׂוֹא by permutation; elevationexcellency.
for שְׁוָא; Sheja, an Israelite: Sheva (from the margin).
from שִׂיא; peak; Sion, the summit of Mt. Hermon: Sion.
from the same as שׁוֹאָה; ruin; Shijon, a place in Palestine --Shihon.
a primitive root; properly, to become aged, i.e. (by implication) to grow gray: (be) grayheaded.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שִׂיב: elder.
from שִׂיב; old age: age.
by permutation from שׁוּב; a return (of property): captivity.
from יָשַׁב; residence: while...lay.
feminine of שֵׂיב; old age: (be) gray (grey hoar,-y) hairs (head,-ed), old age.
from שׂוּג; a withdrawal (into a private place): pursuing.
a primitive root probably meaning to boil up (compare שׁוּד); used only as denominative from שִׂיד; to plaster: plaister.
from שִׂיד; lime (as boiling when slacked): lime, plaister.
a primitive root; to keep in memory: be unmindful. (Render Deuteronomy 32:18, "A Rock bore thee, thou must recollect; and (yet) thou hast forgotten," etc.)
of unknown derivation; Shiza, an Is.: Shiza.
a primitive root; to ponder, i.e. (by implication) converse (with oneself, and hence, aloud) or (transitively) uttercommune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk (with).
from שִׂ֫יחַ; a contemplation; by implication, an utterance: babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk.
from שִׂ֫יחַ; a shoot (as if uttered or put forth), i.e. (generally) shrubbery: bush, plant, shrub.
feminine of שִׂ֫יחַ; reflection; be extension, devotion: meditation, prayer.
for שׁוּחָה; a pit-fall: pit.
or Shichowr; or Shichor; probably from שָׁחַר; dark, i.e. turbid; Shichor, a stream of Egypt: Shihor, Sihor.
from the same as שִׁיחוֹר and לָבַן; darkish whiteness; Shichor-Libnath, a stream of Palestine: Shihor-libnath.
from שׁוּט; an oar; also (compare שׁוֹט) a scourge (figuratively): oar, scourge.
from שָׁלָה; tranquil; Shiloh, an epithet of the Messiah: Shiloh.
or Shiloh; or Shiylow; or Shilow; from the same as שִׁילֹה; Shiloh, a place in Palestine: Shiloh.
or Shiyloniy; or Shiloniy; from שִׁלֹה; a Shilonite or inhabitant of Shiloh: Shilonite.
apparently for יְשִׁימוֹן; desert; Shimon, an Israelite: Shimon.
from an unused root meaning to urinate; urine: piss.
or (the original form) shuwr (1 Sam. 18:6); a primitive root (identical with שׁוּר through the idea of strolling minstrelsy); to sing: behold (by mistake for shuwr), sing(-er, -ing man, - ing woman).
or feminine shiyrah; from שִׁיר; a song; abstractly, singing: musical(-ick), X sing(-er, -ing), song.
from an unused root meaning to bleach, i.e. whiten; white, i.e. marble. See שֵׁשׁ.
from the same as שַׁ֫יִשׁ; whiteness; Shisha, an Israelite: Shisha.
or Shuwshaq; of Egyptian derivation; Shishak, an Egyptian king: Shishak.
a primitive root; to place (in a very wide application): apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay (up), let alone, X look, make, mark, put (on), + regard, set, shew, be stayed, X take.
from שִׁית; a dress (as put on): attire.
from שִׁית; scrub or trash, i.e. wild growth of weeds or briers (as if put on the field): thorns.
from סָכַך in the sense of שׂוּך; a brier (as of a hedge): prick.
from סָכַך in the sense of שׂוּך; a booth (as interlaced): tabernacle.

a primitive root; to lie down (for rest, sexual connection, decease or any other purpose): X at all, cast down, ((lover-))lay (self) (down), (make to) lie (down, down to sleep, still with), lodge, ravish, take rest, sleep, stay.
from שָׁכַב; a lying down (of dew, or for the sexual act): X carnally, copulation, X lay, seed.
from שָׁכַב; a (sexual) lying with: X lie.
a primitive root; to roam (through lust): in the morning (by mistake for shakam).
feminine of שֹׂך in the sense of שִׂכִּים; a dart (as pointed like a thorn): barbed iron.
from an unused root apparently meaning to surmount; an observatory (with the article); Seku, a place in Palestine: Sechu.
from the same as שֶׂ֫כוּ; observant, i.e. (concretely) the mind: heart.
infinitive of שָׁכֹל; bereavement: loss of children, spoiling.
or shakkul; from שָׁכֹל; bereaved: barren, bereaved (robbed) of children (whelps).
or shikkor; from שָׁכַר; intoxicated, as a state or a habit: drunk(-ard, -en, -en man).
or shakeach; a primitive root; to mislay, i.e. to be oblivious of, from want of memory or attention: X at all, (cause to) forget.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁכַח through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing; to discover (literally or figuratively): find.
from שָׁכַח; oblivious: forget.
feminine from the same as שֶׂ֫כוּ; a conspicuous object: picture.
intensive perhaps from the same as שֶׂ֫כוּ in the sense of שׂוּך; a knife (as pointed or edged): knife.
from שָׂכַר; a man at wages by the day or year: hired (man, servant), hireling.
feminine of שָׂכִיר; a hiring: that is hired.
a primitive root; to weave (i.e. lay) a trap; figuratively, (through the idea of secreting) to allay (passions; physically, abate a flood): appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make or act) circumspect and hence, intelligent: consider, expert, instruct, prosper, (deal) prudent(-ly), (give) skill(-ful), have good success, teach, (have, make to) understand(-ing), wisdom, (be, behave self, consider, make) wise(- ly), guide wittingly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׂכַל: consider.

a primitive root; properly, to miscarry, i.e. suffer abortion; by analogy, to bereave (literally or figuratively): bereave (of children), barren, cast calf (fruit, young), be (make) childless, deprive, destroy, X expect, lose children, miscarry, rob of children, spoil.
or sekel; from שָׂכַל; intelligence; by implication, success: discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise.
plural from שָׁכֹל; childlessness (by continued bereavements): to have after loss of others.
(Aramaic) from שְׂכַל; intelligence: understanding.

a primitive root; properly, to incline (the shoulder to a burden); but used only as denominative from שְׁכֶם; literally, to load up (on the back of man or beast), i.e. to start early in the morning: (arise, be up, get (oneself) up, rise up) early (betimes), morning.
from שָׁכַם; the neck (between the shoulders) as the place of burdens; figuratively, the spur of a hill: back, X consent, portion, shoulder.
the same as שְׁכֶם; ridge; Shekem, a place in Palestine: Shechem.
for שְׁכֶם; Shekem, the name of a Hivite and two Israelites: Shechem.
feminine of שְׁכֶם; the shoulder-bone: shoulder blade.
patronymic from שֶׁ֫כֶם; a Shikmite (collectively), or descendants of Shekem: Shichemites.

a primitive root (apparently akin (by transmission) to שָׁכַב through the idea of lodging; compare סִכְלוּת, שָׁכַם); to reside or permanently stay (literally or figuratively): abide, continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-er), have habitation, inhabit, lay, place, (cause to) remain, rest, set (up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁכַן: cause to dwell, have habitation.
from שָׁכַן; a residence: habitation.
from שָׁכַן; a resident; by extension, a fellow-citizen: inhabitant, neighbour, nigh.
or (prol.) Shkanyahuw; from שָׁכַן and יָהּ; Jah has dwelt; Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites: Shecaniah, Shechaniah.

or (by permutation) cakar (Ezra 4:5); a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to כָּרָה through the idea of temporary purchase; compare שָׁכַר); to hire: earn wages, hire (out self), reward, X surely.

a primitive root; to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence: (be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of שָׁקָה.)
from שָׂכַר; wages: reward, sluices.
from שָׂכַר; payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit: hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth.
the same as שָׂכָר; recompense; Sakar, the name of two Israelites: Sacar.
from שָׁכַר; an intoxicant, i.e. intensely alcoholic liquor: strong drink, + drunkard, strong wine.
for שִׁכָּרוֹן; drunkenness, Shikkeron, a place in Palestine: Shicron.
from שָׁכַר; intoxication: (be) drunken(-ness).
from שָׁלָה abbrev.; a fault: error.
for the rel. אֲשֶׁר; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix; on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever: cause, sake.
for שַׁאֲנָן; tranquil: being at ease.
a primitive root; to space off; intensive (evenly) to make equidistant: equally distant, set in order.
from שָׁלַב; a spacer or raised interval, i.e. the stile in a frame or panel: ledge.
a primitive root; properly, meaning to be white; used only as denominative from שָׁ֫לֶג; to be snow-white (with the linen clothing of the slain): be as snow.
from שָׁלַג; snow (probably from its whiteness): snow(-y).
or shalav (Job 3:26); a primitive root; to be tranquil, i.e. secure or successful: be happy, prosper, be in safety.
a primitive root (probably identical with שָׁלָה through the idea of educing); to mislead: deceive, be negligent.
a primitive root (rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of נָשַׁל, שָׁלַל and their congeners through the idea of extracting); to draw out or off, i.e. remove (the soul by death): take away.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁלָה; to be secure: at rest.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to שָׁלָה; a wrong: thing amiss.
the same as שְׁאֵלָה (shortened); request; Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite: Shelah.
from the same as לַ֫הַב with sibilant prefix; a flare of fire: (flaming) flame.
or slayv; by orthographical variation from שָׁלָה through the idea of sluggishness; the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight): quails.
from שָׁלָה; security: prosperity.
(Aramaic) or shaluwth (Aramaic); from the same as שָׁלֻה; a fault: error, X fail, thing amiss.
or shaleyv; feminine shlevah; from שָׁלָה; tranquil; (in a bad sense) careless; abstractly, security: (being) at ease, peaceable, (in) prosper(-ity), quiet(-ness), wealthy.
from שָׁלָה; security (genuine or false): abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שַׁלְוָה; safety: tranquillity. See also שָׁלֵיו.
or shilluach; from שָׁלַח; (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower: presents, have sent back.

or shalom; from שָׁלַם; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. health, prosperity, peace: X do, familiar, X fare, favour, + friend, X great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, X wholly.
or shillum; from שָׁלַם; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee: recompense, reward.
or (shorter) Shallum; the same as שִׁלּוּם; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites: Shallum.
probably for שַׁלּוּם; Shallun, an Israelite: Shallum.

or shalosh; masculine shlowshah; or shloshah; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) thrice: + fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare שָׁלִישׁ.
or shloshiym; multiple of שָׁלוֹשׁ; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth: thirty, thirtieth. Compare שָׁלִישׁ.

a primitive root; to send away, forth, or out (in a great variety of applications): X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, X earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁלַח: put, send.
from שָׁלַח; a missile of attack, i.e. spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. branch: dart, plant, X put off, sword, weapon.
the same as שָׁ֫לַח; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch: Salah, Shelah. Compare שִׁלֹ֫חַ.
or (in imitation of שָׁ֫לַח) Shelach (Neh. 3:15); from שָׁלַח; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of JerusalemShiloah, Siloah.
feminine of שִׁלּוּחִים; a shoot: branch.
from שָׁ֫לַח; missive, i.e. armed; Shilchi, an Israelite: Shilhi.
plural of שָׁ֫לַח; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine: Shilhim.
from שָׁלַח; a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal: table.
a primitive root; to dominate, i.e. govern; by implication, to permit: (bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁלַט: have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler.
from שָׁלַט; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. protecting the person): shield.
(Aramaic) from שָׁלַט; a potentate; --power.
(Aramaic) or shilton (Aramaic); corresponding to שִׁלְטוֹן: ruler.
(Aramaic) from שְׁלֵט; empire (abstractly or concretely): dominion.
feminine from שָׁלַט; a vixen: imperious.
from שָׁלָה; privacy: + quietly.
feminine from שָׁלָה; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth): young one.
from שָׁלַט; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior: governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שַׁלִּיט; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier: captain, be lawful, rule(- r).

or shalowsh ( 1 Chron. 11:11; 12:18); or shalosh (2 Sam. 23:13); from שָׁלוֹשׁ; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute); also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah); also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. the highest): captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin).
ordinal from שָׁלוֹשׁ; third; feminine a third (part); by extension, a third (day, year or time); specifically, a third-story cell): third (part, rank, time), three (years old).
a primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively): adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.
from שָׁלַך; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea): cormorant.
from שָׁלַך; a felling (of trees): when cast.
the same as שַׁלֶּ֫כֶת; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem: Shalleketh.
a primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder: let fall, make self a prey, X of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.
from שָׁלַל; booty: prey, spoil.

a primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate); figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications): make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁלַם; to complete, to restore: deliver, finish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁלוֹם; prosperity: peace.
from שָׁלַם; properly, requital, i.e. a (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks: peace offering.
from שָׁלַם; complete (literally or figuratively); especially friendly: full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfect(-ed), quiet, Shalem (by mistake for a name), whole.
the same as שָׁלֵם; peaceful; Shalem, an early name of Jerusalem: Salem.
from שָׁלַם; requital: recompense.
the same as שִׁלֵּם; Shillem, an Israelite: Shillem.
probably for שַׂלְמָה; clothing; Salma, the name of two Israelites: Salma.
transp. for שִׂמְלָה; a dress: clothes, garment, raiment.
the same as שַׂלְמָה; clothing; Salmah, an Israelite: Salmon. Compare שַׂלְמוֹן.
from שָׁלוֹם; peaceful; Shelomah, David's successor: Solomon.
feminine of שִׁלּוּם; retribution: recompense.
from שַׂלְמָה; investiture; Salmon, an Israelite: Salmon. Compare שַׂלְמָה.
feminine plural of שָׁלוֹם; pacifications; Shelomoth, the name of two Israelites: Shelomith (from the margin), Shelomoth. Compare שְׁלֹמִית.
from שַׂלְמָה; clothed; Salmai, an Israelite: Shalmai.
from שָׁלוֹם; peaceable; Shelomi, an Israelite: Shelomi.
patronymically from שִׁלֵּם; a Shilemite (collectively) or descendants of Shillem: Shillemites.
from שָׁלוֹם and אֵל; peace of God; Shelumiel, an Israelite: Shelumiel.
or Shelemyahuw; from שֶׁ֫לֶם and יָהּ; thank-offering of Jah; Shelemjah, the name of nine Israelites: Shelemiah.
or Shlowmiyth (Ezra 8:10); from שָׁלוֹם; peaceableness; Shelomith, the name of five Israelites and three Israelitesses: Shelomith.
of foreign derivation; Shalman, a king apparently of Assyria: Shalman. Compare שַׁלְמַנְאֶ֫סֶר.
from שָׁלַם; a bribe: reward.
of foreign derivation; Shalmaneser, an Assyrian king: Shalmaneser. Comp שַׁלְמַן.
the same as שִׁילוֹנִי; Shiloni, an Israelite: Shiloni.
from שֵׁלָה; a Shelanite (collectively), or descendants of Shelah: Shelanites.
a primitive root; to pull out, up or off: draw (off), grow up, pluck off.
from שָׁלַף; extract; Sheleph, a son of Jokthan: Sheleph.

a primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. treble; but apparently used only as denominative from שָׁלוֹשׁ, to be (causatively, make) triplicate (by restoration, in portions, strands, days or years): do the third time, (divide into, stay) three (days, - fold, parts, years old).
from שָׁלַשׁ; triplet; Shelesh, an Israelite: Shelesh.
from שָׁלַשׁ; a descendant of the third degree, i.e. great grandchild: third (generation).
feminine from the same as שֵׁ֫לֶשׁ; triplication; Shilshah, an Israelite: Shilshah.
feminine from שָׁלַשׁ; trebled land; Shalishah, a place in Palestine: Shalisha.
or shilshom; from the same as שֵׁ֫לֶשׁ; trebly, i.e. (in time) day before yesterday: + before (that time, - time), excellent things (from the margin), + heretofore, three days, + time past.
a primitive particle (rather from the relative pronoun, אֲשֶׁר); there (transferring to time) then; often thither, or thence: in it, + thence, there (-in, + of, + out), + thither, + whither.

a primitive word (perhaps rather from שׂוּם through the idea of definite and conspicuous position; compare שָׁמַ֫יִם); an appellation, as a mark or memorial of individuality; by implication honor, authority, character: + base, (in-)fame(-ous), named(-d), renown, report.
the same as שֵׁם; name; Shem, a son of Noah (often includ. his posterity): Sem, Shem.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שֵׁם: name.
from שָׁמֵם; desolation; Shamma, an Israelite: Shamma.
apparently from שֵׁם and אֵ֫בֶר; name of pinion, i.e. illustrious; Shemeber, a king of Zeboim: Shemeber.
perhaps for שִׁמְעָה; Shimah, an Israelite: Shimah. Compare שִׁמְאָם.

or smosl; a primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as שִׂמְלָה (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up); properly, dark (as enveloped), i.e. the north; hence (by orientation), the left hand: left (hand, side).
a primitive root (denominative from שְׂמֹאול); to use the left hand or pass in that direction): (go, turn) (on the, to the) left.
from שְׂמֹאול; situated on the left side: left.
for שִׁמְאָה (compare אֲבִיָּם); Shimam, an Israelite: Shimeam.
of uncertain derivation; Shamgar, an Israelite judge: Shamgar.
a primitive root; to desolate: destroy(- uction), bring to nought, overthrow, perish, pluck down, X utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁמַד: consume.
from שָׁמֵם; ruin; by implication, consternation: astonishment, desolate(-ion), waste, wonderful thing.
the same as שַׁמָּה; Shammah, the name of an Edomite and four Israelites: Shammah.
for שַׁמָּה; desolation; Shamhuth, an Israelite: Shamhuth.
from the passive participle of שָׁמַע and אֵל; heard of God; Shemuel, the name of three Israelites: Samuel, Shemuel.
from שָׁמֵם; renowned; Shammua, the name of four Israelites: Shammua, Shammuah.
feminine passive participle of שָׁמֵם; something heard, i.e. an announcement: bruit, doctrine, fame, mentioned, news, report, rumor, tidings.
passive participle of שִׁמְצָה; observed; Shamur, an Israelite: Shamir (from the margin).
plural of שַׁמָּה; ruins; Shammoth, an Israelite: Shamoth.

a primitive root; probably to brighten up, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) blithe or gleesome: cheer up, be (make) glad, (have, make) joy(-ful), be (make) merry, (cause to, make to) rejoice, X very.
from שָׂמַח; blithe or gleeful: (be) glad, joyful, (making) merry((-hearted), -ily), rejoice(-ing).
from שָׂמֵ֫חַ; blithesomeness or glee, (religious or festival): X exceeding(-ly), gladness, joy(-fulness), mirth, pleasure, rejoice(-ing).
a primitive root; to fling down; incipiently to jostle; figuratively, to let alone, desist, remit: discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down.
from שָׁמַט; remission (of debt) or suspension of labor): release.
from שַׁמְלַי; destructive; Shammai, the name of three Israelites: Shammai.
apparently from שֵׁם and יָדַע; name of knowing; Shemida, an Israelite: Shemida, Shemidah.
patronymically from שְׁמִידָע; a Shemidaite (collectively) or descendants of Shemida: Shemidaites.
from סָמַך; a run (as sustaining the Oriental sitter): mantle.

dual of an unused singular shameh; from an unused root meaning to be lofty; the sky (as aloft; the dual perhaps alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve): air, X astrologer, heaven(-s).
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁמַ֫יִם: heaven.
from שְׁמֹנֶה; eight: eight.
feminine of שְׁמִינִי; probably an eight-stringed lyre: Sheminith.
from שָׁמַר in the original sense of pricking; a thorn; also (from its keenness for scratching) a gem, probably the diamond: adamant (stone), brier, diamond.
the same as שָׁמִיר; Shamir, the name of two places in Palestine: Shamir. Compare שָׁמוּר.
or Shmariymowth; probably from שֵׁם and plural of רָמָה; name of heights; Shemiramoth, the name of two Israelites: Shemiramoth.

perhaps by permutation for the feminine of סֵ֫מֶל (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath); a dress, especially a mantle: apparel, cloth(-es, -ing), garment, raiment. Compare שַׂלְמָה.
probably for the same as שִׂמְלָה; Samlah, an Edomite: Samlah.
for שַׁלְמָי; Shamlai, one of the Nethinim: Shalmai (from the margin).

a primitive root; to stun (or intransitively, grow numb), i.e. devastate or (figuratively) stupefy (both usually in a passive sense): make amazed, be astonied, (be an) astonish(-ment), (be, bring into, unto, lay, lie, make) desolate(-ion, places), be destitute, destroy (self), (lay, lie, make) waste, wonder.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁמֵם: be astonied.
from שָׁמֵם; ruined: desolate.
or shimamah; feminine of שָׁמֵם; devastation; figuratively, astonishment: (laid, X most) desolate(- ion), waste.
from שָׁמֵם; stupefaction: astonishment.
probably from שָׁמֵם (in the sense of poisoning); a lizard (from the superstition of its noxiousness): spider.
a primitive root; to shine, i.e. (by analogy) be (causatively, make) oily or gross: become (make, wax) fat.
from שָׁמַן; grease, especially liquid (as from the olive, often perfumed); figuratively, richness: anointing, X fat (things), X fruitful, oil((-ed)), ointment, olive, + pine.
from שָׁמַן; greasy, i.e. gross; figuratively, rich: fat, lusty, plenteous.

or shmowneh; feminine shmonah; or shmownah; apparently from שָׁמֵן through the idea of plumpness; a cardinal number, eight (as if a surplus above the "perfect" seven); also (as ordinal) eighth: eight((-een, -eenth)), eighth.
or shmowniym; mult. from שְׁמֹנֶה; eighty, also eightieth: eighty(-ieth), fourscore.

a primitive root; to hear intelligently (often with implication of attention, obedience, etc.; causatively, to tell, etc.): X attentively, call (gather) together, X carefully, X certainly, consent, consider, be content, declare, X diligently, discern, give ear, (cause to, let, make to) hear(-ken, tell), X indeed, listen, make (a) noise, (be) obedient, obey, perceive, (make a) proclaim(-ation), publish, regard, report, shew (forth), (make a) sound, X surely, tell, understand, whosoever (heareth), witness.
(Aramaic) corresponding to שָׁמַע: hear, obey.
for the same as שֵׁ֫מַע; Shema, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites: Shema.
from שָׁמַע; something heard, i.e. a sound, rumor, announcement; abstractly, audience: bruit, fame, hear(-ing), loud, report, speech, tidings.
from שָׁמַע; a report: fame.
for שֶׁ֫מַע; Shema, a place in Palestine: Shema.
from שָׁמַע; obedient; Shama, an Israelite: Shama.
for שִׁמְעָה; Shima, the name of four Israelites: Shimea, Shimei, Shamma.
feminine of שֵׁ֫מַע; annunciation; Shimah, an Israelite: Shimeah.
for שִׁמְעָה; Shemaah, an Israelite: Shemaah.
from שָׁמַע; hearing; Shimon, one of Jacob's sons, also the tribe descended from him: Simeon.
